  {
    "name": "Marine Sidearm",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/9/90/Marine_Sidearm.png/revision/latest?cb=20160310051052",
    "notes": "Starting gun of The Marine . Does not crack secret walls .",
    "quote": "Always With You",
    "quality": "N",
    "type": "Semiautomatic",
    "dps": "15.6",
    "magazine_size": "10",
    "ammo_capacity": "",
    "damage": "5",
    "fire_rate": "0.25",
    "reload_time": "1.2",
    "shot_speed": "25",
    "range": "18",
    "force": "12",
    "spread": "5",
    "class": "SHITTY",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Cannot be dropped."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Is technically automatic, as tapping the fire button does not provide a faster fire rate than holding it down."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "After defeating "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "The Marine",
              "kind": "character"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "'s past with his alternate skin, an alternate skin of this weapon is unlocked.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Bullets become slightly bigger with the alternate skin."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "While it is impossible to see in-game due to the gun having the infinite ammo variable set to true, the Marine Sidearm has a maximum ammo of 350."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The final line of the Marine Sidearms Ammonomicon description draws a thematic link between the gun and the Marine himself. Although both appear tough, both have failed when others relied upon them. For example, how the Marine ran from the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Interdimensional Horror",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", leaving the research staff and other marines to die."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The entry for the Marine Sidearm in the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Physical Ammonomicon",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " has a small doodle of the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "The Marine",
              "kind": "character"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
