  {
    "name": "Slinger",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/f/f4/Slinger.png/revision/latest?cb=20190406101659",
    "notes": "Starting weapon of The Gunslinger . Reloading an empty clip throws the gun, which has a chance to stun enemies. Does not crack secret walls .",
    "quote": "Farewell to arms",
    "quality": "N",
    "type": "Semiautomatic",
    "dps": "22.4",
    "magazine_size": "7",
    "ammo_capacity": "",
    "damage": "6 (bullet) 4 (gun)",
    "fire_rate": "0.1 (Manual) 0.25 (Automatic)",
    "reload_time": "1.3",
    "shot_speed": "23 (Bullet) 19 (Gun)",
    "range": "1,000 (Bullet) 30 (Gun)",
    "force": "9 (Bullet) 40 (Gun)",
    "spread": "0",
    "class": "NONE",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The gun thrown when the clip is emptied is unaffected by some bullet modifiers — namely, those that increase damage and those that multiply the number of bullets fired (except for the Y.V. "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Shrines",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ").\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Omega Bullets",
                  "kind": "item"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " is excluded from this, as Omega Bullet's damage increase only applies to the thrown gun."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Slinger has a faster fire rate after a dodge roll."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Slinger fires faster when shot rapidly like a semi-automatic weapon, rather than holding the trigger like an automatic."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Slinger has zero bullet spread and its accuracy cannot be decreased, making it one of the most precise guns in the game."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Slinger is the fastest-firing of all the starter weapons."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Uniquely, Slinger has two reload animations. If reloaded with an empty clip, the Gunslinger will throw it and get a new one from his belt. If the clip is not empty, then the gun will spin."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The gun thrown when the clip is emptied will retain its original appearance even if the gun's appearance when held has been modified by an item, such as "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Platinum Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Slinger is one of the three weapons in the NONE "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Guns",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " that can be obtained in normal play, the others being the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Chamber Gun",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " and the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Kruller Glaive",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ".\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The Slinger being in the NONE class may be an intentional attempt to avoid skewing the Gunslinger's loot pools. Most character starters other than "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Blasphemy",
                  "kind": "gun"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " are in the SHITTY gun class, which makes many other low tier guns less common. Since many low tier guns have "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Synergies",
                  "kind": "lore"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " making them much more powerful, the Slinger being in the NONE class may be to prompt them to show up more often as the Gunslinger."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "trivia": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This gun was actually a cut gun from the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Advanced Gungeons & Draguns Update",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "While it is impossible to see in-game due to the gun having the infinite ammo variable set to true, the Slinger has a maximum ammo of 500."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This gun might be a reference to Borderlands. In it, the manufacturer Tediore's guns have the unique property that they are thrown as a grenade instead of being reloaded like other weapons. Furthermore, the challenge consisting of dealing damage using this mechanic is called \"Gun Slinger\"."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Slinger has a charge style projectile assigned to it that it is incapable of firing and is therefore rendered unused. This projectile is a duplicate of the basic projectile of the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Boxing Glove",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " and is likely developer error."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Blasphemy",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/2/22/Blasphemy.png/revision/latest?cb=20160310050332",
    "notes": "Starting weapon of The Bullet . Swings destroy nearby bullets. At full health, swings send out a piercing sword projectile. Does not crack secret walls .",
    "quote": "To The Point",
    "quality": "B",
    "type": "Semiautomatic",
    "dps": "Beam or Sword- 28.0 Both- 56.0",
    "magazine_size": "N/A",
    "ammo_capacity": "",
    "damage": "14",
    "fire_rate": "0.20",
    "reload_time": "1.0",
    "shot_speed": "26",
    "range": "",
    "force": "10",
    "spread": "10",
    "class": "SILLY",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Fires a piercing rainbow sword projectile when swung.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " This projectile is only spawned if the player is at full health. The "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "The Robot",
                  "kind": "character"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " is never considered at full health, and as such, cannot fire the sword projecitle."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "When swung, Blasphemy creates a wide arc that destroys enemy bullets caught within.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " This swing also deals 28 damage to all enemies within its arc, and pulls the player slightly forward in the direction aimed."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Bullets that would normally split into more bullets do not do so when destroyed by Blasphemy. This is especially beneficial for countering a number of Boss attacks."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Enemy lasers can also be cancelled by Blasphemys melee swing, however they must be hit by the swing at the origin point of the laser."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " Blasphemy does not need to reload, however pressing the reload button will perform a block, destroying all enemy bullets in a small radius around the player. Pressing the reload button again while performing a block will perform a 'double-tap reload', actually bringing up the reload bar. Double-tap reloads are required to trigger on-reload effects like the  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Hip Holster",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The hitbox of Blasphemy's swing extends slightly behind the player, allowing it to hit an enemy that is very closely behind the player by swinging forward. This effect is fickle and depends greatly on the direction the player is aiming."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The block effect of Blasphemy only destroys bullets at the very start of the animation, meaning that new bullets that come near after the block has already begun will not be destroyed."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The hitbox of blasphemy's main swing moves with the player, allowing them to slice through thicker bullet walls by moving and slashing."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "It is easier to perform a guard flash with controller input by remapping the reload button to the left bumper or trigger."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Quickswitching between Blasphemy and a secondary weapon in between guard flashes can cancel Blasphemy's reload time. Although this is a bit trickier, it allows its users to perform a faster guard flash."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "It is possible to perform a guard flash with a single press of the reload button, although it is considerably more precise."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Super Hot Watch",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " can make performing a guard flash considerably easier by pausing time to make the trick less precise."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "item_interactions": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Blasphemys firerate is not affected by the players "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Rate of Fire",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " stat."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Hip Holster",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ",  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Cog of Battle",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - Blocking with Blasphemy is not considered reloading, and therefore does not trigger on-reload effects. The player must perform a "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "double-tap",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " reload by pressing the reload button twice in order to trigger these items.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Cog of Battle",
                  "kind": "item"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " - Because Blasphemy never "
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "needs",
                  "style": "i"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " to reload, once an active reload has been hit, Blasphemy can keep the damage bonus permanently until swapping to a different gun."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Hip Holster",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ",  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Ring of Triggers",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - The player does not have to be at full health for these items to spawn Blasphemy's rainbow sword laser."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Betrayer's Shield",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - Blasphemys melee swing can damage the shields left by Betrayers Shield."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Alpha Bullet",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - The first sword beam after a double-tap reload will gain the effect of Alpha Bullet. Blocking with Blasphemy does not refill its hidden clip, and therefore does not grant the benefit of Alpha Bullet."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Omega Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - The sixth sword beam after a double-tap reload will gain the effect of Omega Bullets, as it is technically the last bullet in Blasphemys hidden clip- despite the fact that Blasphemy does not need to reload. Blocking with Blasphemy does not refill its hidden clip, and therefore does not reset the counter towards Omega Bullets."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Crisis Stone",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - Has no effect, but will play its sound effect regardless."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Key Witness"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If the player is at full health, Blasphemy will always fire an "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "AKEY-47",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " projectile in addition to its sword laser when swung."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Despite being a melee weapon, Blasphemy does not give any  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Curse",
              "kind": "stat"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Blasphemy is the only weapon that does not visually show a magazine size.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Despite this, it still has a hidden six-round magazine — it just doesn't need reloading."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Blasphemy cannot be dropped if obtained as a starter."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Because Blasphemy's melee attack is not a projectile, it cannot be blanked by "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Bombshee",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Blasphemy is one of the only two character starter weapons not in the SHITTY "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Guns",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", the other being the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Slinger",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Defeating "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "The Bullet",
              "kind": "character"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "'s past with its alternate skin will unlock a skin for this weapon. This alt form resembles a carrot to match the Bullets bunny alt skin."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Because Blasphemy does not need to reload, it mostly circumvents the  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Challenge Mode",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " Challenge Modifier. However, waiting 30 seconds or attempting to perform a block (the player does not need to perform a double-tap reload) will still trigger the modifier to switch to the next gun."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Performing a block with Blasphemy does not trigger the  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Challenge Mode",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " Challenge Modifier.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Double-tap reloading Blasphemy "
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "does",
                  "style": "i"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " trigger Thermal Clips, but only if the player has swung the sword exactly six times since the last double-tap reload."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "If the player is at full health, but has been reduced to a temporary 1/2 state by the  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Challenge Mode",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " Challenge Modifier, Blasphemy will still shoot sword beams."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The 'bullet arms' of "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Misfire Beast",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " cannot be destroyed by Blasphemy. The arms of the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Revolvenant",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "can",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " be destroyed by Blasphemy, but will instantly regenerate."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Beadie",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " created by the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Beholster",
              "kind": "shrine"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Mine Flayer",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " Claymores, "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "High Dragun",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " knives, and the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Resourceful Rat (Boss)",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " mousetraps all spawn in the form of projectiles, and as such can be destroyed by Blasphemy before hitting the ground and spawning."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "High Dragun",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "'s RPG rocket can be destroyed with Blasphemy."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "While it is impossible to see in-game due to the gun having the infinite ammo variable set to true, Blasphemy has a maximum ammo of 350."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Bullets super attack in the "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Punch Out!",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " phase of the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Resourceful Rat (Boss)",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " Boss shows him striking the rat with Blasphemy."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "  Possible Bug The special UI icon for Blasphemy's Alt Skin in the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Chinese Mobile Version",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " of "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Enter the Gungeon",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " appears blue. This is likely due to incorrect colour encoding issues when saving the file, as the same thing can be seen in other UI textures."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The function of Blasphemy, namely firing a sword projectile when at full health, is a reference to the classic "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Master Sword",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " from "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "The Legend of Zelda",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Legend_of_Zelda"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
