          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Stout Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - Stout Bullets functions on enemy bullets reflected by Casey, however because Stout Bullets functions based on the total distance travelled by a projectile, by the time it is reflected by Casey it will most likely have surpassed Stout Bullets threshold for 'close range' and will only gain the negative effect of the item, reducing reflected projectiles in damage and size.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "If the player is able to reflect bullets immediately after an enemy spawns them, they will gain the positive effects of Stout Bullets, however this requires good timing and being dangerously close to enemies."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "This means that Stout Bullets is most often actively detrimental to strategies which involve reflecting bullets with Casey."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Jammed",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " bullets and enemies do not deal additional damage when reflected/launched."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Firing Casey nudges the player forward a moderate amount. Be mindful near pits to avoid falling."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Casey can deflect the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "High Dragun",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " rocket attack, but the deflected rocket will not deal damage."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Most explosive enemies killed with Casey will have their explosion delayed, preventing unavoidable damage.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "This does not apply to explosive barrels or explosion from the  "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Challenge Mode",
                  "kind": "lore"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " Challenge Mode modifier."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Casey can reflect the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Killithid",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " bullet portals."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "If the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Bullet King",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " or "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Old King",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "’s Chancellor is launched into a boss, the Chancellor’s body will deal a large amount of damage to the boss it hits, killing both Bullet King and Old King in one hit.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "This does not work if the chancellor is jammed."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "This also works on most other bosses if you have spared the Chancellor, as sparing him can cause him to appear in other boss rooms."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "If Casey reflects a "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Bullat",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " while the enemy is in projectile form, it will teleport back towards the direction of the player at an elevated velocity equal to the speed it was reflected."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Although Casey is a D tier item, it is much better than other D tiers, with huge destructive potential with an enemy that shoots enough bullets. On top of this, it can clear out bullets similar to "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Blasphemy",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", making it very good for maneuverability."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "trivia": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This weapon is a reference to Ernest Thayer's 1888 poem "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Casey at the Bat",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Casey_at_the_Bat"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This weapon is also a reference to the Casey Bat from "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Earthbound",
              "url": "https://earthbound.fandom.com/wiki/Casey_Bat"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", also named after the poem."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The quote \"Nothing can happen until you swing the bat.\" is from "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "FLCL",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/FLCL"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The tagline “Batting .50” is a reference to .50 caliber bullets and "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Batting Average",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Batting_average_(baseball)"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " in baseball (a theoretical 0.500 being impossibly good)."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The top half of the bat is a shotgun shell casing, making its name a pun."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The fact that the weapon increases "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Curse",
              "kind": "stat"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " while being carried stems from the Gungeon rejecting melee weapons."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This gun is among those "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Gunsling King and Manservantes",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " can challenge the player to clear a room with."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Usually, opening a chest containing Casey causes it to appear on the right side of the chest, instead of the center."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Whenever the player finishes a round with a super punch in the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Resourceful Rat",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "'s Punch-Out!! phase, he will swing Casey at the player. Even if the player has Casey, The Rat will still use it and the player will be unable to."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Careful Iteration"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " synergy is likely a reference to Steve's bat from "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Stranger Things",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stranger_Things"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ". It should be known that it could also be a reference to "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Negan",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Negan"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " from "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "The Walking Dead",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Walking_Dead_(comic_book)"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Casey actually has two charged modules, similarly to a gun like the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Megahand",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", with the first projectile charging after 1 second, and being replaced by the second projectile after a further 0.25 seconds of charging. This can be seen in the dust cloud that appears below the player to indicate that a gun has been charged appearing twice in quick succession.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Despite this, both charge tiers have the exact same projectile, and there is no statistical difference between them. The purpose for this strange setup is unknown, and may be a bug or oversight."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "  Possible Bug The special UI icon for both Casey and  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Careful Iteration"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " in the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Chinese Mobile Version",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " of "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Enter the Gungeon",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " appear blue. This is likely due to incorrect colour encoding issues when saving the files, as the same thing can be seen in other UI textures."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Pea Shooter",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/0/09/Pea_Shooter.png/revision/latest?cb=20160305235549",
    "notes": "Fires peas.",
    "quote": "Baby's First Gun",
    "quality": "D",
    "type": "Semiautomatic",
    "dps": "10. 6",
    "magazine_size": "6",
    "ammo_capacity": "1000",
    "damage": "4",
    "fire_rate": "0.15",
    "reload_time": "1.5",
    "shot_speed": "20",
    "range": "20",
    "force": "3",
    "spread": "10",
    "class": "SHITTY",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "A peashooter is a type of toy blowgun. The term \"pea shooter\" is also used derogatorily to describe a weak, small-caliber firearm."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Pea Shooter is given to you by "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Ser Manuel",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " in the tutorial."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Pea Shooter may be a reference to the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Plants Vs. Zombies",
              "url": "https://plantsvszombies.fandom.com/wiki/Main_Page"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " series, where a plant named the Peashooter is usually the very first plant that the player obtains, also fires peas, and is also relatively weak, yet has a low cost, making it decent late game.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "This is supported by its synergy with Cactus, which also appears as a thorn or needle-shooting plant in the Plants vs. Zombies series."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "It could also be a reference to Earthworm Jim 3D, where you can shoot peas out of a peashooter in the level \"Lord of the Fries\""
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This gun is among those "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Gunsling King and Manservantes",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " can challenge you to clear a room with."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The entry for the Pea Shooter in the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Physical Ammonomicon",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " has a small doodle of three peas (with faces) in a pod."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "38 Special",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/e/e9/38_Special.png/revision/latest?cb=20160310050218",
    "notes": "Fires faster right after a dodge roll.",
    "quote": "For The Inquisitive",
    "quality": "D",
    "type": "Semiautomatic",
    "dps": "26.5",
    "magazine_size": "6",
    "ammo_capacity": "350",
    "damage": "5",
    "fire_rate": "0.07",
    "reload_time": "0.78",
    "shot_speed": "23",
    "range": "35",
    "force": "10",
    "spread": "5",
    "class": "SHITTY",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "item_interactions": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Book of Chest Anatomy",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " +  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Detective Mode"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - Because Book of Chest Anatomy raises the chance of broken chests dropping an item to 55%, all chests effectively have a 55% chance to drop the item they were predicted to contain when broken."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Spamming the fire button while "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Dodge Roll (Move)",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " causes the gun to fire considerably faster for a brief time after the dodge roll has concluded."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "With a fire rate of 0.07, the 38 Special requires a minimum of ~14 clicks per second to fire at maximum DPS, meaning the player is likely to be unable to take full advantage of the high fire rate.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "This can be mitigated on PC by temporarily binding the player's fire keys to ScrollUp and ScrollDown on the scroll wheel."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The 38 Special is used by various detectives in a wide range of films and other media, hence the description."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This may be a reference to the Max Payne series of games, where the protagonist, a detective, slows down time when dodging, allowing him to fire faster and more accurately."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Detective Mode"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " synergy is a reference to the mechanic of the same name from the Batman Arkham games."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The entry for the 38 Special in the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Physical Ammonomicon",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " has a small doodle of a "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Bullet Kin",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " in a trenchcoat and fedora."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Derringer",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/0/01/Derringer.png/revision/latest?cb=20160310050559",
    "notes": "",
    "quote": "One Last Trick",
    "quality": "D",
    "type": "Semiautomatic",
    "dps": "15.2",
    "magazine_size": "2",
    "ammo_capacity": "200",
    "damage": "10",
    "fire_rate": "0.07",
    "reload_time": "1.2",
    "shot_speed": "23",
    "range": "60",
    "force": "30",
    "spread": "6",
    "class": "SHITTY",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Dead Prez"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If the player has the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Dueling Pistol",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", Derringer fires bouncing musket balls identical to the Dueling Pistol, and Dueling Pistol fires a wide spread of 4 bullets alongside its normal shots."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Thorn Bath, ooh!"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If the player has "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Armor of Thorns",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", Derringer's damage is increased by 30%. While Derringer is held in a room with enemies, thorns are periodically fired in all directions."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This gun is among those "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Gunsling King and Manservantes",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " can challenge you to clear a room with."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "trivia": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Unused and Cut Content",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - This gun used to be able to synergize with "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Barrel",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " for the synergy  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Like Shooting Fish"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "In real life, "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Derringers",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Derringer"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "  were very small, concealable pocket pistols that became very popular from the 19th century onwards. Also known as "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "palm pistols",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", they bear the name of their inventor, Henry Deringer. Most of them were single shot or - as in the model portrayed in game - double shot."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Dead Prez"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " synergy refers to the assassination of President Abraham Lincoln, who was famously shot by John Wilkes Booth using a Philadelphia Deringer. \"Dead Prez\" is also the name of a hip hop act."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The characters in game reload the Derringer through the use of a sleeve rig causing the weapon to disappear into their sleeve and reappear fully loaded a fraction of a second later. This is referenced with the flavor text \"One Last Trick\"."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Trank Gun",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/a/af/Trank_Gun.png/revision/latest?cb=20190406104939",
    "notes": "",
    "quote": "Non Non Lethal",
    "quality": "C",
    "type": "Semiautomatic",
    "dps": "47.6",
    "magazine_size": "12",
    "ammo_capacity": "200",
    "damage": "6.5",
    "fire_rate": "0.15",
    "reload_time": "1.2",
    "shot_speed": "23",
    "range": "60",
    "force": "30",
    "spread": "6",
    "class": "PISTOL",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This gun is wielded by "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Beadie",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Coaler",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", and the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Beholster",
              "kind": "shrine"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ".\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "As it is held by the Beholster, it can be placed on the "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Beholster Shrine?action=edit&redlink=1",
                  "kind": "unresolved"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Trank Gun is a reference to the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Tranq Gun",
              "url": "https://metalgear.fandom.com/wiki/Tranquilizer_gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " from the "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Metal Gear",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " franchise, in particular a modified Beretta M9 used in "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Metal Gear Solid: The Twin Snakes",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " and "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Metal Gear Solid 2: Sons of Liberty",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The synergy  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "I need scissors! 61!"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " is a reference to a nonsense line said by the corrupted "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Colonel Campbell AI",
              "url": "https://metalgear.fandom.com/wiki/Colonel_(AI)"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " during the final act of Metal Gear Solid 2: Sons of Liberty.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Additionally, the gun's appearance changes to look like the tranquilizer pistol from the Metal Gear Solid games."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " Fixed Bug Prior to v2.1.17 h1 for some players this gun is featured twice in the Ammonomicon."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Unfinished Gun",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/e/e8/Unfinished_Gun.png/revision/latest?cb=20160310051748",
    "notes": "Fires piercing bullets.",
    "quote": "Still Warm",
    "quality": "D",
    "type": "Semiautomatic",
    "dps": "20.9",
    "magazine_size": "15",
    "ammo_capacity": "350",
    "damage": "6",
    "fire_rate": "0.20",
    "reload_time": "1.5",
    "shot_speed": "15",
    "range": "35",
    "force": "6",
    "spread": "15",
    "class": "FIRE",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Despite not actually igniting enemies, the Unfinished Gun is in the FIRE "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Guns",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ".\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "As a consequence, having the Unfinished Gun in the player's inventory makes them less likely to find other guns in the FIRE class that "
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "actually",
                  "style": "i"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " burn enemies."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Blacksmith",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " can be seen working on an Unfinished Gun."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Certain elements of the Finished Guns design can be seen in the Unfinished Gun, such as the hourglass on its cylinder,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "During the development of "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Enter the Gungeon",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", many guns were prototyped as unobtainable weapons prior to updates that actually added them (for example, the  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Devolver",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "). Many of these prototype versions of guns used the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Ammonomicon",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " icon and/or description of the Unfinished Gun as placeholder. This suggests that the Unfinished Gun may have been used as a template."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The entry for the Unfinished Gun in the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Physical Ammonomicon",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " has a small doodle of an anvil."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " Bug After unlocking Finished Gun, Unfinished Gun can still be obtained as one of "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "The Paradox",
              "kind": "character"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "'s starting guns, as a reward from "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "The Lost Adventurer",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", as a reward from the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Gunsling King and Manservantes",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", in a synergy chess from "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Synergrace",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", during a "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Sorceress",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", a boss reward, or as one of the guns given when taking a "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Shortcuts",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Elimentaler",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/9/94/Elimentaler.png/revision/latest?cb=20180720005944",
    "notes": "Encases enemies in cheese, freezing them. Enemies that die while cheesed spawn a large cheese pool, which cheeses any enemies that step in it.",
    "quote": "Full of Holes",
    "quality": "1S",
    "type": "Semiautomatic",
    "dps": "29.0",
    "magazine_size": "15",
    "ammo_capacity": "",
    "damage": "Cheese ball: 5.5 Pointy cheese: 8 Cheese wheel: 15",
    "fire_rate": "0.22",
    "reload_time": "1.2",
    "shot_speed": "23",
    "range": "1,000",
    "force": "9",
    "spread": "0",
    "class": "PISTOL",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Fires chunks of cheese that "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Status Effects",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " enemies, encasing them in cheese and freezing them. Enemies that die while encheesed spawn a large cheese pool, which encheeses any enemies that step in it."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Has a 50% chance to fire a cheese ball that deals 5.5 damage, a 33.33% chance to fire a cheese wedge that deals 8 damage, and a 16.67% chance to fire a whole cheese wheel that deals 15 damage."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Elimentaler will not reveal secret room walls, nor can be fed to "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Muncher",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Enemies can be encheesed while in invulnerable states (such as "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Shelleton",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " while turning into a skull), forcing the player to wait until the effect wears off."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The pool of cheese left behind by enemies will put out the fireplace in the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Keep of the Lead Lord",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Elimentaler is one of the few guns in the game with perfect accuracy, with its accuracy unaffected even by accuracy reducing items such as "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Eyepatch",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Enemies such as "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Pinhead",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " and "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Nitra",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " will not explode if killed while encheesed."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Additional shots fired due to the effects of the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Shrines",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " will be of the same projectile type as the first shot of the burst."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The name of this gun is a portmanteau of \"eliminate\" and Emmentaler, a variety of Swiss cheese."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The reload animation is a reference to "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Babybel cheese",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Babybel"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The entry for the Elimentaler in the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Physical Ammonomicon",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " has a small doodle of the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Resourceful Rat",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Bullet",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/6/65/Bullet_%28Gun%29.png",
    "notes": "Fires rotating guns which fire bullets as they travel.",
    "quote": "Fires Guns",
    "quality": "C",
    "type": "Semiautomatic",
    "dps": "21.0",
    "magazine_size": "6",
    "ammo_capacity": "250",
    "damage": "Gun: 7 Bullet: 4",
    "fire_rate": "0.2",
    "reload_time": "1.0",
    "shot_speed": "?",
    "range": "?",
    "force": "?",
    "spread": "?",
    "class": "PISTOL",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Blammo!"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " -  If the player also has "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Shell",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", the guns are dual-wielded."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This gun seems to be in reference to two colloquial sayings that mean relatively the same thing - \"Firing a gun\" and \"Firing a bullet\". The meanings are swapped, but still technically are true."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The smaller bullets fired by launched guns are not affected by the player's "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Damage",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " stat.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "They are however affected by "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Bullet Modifiers",
                  "kind": "unresolved"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " and items that adjust projectile damage directly such as "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Cursed Bullets",
                  "kind": "item"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " or "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Gilded Bullets",
                  "kind": "item"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The entry for the Bullet in the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Physical Ammonomicon",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " has a small doodle of a "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Bullet Kin",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " firing the Bullet, which fires a gun, which fires a bullet kin holding the bullet, who in turn fires another gun."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Bullet is shown in the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "release trailer",
              "url": "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=x3YN0qhy8R8"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " for the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Supply Drop Update",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", with its fired guns shooting at a "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "much",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " faster rate than can actually be seen ingame."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
