              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If Hyper Light Drifter is combined with another gun using duct tape, its laser bullets will "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "still",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " restore ammo to the combination gun, regardless of if the Hyper Light Blaster is the base of the combination."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Friend to Gun and Bullet"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - Bullets fired from an orbiting Hyper Light Blaster will also restore ammo to the main gun."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Shot creatures do not need to be hostile to restore ammo to this gun. As such, shooting chickens and rats will still restore ammunition."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Shooting an enemy that is in the midst of its death animation will still restore ammo, as long as the enemy hitbox still blocks bullets."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Other shootable targets like "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Chests",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Cursed Pot",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", or explosive "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Barrels",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " will "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "not",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " restore ammo to the Hyper Light Blaster.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The initial shot used to awaken a "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Mimic",
                  "kind": "lore"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " does "
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "not",
                  "style": "i"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " count as landing a hit on an enemy, and will not restore ammo."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This gun, as well as its effect, is a reference to the game "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Hyper Light Drifter",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hyper_Light_Drifter"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ".\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The tagline is a quote from one of the monoliths seen in-game."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Despite this, Hyper Light Blaster behaves differently from Hyper Light Drifter's pistol, where hitting enemies with the "
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "sword",
                  "style": "i"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " restores ammo rather than the gun itself. This change is mentioned in its Ammonomicon entry."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The  "
                },
                {
                  "t": "synref",
                  "v": "Hard Light"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " synergy changes the gun's appearance from the pistol to Zaliska, another gun from Hyper Light Drifter. The name of this synergy references the melee weapons in the Hyper Light Drifter universe being made of hard light."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Whenever ammo is refunded, the center of the gun is opened, revealing a red, glowing core."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The entry for the Hyper Light Blaster in the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Physical Ammonomicon",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " has a small doodle of the main character of "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Hyper Light Drifer",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " swinging a sword."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "A depiction of the Hyper Light Blaster can be seen in the opening scroll of the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Supply Drop Trailer",
              "url": "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=x3YN0qhy8R8"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Boxing Glove",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/e/e1/Boxing_Glove.png",
    "notes": "Shoots a boxing glove with a chance to stun . Gains a star each time it kills an enemy, up to 3. When at 3 stars, can be charged to consume the stars and fire a high-damage super punch. Increases curse by 1.",
    "quote": "Pistol Hondo",
    "quality": "C",
    "type": "Charged",
    "dps": "30.0",
    "magazine_size": "350",
    "ammo_capacity": "350",
    "damage": "Regular: 12 Super: 200",
    "fire_rate": "0.40",
    "reload_time": "1.5",
    "shot_speed": "?",
    "range": "3.5",
    "force": "?",
    "spread": "N/A",
    "class": "CHARGE",
    "curse": 1.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Fires a limited range punch with a 30% chance to "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Stun",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " enemies for 3 seconds. Despite being a charged gun, the base punch has a charge time of 0 seconds, and can be rapid fired."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Killing an enemy with the Boxing Glove adds a star to the gun, shown on the UI above the ammo counter, to a maximum of 3 stars. Taking damage or switching to another gun will remove all accumulated stars."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Holding down the fire button to charge the gun with 3 stars will prepare a high damage super punch, consuming the stars.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "This super punch bypasses the "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Bosses",
                  "kind": "lore"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Non-boss enemies killed by a super punch are launched backwards in the direction they were punched, and can collide with other enemies, dealing damage. Unlike enemies launched by  "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Casey",
                  "kind": "gun"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": ", enemies launched by the Boxing Glove always deal a consistent 5.5 damage to foes they impact."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Enemies killed by a super punch will not spawn additional enemies on death (such as "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "King Bullat",
                  "kind": "unresolved"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " and "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Blobulon",
                  "kind": "unresolved"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": ")."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Enemies killed by a super punch will not drop any . "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Keybullet Kin",
                  "kind": "unresolved"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " and "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Chance Kin",
                  "kind": "unresolved"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " will not drop any pickups. "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Mimics",
                  "kind": "unresolved"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " will not drop any items or guns."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Increases  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Curse",
              "kind": "stat"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " by 1."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "item_interactions": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Flak Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - With Flak Bullets, each punch of the boxing glove will fire a spread of six small projectiles."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Duct Tape",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If Boxing Glove is duct taped onto another gun, "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "all",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " punches charged longer than 0.5 seconds will be super punches. It is difficult to see the Boxing Glove firing however, due to its projectile being invisible."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This gun is a reference to "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Mike Tyson's Punch Out!!",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Punch-Out!!_(NES)"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ". Its "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Ammonomicon",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " quote is a reference to "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Piston Honda",
              "url": "https://punchout.fandom.com/wiki/Piston_Hondo"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " (renamed in later games to Piston Hondo), one of the boxers in the "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Punch-Out!",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " franchise."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "It is also a reference to (and example of) the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Extendo Boxing Glove",
              "url": "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ExtendoBoxingGlove"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", which has appeared broadly in film, television, and literature."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Canonically, "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "The Gungeon",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " rejects melee weapons, viewing them as heretical. This is the reason why the Boxing Glove gives 1  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Curse",
              "kind": "stat"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "  Possible Bug The special UI icon for Boxing Glove in the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Chinese Mobile Version",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " of "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Enter the Gungeon",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " appears blue. This is likely due to incorrect colour encoding issues when saving the file, as the same thing can be seen in other UI textures."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The entry for the Boxing Glove in the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Physical Ammonomicon",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " is misprinted, with the Ammonomicon subtitle "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Gun Punch Man",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " instead of "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Pistol Hondo",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ".\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "This subtitle is a reference to the manga series "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ext",
                  "v": "One-Punch Man",
                  "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/One-Punch_Man"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "This entry in the "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Physical Ammonomicon",
                  "kind": "lore"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " is also accompanied by a small doodle of two characters boxing, referencing the appearance of the "
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Punch-Out!",
                  "style": "i"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " franchise."
                }
