  {
    "name": "Makarov",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/4/4c/Makarov.png",
    "notes": "",
    "quote": "The People's Gun",
    "quality": "D",
    "type": "Semiautomatic",
    "dps": "16. 6",
    "magazine_size": "7",
    "ammo_capacity": "350",
    "damage": "5",
    "fire_rate": "0.15",
    "reload_time": "1.2",
    "shot_speed": "23",
    "range": "60",
    "force": "10",
    "spread": "4",
    "class": "SHITTY",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This gun is based on the real life Russian firearm Pistolet Makarova (Makarov's Pistol)."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This gun's description references "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "The Cosmonaut",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", who was originally going to be found in the game as a "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Gungeoneers",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", but got cut during development. The gun may also reference the fact that before going into space Russian astronauts are given a gun."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "\"This gun is no better or worse than any other gun.\"",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " is a reference to equality under the doctrine of Communism, which was prevalent during the creation of the Makarov. The Makarov was also created and used by the Soviet Union (later Russia) as its standard issue handgun until the introduction of the MP-443 Grach in 2003."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "No Odd Job"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " synergy references "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "GoldenEye 007",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/GoldenEye_007_(1997_video_game)"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ". In its multiplayer mode, Oddjob is a character who is looked down upon and often banned in competitive play because his small hitbox confers an unfair advantage to players who choose him."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "M1911",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/b/b2/M1911.png",
    "notes": "",
    "quote": "Classic",
    "quality": "C",
    "type": "Semiautomatic",
    "dps": "26.0",
    "magazine_size": "7",
    "ammo_capacity": "200",
    "damage": "8",
    "fire_rate": "0.15",
    "reload_time": "1.2",
    "shot_speed": "23",
    "range": "60",
    "force": "30",
    "spread": "6",
    "class": "PISTOL",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This gun is one of the six guns wielded by the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Beholster",
              "kind": "shrine"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ".\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "As it is held by the Beholster, it can be placed on the "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Beholster Shrine?action=edit&redlink=1",
                  "kind": "unresolved"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The in-game description erroneously refers to the M1911's magazine as a clip."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Pulp Gungeon"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " synergy is referencing character "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Vincent Vega's use of a M1911",
              "url": "http://www.imfdb.org/wiki/Pulp_Fiction#Handguns"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " in the film "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Pulp Fiction",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pulp_Fiction"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The 1911 is based on the ubiquitous "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "45. ACP handgun of the same name",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/M1911_pistol"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " in real life."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "If the  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Pulp Gungeon"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " synergy is active, and the player has the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Cat Bullet King Throne",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", the orbiting gun will shoot a stream of bullets at the cursor location while the player dodge rolls."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The   "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Mmmmmmmmm MMMMmm!"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " synergy is likely a reference to the distinctive guitar notes prefacing each verse in \"Fortunate Son\" by Creedence Clearwater Revival. Both the song and all three guns are heavily associated with the Vietnam War."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The M1911 does not appear in "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Exit the Gungeon",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", however it still exists in the assets and text string database of the game. Like all real-world guns in Exit the Gungeon, the unused M1911 has a different name in the "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Apple Arcade",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " string database, where it is called the Standard Issue."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Magnum",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/9/90/Magnum.png",
