        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The quote \"5 shots or 6?\" is a reference to the film "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Dirty Harry",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dirty_Harry"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ".\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The gun's description also is a reference to Harry calling his magnum a filthy gun."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Reload Roll"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " synergy may be a reference to "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Cassidy",
              "url": "https://overwatch.gamepedia.com/McCree"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " from "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Overwatch",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", who has the ability to reload his revolver while performing a roll."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Wicked Sister"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " synergy may be a reference to the Gentlemen Bastard series by author Scott Lynch in which the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Wicked Sisters",
              "url": "https://camorr.fandom.com/wiki/Wicked_Sisters"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " are the twin hatchets serving as the primary weapons of one of the series’ two protagonists - Jean Tannen."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Magnum's altered form with the  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Wicked Sister"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " synergy was originally an unused standalone gun, also named Wicked Sister."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Detective Magnum"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " synergy is likely a reference to the 1980s crime drama "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Magnum, P.I.",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", a television series starring the titular character, Thomas Magnum, as a private investigator."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Two Magnums always appear in "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "The Cultist's Past?action=edit&redlink=1",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", one for each "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Co-op",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " player, to allow them to fight each other."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The unobtainable  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Magnum Titan",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " gun used by "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Titan Bullet Kin",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " appears to be an enlarged version of the Magnum."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Colt 1851",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/c/cd/Colt_1851.png",
    "notes": "Fires a burst of two bullets.",
    "quote": "You Dig",
    "quality": "C",
    "type": "Burst",
    "dps": "28.2",
    "magazine_size": "12",
    "ammo_capacity": "350",
    "damage": "6",
    "fire_rate": "0.21",
    "reload_time": "1.5",
    "shot_speed": "25",
    "range": "1,000",
    "force": "10",
    "spread": "8",
    "class": "PISTOL",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The description and pickup quote are referencing the gun's use in the film, "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "The Good, the Bad, and the Ugly",
              "url": "http://www.imfdb.org/wiki/The_Good,_The_Bad,_and_The_Ugly#Colt_1851_Navy_.28Cartridge_Conversion.29"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ".\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The name 'Blondie' used for the Colt 1851 in the "
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Apple Arcade",
                  "style": "i"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " version of Exit the Gungeon is a reference to the nickname given to the "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ext",
                  "v": "Man With No Name",
                  "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Man_with_No_Name"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " in the film by the character Tuco."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This gun is used in "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "The Hunter",
              "kind": "character"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " past.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Given such, it's likely that "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Rusty Sidearm",
                  "kind": "gun"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " is an old and rusty version of the Colt."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The name and design of this gun is based on the Colt 1851 Navy revolver."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The synergy Two Kinds of People is a reference to a scene in the film "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "The Good, the Bad, and the Ugly",
              "url": "http://www.imfdb.org/wiki/The_Good,_The_Bad,_and_The_Ugly#Colt_1851_Navy_.28Cartridge_Conversion.29"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " , in which a Colt 1851 is used to threaten someone digging up treasure. The Good is quoted as saying \"There are two kinds of people in the world: those with loaded guns and those who dig. You dig.\""
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The entry for the Colt 1851 in the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Physical Ammonomicon",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " has a small doodle of one cowboy forcing another cowboy to dig a hole in the desert. This is another reference to "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Good, the Bad, and the Ugly",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "SAA",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/8/8f/SAA.png",
    "notes": "Fires bouncing bullets that aim towards enemies after bouncing.",
    "quote": "Exhilarating Reload Time",
    "quality": "B",
    "type": "Semiautomatic",
    "dps": "43.6",
    "magazine_size": "6",
    "ammo_capacity": "200",
    "damage": "Direct: 8 Bounce: 12",
    "fire_rate": "0.12",
    "reload_time": "0.6",
    "shot_speed": "25",
    "range": "1,000",
    "force": "14",
    "spread": "0",
    "class": "PISTOL",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The SAA fires bouncing bullets that can ricochet up to two times. Bullets will moderately adjust the angle of their ricochet to hit enemies, and bullets that ricochet gain a 1.5x damage multiplier. \nThis damage multiplier stacks each time the bullet ricochets. Additional bounces above the guns inherent 2 can be granted by items such as "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Bouncy Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ". Bounces added by Bouncy Bullets also apply a 1.5x damage multiplier."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "In addition to this, the SAA is notable for its very rapid reload."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "SAA refers to the Colt Single Action Army."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "If combined with "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Angry Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", the shots fired from the SAA will often bounce around the room multiple times, great for fighting large, slow moving enemies."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The gun also contains multiple references to Revolver Ocelot from Metal Gear Solid, who uses the Single Action Army as his weapon of choice.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Exhilarating Reload Time",
                  "style": "i"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " is a reference to Revolver Ocelot's similar quote when he uses this gun, \"The reload time is exhilarating!\"."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "This weapon's ability to bounce bullets off of walls is a reference to Ocelot's ability to ricochet bullets."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The synergy  "
                },
                {
                  "t": "synref",
                  "v": "Pretty Good"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " is a reference to Ocelot's catchphrase from Metal Gear Solid, \"You're pretty good\"."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The SAA's spinning animation is a reference to Ocelot's tendency to twirl his guns."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "In Exit the Gungeon the Ammonomicon entry of the SAA is slightly altered to exclude the word 'Army'.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "While the resulting name of "
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Single Action",
                  "style": "i"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " matches with the name of the SAA in the Apple Arcade version of Exit the Gungeon, this description change affects all versions of Exit the Gungeon."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The entry for the SAA in the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Physical Ammonomicon",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " has a small doodle of Revolver Ocelot from the "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Metal Gear Solid",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " franchise."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Cold 45",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/c/c2/Cold_45.png",
    "notes": "Fires bullets that freeze enemies.",
    "quote": "Shatterday Night Special",
    "quality": "B",
    "type": "Semiautomatic",
    "dps": "25.3",
    "magazine_size": "12",
    "ammo_capacity": "350",
    "damage": "6",
    "fire_rate": "0.15",
    "reload_time": "1.2",
    "shot_speed": "28",
    "range": "35",
    "force": "10",
    "spread": "6",
    "class": "ICE",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Its name is a reference to the term \"Colt 45\" (which is likely the \"typographical error\" that the Ammonomicon Entry refers to). The \"Colt 45\" is a nickname for the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "SAA",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " or "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "M1911",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " handguns, as both are .45 caliber handguns manufactured by Colt. It is also the name of a malt liquor beverage commonly sold in a 40 oz. bottle."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "\"Shatterday Night Special\" is a reference to the term \"Saturday Night Special\", a nickname for a cheap, easily disposable handgun normally purchased in a hasty decision to commit a crime or suicide."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The yeti in the  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Why's Bullet's Crying?"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " synergy may be a reference to the yetis seen in "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Fork Parker's holiday profit hike",
              "url": "https://store.steampowered.com/app/339120/Fork_Parkers_Holiday_Profit_Hike/"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Polaris",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/a/a2/Polaris.png",
    "notes": "Has 3 levels. Killing enough enemies causes the gun to level up, increasing its damage. Taking damage decreases its level by 1.",
    "quote": "Storied",
    "quality": "B",
    "type": "Semiautomatic",
    "dps": "17.9-71.6",
    "magazine_size": "12",
    "ammo_capacity": "450",
    "damage": "Level 1: 5 Level 2: 12 (6x2) Level 3: 20",
    "fire_rate": "0.25",
    "reload_time": "0.6",
    "shot_speed": "40",
    "range": "1,000",
    "force": "30",
    "spread": "5",
    "class": "PISTOL",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Has three different levels, with the gun leveling up after enough enemies are slain. Higher levels deal more damage.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Killing 11 enemies will level up Polaris to level 2."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Killing 20 more enemies (31 total) will level up Polaris to level 3."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Taking damage reduces the level of this gun by 1.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The gun does not need to be currently equipped for taking damage to reduce its level."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Taking damage while the gun is at level 1 resets any progress towards the next level."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Dropping this gun will reset its level to 1."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "item_interactions": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Duct Tape",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - Duct taping Polaris onto a different weapon will duct tape each level of Polaris as a different module, causing the new gun to act like a shotgun."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Helix Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If Polaris is at level two, both bullets fired follow the same helical pattern, instead of crossing one another."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Polaris' level does not affect its selling price."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "While level 1 and 3 fire a single projectile of varying damage, level 2 fires two. Because of this, level 2 projectiles have "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "double",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " the probability of gaining chance-based bullet effects (e.g., "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Vorpal Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Katana Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Hungry Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", etc.)."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Losing hearts in ways that do not deal damage to the player, such as the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Vampire",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", do "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "not",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " affect the level of Polaris."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The symbol for reaching level 3 appears every time after killing an enemy once Polaris is at level 3 and it has killed a large amount of enemies."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Prior to the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Advanced Gungeons & Draguns Update",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", Polaris had 0.07 fire rate."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Prior to the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Supply Drop Update",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", Polaris had 400 maximum ammo."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This gun is a reference to the Polar Star from "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Cave Story",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cave_Story"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ".\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Cave Story's weapon leveling mechanics are also the inspiration for this weapon's abilities."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The \"two small tick marks\" refers to "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ext",
                  "v": "Quote",
                  "url": "https://cavestory.fandom.com/wiki/Quote"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " (\"), the main playable character of the game."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The synergy  "
                },
                {
                  "t": "synref",
                  "v": "Square Brace"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " is a reference to Curly Brace, a robot character in Cave Story."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Its altered appearance due to the  "
                },
                {
                  "t": "synref",
                  "v": "Square Brace"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " synergy is identical to the Machine Gun from the same game, which replaces the Polar Star upon obtaining it from Curly Brace."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Gummies",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " have no limit on the number of "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Cursebullet",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " they can summon. As such, a single Gummy can be farmed for enemy kills to fully level up Polaris."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The entry for Polaris in the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Physical Ammonomicon",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " has two small doodles accompanying it. One doodle is of the character "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Quote",
              "url": "https://cavestory.fandom.com/wiki/Quote"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", the other "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "King",
              "url": "https://cavestory.fandom.com/wiki/King"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", both from "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Cave Story",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Jolter",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/e/e6/Jolter.png",
    "notes": "Fires large rectangular bullets with high knockback.",
    "quote": ".95 Caliber",
    "quality": "B",
    "type": "Semiautomatic",
    "dps": "39.5",
    "magazine_size": "12",
    "ammo_capacity": "200",
    "damage": "13",
    "fire_rate": "0.25",
    "reload_time": "1.2",
    "shot_speed": "25",
    "range": "25",
    "force": "50",
    "spread": "10",
    "class": "PISTOL",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Jolter is a reference to the Warhammer 40k weapon, the Bolter, typically used by space marines. However, unlike the Bolter, the Jolter isn't an explosive weapon. The gun's sprites also reference the Bolter, as they are named Bolt_Rifle."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Having the Demon Head orbital while using the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Gun That Can Kill The Past",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " may crash the game and force you to restart the floor."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Synergy \"There is Only War\" is a reference to Warhammer 40k's iconic tagline: \"In the grim darkness of the far future, there is only war.\""
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The entry for the Jolter in the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Physical Ammonomicon",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " has a small doodle of a heavily armoured figure with a tiny head. This is likely a stylised reference to "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Space Marines",
              "url": "https://wh40k.lexicanum.com/wiki/Space_Marines"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " in the "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Warhammer 40k",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " franchise."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Dungeon Eagle",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/f/f6/Dungeon_Eagle.png",
