  {
    "name": "Vorpal Gun",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/9/9f/Vorpal_Gun.png",
    "notes": "Has a chance to fire a critical shot which deals 20x damage.",
    "quote": ".50 Criticaliber",
    "quality": "B",
    "type": "Semiautomatic",
    "dps": "23. 8",
    "magazine_size": "6",
    "ammo_capacity": "250",
    "damage": "Normal Shot: 5 Critical Shot: 100",
    "fire_rate": "0.10",
    "reload_time": "0.90",
    "shot_speed": "?",
    "range": "1,000",
    "force": "9",
    "spread": "8",
    "class": "PISTOL",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "A regular revolver pistol. Every shot has a 1% chance to be replaced by a crit-shot that instantly hits the nearest enemy in the direction the player is aiming, dealing 100 damage.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Crit-shots are more common the higher the player's "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Coolness",
                  "kind": "stat"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " stat is. Each level of coolness increases the percentage chance of firing a crit-shot by 1.\n"
                }
              ],
              "sub": [
                {
                  "tokens": [
                    {
                      "t": "text",
                      "v": "In "
                    },
                    {
                      "t": "ref",
                      "v": "Co-op",
                      "kind": "lore"
                    },
                    {
                      "t": "text",
                      "v": " mode, this effect is based on the combined coolness of both players, not just the one holding the gun."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Time will slightly slow for a moment when a crit-shot activates."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "item_interactions": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Any items which increase "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Coolness",
              "kind": "stat"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " (such as the  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Ballot",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " or  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Ice Cube",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ") greatly boost the Vorpal Gun's effectiveness by making crits more likely."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Scattershot",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - Time will no longer slightly slow down when a crit-shot activates. Crits are rolled per shot, so if the next shot will be a crit, all 3 shots will crit."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Smoke Bomb",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " /  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Grey Mauser",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " /  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "The Predator",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " /  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Box",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If the player is  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Status Effects",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", the Vorpal Gun will "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "always",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " crit."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Duct Tape",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If another gun is duct taped to the Vorpal Gun, bullets from that gun will also have a chance to be replaced by crit-shots. However, if the Vorpal Gun is taped onto a different gun, it loses the ability to crit."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Because crit-shots instantly hit the nearest enemy in the aimed direction, they do not interact with environmental objects such as "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Barrels",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", cannot break "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Chests",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " or "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Secret room",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " walls, or awaken "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Mimic",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The word 'Vorpal' is a nonsense word coined by Lewis Carrol in his nonsense poem '"
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Jabberwocky",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jabberwocky#:~:text=%22Jabberwocky%22%20is%20a%20nonsense%20poem,Adventures%20in%20Wonderland%20(1865)."
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "'. It describes a blade which is supposedly very sharp."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This gun is also a reference to an artifact type called \"Vorpal\" from "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Dungeons & Dragons",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dungeons_%26_Dragons"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", that upon a roll of natural 20 severs the head of those it strikes, in most cases instantly killing them."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Vorpal Gun also resembles the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Gunblade",
              "url": "https://finalfantasy.fandom.com/wiki/Gunblade_(weapon_type)"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " recurring weapon type from the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Final Fantasy",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Final_Fantasy"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " series, first introduced in Final Fantasy VII."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The entry for the Vorpal Gun in the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Physical Ammonomicon",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " has a small doodle of '20!' in block text."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "High Kaliber",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/b/b1/High_Kaliber.png",
    "notes": "Causes enemy souls to leave their bodies. Touching a soul deals high damage to the enemy. Each shot costs 6 ammo.",
    "quote": "Soul Reaver",
    "quality": "A",
    "type": "Semiautomatic",
    "dps": "33.0",
    "magazine_size": "66",
    "ammo_capacity": "666",
    "damage": "15",
    "fire_rate": "0.50",
    "reload_time": "1.0",
    "shot_speed": "22",
    "range": "25",
    "force": "13",
    "spread": "8",
    "class": "PISTOL",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Consumes 6 ammo per shot, effectively having an ammo capacity of 111."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Fires fat white maggots that can pierce once."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "On non-fatally piercing through an enemy, that enemy is marked and the projectile is converted into a spinning 'soul', continuing along its initial trajectory.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "These 'soul' projectiles do not hit enemies, and will be harmlessly destroyed upon impacting a wall or reaching the end of their range. They will also be destroyed by  "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Blank",
                  "kind": "shrine"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": ", as if they were enemy projectiles."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "If a player touches this soul, it will be destroyed, and will deal a huge amount of damage to the enemy to which the soul belongs, as well as dealing 5 damage to all other marked enemies in the room.\n"
                }
              ],
              "sub": [
                {
                  "tokens": [
                    {
                      "t": "text",
                      "v": "Non-boss enemies always take damage equal to their maximum health, instantly killing them in most cases."
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "tokens": [
                    {
                      "t": "text",
                      "v": "Boss enemies are always dealt 55 damage, bypassing the boss DPS cap."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Deals quadruple damage when fired while the player is  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Status Effects",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "item_interactions": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Scattershot",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " /  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Helix Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " /  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Backup Gun",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " /  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Double Vision",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " /  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Table Tech Sight",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - Each projectile that hits an enemy will spawn its own soul. The damage dealt by collecting souls is not affected by the players "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Damage",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " stat, meaning that Scattershot and Helix Bullets do not negatively affect it."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Remote Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - Rended souls will sluggishly follow the players crosshair/aim direction for a time."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Bouncy Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - Unspent bounces persist over to the rended soul, allowing it to ricochet up to two times."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Ring of Ethereal Form",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - Rended souls cannot be stepped on while the player is in ethereal form."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Orbital Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - Initial projectiles cannot rend souls while orbiting the player. Souls that hit walls while the enemy they belong to is alive will not orbit the player. Souls that hit walls after the enemy they belong to has been killed "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "will",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " orbit the player, however as they cannot hit enemies this is largely irrelevant."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Fat Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - Rended souls are larger in size, making them easier to step on."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " Possible Bug  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Helix Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - After converting into soul form, the souls will fly towards the player and stop in front of them, before continuing their initial trajectory. This makes the souls extremely easy to step on."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Souls cannot be stepped on during the player's I-frames after taking damage."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Stepping on a bosses soul can damage them even while they are in normally un-damageable states;\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "While "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Blobulord",
                  "kind": "unresolved"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " is split into smaller "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Blobulon",
                  "kind": "unresolved"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "-shaped bullets."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "While The "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Gorgun",
                  "kind": "unresolved"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " is underwater."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "While The "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Mine Flayer",
                  "kind": "unresolved"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " is concealed as a Bell."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "While "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Cannonbalrog",
                  "kind": "lore"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " is hidden in the black smoke."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "While The "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "High Priest",
                  "kind": "lore"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " is performing his dark room attack."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Both players in "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Co-op",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " mode can step on souls, regardless of which player holds the High Kaliber. The ghosts of dead co-op players can also step on rended souls."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "When fighting the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Ammoconda",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", souls only appear when shooting the head of the snake."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The stepping on rended souls can kill normally invulnerable enemies like the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Gunreaper",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " or "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Lead Cube",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The synergy  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Kaliber k'pow uboom k'bhang"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " is most likely a reference to the famous quote \"ph'nglui mglw'nafh Cthulhu R'lyeh wgah'nagl fhtagn\" of the H.P Lovecraft story "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Call of Cthulhu",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This gun is most likely a dual reference to both Soulcalibur, a fighting game series featuring a demonic blade that turns its host into a nightmarish abomination similar to what the Entry physically describes the gun as, and Soul Reaver, a spinoff game from the Legacy of Kain series starring an undead vampire that consumes the souls of his slain foes."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The damage done by stepping on enemies souls is referred to internally as "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "'Soul Burn'",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The maximum ammo of the High Kaliber is a reference to the biblical "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Number of the beast",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Number_of_the_beast"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " (666)."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
