  {
    "name": "AU Gun",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/0/04/AU_Gun.png",
    "notes": "Fires a single powerful bullet.",
    "quote": "Some Assembly Required",
    "quality": "1S",
    "type": "Semiautomatic",
    "dps": "80.0",
    "magazine_size": "1",
    "ammo_capacity": "22",
    "damage": "100",
    "fire_rate": "0.20",
    "reload_time": "1.2",
    "shot_speed": "25",
    "range": "1,000",
    "force": "10",
    "spread": "0",
    "class": "PISTOL",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "It is worth noting that due to the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "DPS cap mechanic",
              "url": "https://enterthegungeon.fandom.com/wiki/Bosses#Notes"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " existent in most Bosses, shots from the AU Gun should ideally be fired 3 seconds apart."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This gun is a reference to the Golden Gun from the James Bond movie "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "The Man with the Golden Gun",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Man_with_the_Golden_Gun_(film)"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ". The movie's villain, the assassin Francisco Scaramanga, uses the titular Golden Gun as his weapon of choice and boasts of only needing one shot per target.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "\"Some Assembly Required\" refers to the fact that in the film, the Golden Gun is assembled from a series of golden innocuous-looking items: a fountain pen (the barrel), a cigarette lighter (breech), cuff-link (trigger), and a cigarette case (the grip)."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The flavor text is a reference to the James Bond game GoldenEye 007 for Nintendo 64 (and subsequent James Bond games) where it was unique in that it instantly killed anything it shot."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Au is the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "chemical symbol",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gold"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " for gold."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The 22 ammo count likely references 22 karat gold, also known as \"Crown Gold\". The exception to this is "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "The Pilot",
              "kind": "character"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " whose bonus increases the gun's ammo by 10% to 24, which would reference 24 karat or \"Pure Gold\".  It may be tied to the flavor text.  \"It doesn't live up to the legends, but it comes close\" - The gun in the movie was 23 carat gold."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Klobbering Time"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " synergy is a reference to an iconic quote from "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "The Thing",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thing_(comics)"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", a superhero in the "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Fantastic Four",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " franchise."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The entry for the AU Gun in the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Physical Ammonomicon",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " has two small doodles accompanying it. One doodle is of three shining rounds, while the other is of a man in a suit.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The three shining bullets may be a reference to the "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ext",
                  "v": "Golden Gun",
                  "url": "https://www.destinypedia.com/Golden_Gun"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " super ability from "
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Destiny",
                  "style": "i"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": ", which gives the user the ability to fire three powerful shots."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Big Iron",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/c/c2/Big_Iron.png",
    "notes": "Fires a random spread of three bullets.",
    "quote": "Heavy",
    "quality": "B",
    "type": "Semiautomatic",
    "dps": "42.0",
    "magazine_size": "6",
    "ammo_capacity": "150",
    "damage": "21 (7x3)",
    "fire_rate": "0.33",
    "reload_time": "1.2",
    "shot_speed": "16",
    "range": "16",
    "force": "10",
    "spread": "4",
    "class": "PISTOL",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " Despite Big Iron using bullets in its ammo bar, shell cartridges come out of its compartment when reloading."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " Despite firing a spread of multiple bullets like a shotgun, the Big Iron is not in the SHOTGUN "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Guns",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", instead residing in the PISTOL class."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This gun is a reference to the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Marty Robbins",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Marty_Robbins"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "song of the same name",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Big_Iron"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The synergy  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Iron Slug"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " may be a reference to the game \"Metal Slug\"."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " The two bullets fired by the Big Iron each have different accuracy values. In addition, the second bullet fired is always aimed 10° from the barrel direction of the gun."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " Bug  If the player has both  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Cast Iron"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " and  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Iron Slug"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", but loses either synergy, Big Iron will fire regular bullets until a synergy item is dropped and picked up again."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
