  },
  {
    "name": "Knight's Gun",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/2/24/Knight%27s_Gun.png",
    "notes": "Fires five bullets in an arrow shape. Gains some pickups when reloading an empty clip.",
    "quote": "Plowshare",
    "quality": "A",
    "type": "Semiautomatic",
    "dps": "64.9",
    "magazine_size": "6",
    "ammo_capacity": "180",
    "damage": "40 (8x5)",
    "fire_rate": "0.4",
    "reload_time": "1.7",
    "shot_speed": "23",
    "range": "10",
    "force": "20",
    "spread": "?",
    "class": "SILLY",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Fires five bullets in a fixed arrow-shaped spread."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Upon reloading an empty magazine, the player digs into the ground with the gun, potentially unearthing one of a number of items from the below tables.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The Knight's Gun has a 50% chance to unearth an item from the Good Digs Loot Table so long as it has not already unearthed a good dig in the current room. Up to 5 'Good Digs' total can be excavated in a run."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "If the Knights Gun fails its 50% chance, or has already unearthed 5 Good Digs, it will instead dig up an item from the Bad Digs Loot Table."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The digging effect bypasses the item acquirement restrictions of "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Rainbow Mode",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "If the player has used "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Spice",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", drops have a chance to be replaced with more Spice (even the 1 casing after all good digs have been expended)."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This weapon is extremely powerful when playing as "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "The Robot",
              "kind": "character"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", as it frequently digs up Junk, which increases the Robot's damage."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The amount of \"good digs\" is reset upon saving and quitting between floors using the Save Button, allowing the player to get 5 more \"good digs\" after every floor."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Despite firing multiple bullets like a shotgun, the Knight's Gun is not in the SHOTGUN gun class, instead being classified as SILLY.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "This means that the Knight's Gun does not benefit from the  "
                },
                {
                  "t": "synref",
                  "v": "Shotgun Affinity"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " synergy."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This gun is a reference to the game "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Shovel Knight",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shovel_Knight"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ".\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The gun's ability to dig up bomb related items may be a reference to Plague Knight, who is a playable character whose play style focuses on using bombs. Bombs are also a common hazard in Shovel Knight that may be found in fake walls or when opening silver platters with the shovel."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The description is a reference to the creators of "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ext",
                  "v": "Shovel Knight",
                  "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shovel_Knight"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": ", "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ext",
                  "v": "Yacht Club Games",
                  "url": "https://yachtclubgames.com/"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The synergy  "
                },
                {
                  "t": "synref",
                  "v": "Shield Night"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " is a reference to Shovel Knight's partner, "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ext",
                  "v": "Shield Knight",
                  "url": "https://shovelknight.fandom.com/wiki/Shield_Knight"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": ", as well as her weapon of choice being a shield."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Synergy  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Two Kinds of People"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " is a reference to a line from the film 'The Good, The Bad, and The Ugly'.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "This synergy and the increase to 10 digs is also a reference to the joke '10 kinds of people', in which 10 is binary for two."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "\"Plowshare\" is a reference to a popular card in Magic: The Gathering called \""
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Swords to Plowshares",
              "url": "https://gatherer.wizards.com/pages/card/Details.aspx?multiverseid=446078"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "\"."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "GuNNER",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/2/25/GuNNER.png",
    "notes": "Taking damage while GuNNER is held drains 40 ammo and drops a skull that heals the player upon pickup.",
    "quote": "Backpack Not Included",
    "quality": "B",
    "type": "Semiautomatic",
    "dps": "27.5",
    "magazine_size": "12",
    "ammo_capacity": "200",
    "damage": "13.5",
    "fire_rate": "0.4",
    "reload_time": "1.5",
    "shot_speed": "27",
    "range": "1,000",
    "force": "9",
    "spread": "0",
    "class": "RIFLE",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Heads Up"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If the player also has "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Stone Dome",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", Stone Dome will shoot skulls instead."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Whale of a Time"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If the player also has "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Backpack",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", there's a chance a skull will spawn when getting hit to recover lost health, even if the player has another weapon equipped while getting hit."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Picking up the skull while playing as "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "The Robot",
              "kind": "character"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " will give you 1 armor."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "If the player has the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Holey Grail",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", then as long as they keep picking up the blue skull after getting hit and don't take hits from Jammed enemies/bosses, they will never run out of health and ammo.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "However, this is difficult as the Holey Grail also causes a blank each time you are hit, and the skulls disappear after a relatively short time. Items or guns that increase speed can assist with retrieval."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "If the player has "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Antibody",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", the skull has a chance to heal for a full heart."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The skull does not consume ammo if the player is under the effects of "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Magazine Rack",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The skull will not appear when feeding the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Vampire",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This gun can effectively trade armor for health, as damage to armor will still produce the skull. This may be useful if one wants to use "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Blasphemy",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " sword beam or sell health to the Vampire."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "trivia": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This gun is a reference to the game "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "GoNNER",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gonner_(video_game)"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ". It functions very similarly to the game's health mechanic - upon taking damage, the player loses their \"skull\", weapon, and backpack, and can pick them back up for more health.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The Whale of a Time Synergy is a reference to Sally, the helpful whale at the end of each of GoNNER's stages. The skulls spawning with any weapon is most likely a reference to how Sally gives the player health upgrades at the end of a stage."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Category:Guns",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
