  {
    "name": "Regular Shotgun",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/c/c6/Regular_Shotgun.png",
    "notes": "",
    "quote": "Cocked And Loaded",
    "quality": "D",
    "type": "Semiautomatic",
    "dps": "32.0",
    "magazine_size": "8",
    "ammo_capacity": "150",
    "damage": "24 (4x6)",
    "fire_rate": "0.60",
    "reload_time": "1.8",
    "shot_speed": "23",
    "range": "15",
    "force": "30",
    "spread": "10",
    "class": "SHOTGUN",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Regular Shotgun has an equip animation in which the gungeoneer racks the pump."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " The Regular Shotgun is in the SHOTGUN gun class, meaning it benefits from the  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Shotgun Affinity"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " synergy."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Regular Shotgun is the gun wielded by "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Shotgun Kin",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Shotgun Kin",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", and "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Shotgun Kin",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Regular Shotgun has nearly identical stats to the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Winchester",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", having a lower fire rate, slightly slower reload, and more spread, but more max ammo."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The name 'Regular Shotgun' was decided upon very early in "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Enter the Gungeons",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " development, and stuck as an in-joke with "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Dodge Roll",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " for how comically non-descriptive it is."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The entry for the Regular Shotgun in the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Physical Ammonomicon",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " has a small doodle of several "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Shotgun Kin",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", bowed in seeming worship to the weapon."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Big Shotgun",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/d/de/Big_Shotgun.png",
    "notes": "Fires three exploding shots that burst into bullets. Reloading next to Shotgun Kin sucks them up, killing them and restoring 1 ammo.",
    "quote": "A Shotgun That's Big",
    "quality": "A",
    "type": "Semiautomatic",
    "dps": "63.1",
    "magazine_size": "4",
    "ammo_capacity": "70",
    "damage": "Large: 45 (15x3) Small: 5.5",
    "fire_rate": "0.6",
    "reload_time": "2.1",
    "shot_speed": "?",
    "range": "1,000",
    "force": "?",
    "spread": "?",
    "class": "EXPLOSIVE",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " The maximum ammo of the Big Shotgun was increased from 50 to 70  in the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Farewell to Arms",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " update."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Despite being a shotgun, the Big Shotgun is not in the SHOTGUN "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Guns",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ".\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "As a consequence, the Big Shotgun is not affected by the  "
                },
                {
                  "t": "synref",
                  "v": "Shotgun Affinity"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " synergy."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This weapon is likely a reference to the \"Big Shotgun\" weapon pickup featured in "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Metal Slug",
              "url": "https://metalslug.fandom.com/wiki/Shotgun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Big Shotgun Gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " synergy is inherently a reference to the DOOM franchise, as the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "BSG",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " itself is a reference to the BFG-9000 from the DOOM series."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Reloading the Big Shotgun can \"defuse\" Red and Blue Shotgun Kin that are in the middle of their burst animation."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The entry for the Big Shotgun in the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Physical Ammonomicon",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " has a small doodle of a "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Bullet Kin",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " hoisting the weapon aloft."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Old Goldie",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/5/57/Old_Goldie.png",
    "notes": "Increases coolness by 1.",
    "quote": "For The Discerning",
    "quality": "A",
    "type": "Semiautomatic",
    "dps": "88.1",
    "magazine_size": "4",
    "ammo_capacity": "150",
    "damage": "35 (3.5x10)",
    "fire_rate": "0.50",
    "reload_time": "1.2",
    "shot_speed": "23",
    "range": "10",
    "force": "30",
    "spread": "5",
    "class": "SHOTGUN",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 1.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Fires a tight spread of shotgun pellets that deal significant damage, but have short range."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Increases "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Coolness",
              "kind": "stat"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " by 1."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Increases "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Damage",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " by 70% while held."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "When a gun is "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Duct Tape",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " to Old Goldie, it too will receive the 70% damage boost. However, when Old Goldie is duct taped to another gun, the damage boost is lost. Be sure to use Old Goldie as the base weapon to receive the boost."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Old Goldie is in the SHOTGUN "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Guns",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", meaning it benefits from the  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Shotgun Affinity"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " synergy."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This weapon's name is likely a play on \"Golden Oldie\", a nostalgic term used to refer fondly to old music or movies."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The synergy  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "The Ecstasy of Gold"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " is a reference to film composer "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Ennio Moricone",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ennio_Morricone"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "'s song of the same name. The most notable appearance of this song is in the movie "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "The Good, the Bad, and the Ugly",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Good,_the_Bad_and_the_Ugly"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This weapon references masterwork weapons from DnD, a type of powerful standard weapon without magical enhancements."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Sawed-Off",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/8/87/Sawed-Off.png",
    "notes": "Starting gun of The Convict .",
    "quote": "No Butts About It",
    "quality": "D",
    "type": "Semiautomatic",
    "dps": "25.9",
    "magazine_size": "6",
    "ammo_capacity": "150",
    "damage": "16 (4x4)",
    "fire_rate": "0.50",
    "reload_time": "1.2",
    "shot_speed": "23",
    "range": "8",
    "force": "30",
    "spread": "8",
    "class": "SHOTGUN",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Sawed-Off is in the SHOTGUN "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Guns",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", and as such benefits from the  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Shotgun Affinity"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " synergy.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "This also means that, according to the rules of how loot is distributed, holding the Sawed-Off makes finding other SHOTGUN type weapons more rare. It may be in the player's best interests to "
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "drop",
                  "style": "i"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " the Sawed-Off to increase their chances of finding a different, better shotgun."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Notably, this makes it the only starting weapon to "
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "technically",
                  "style": "i"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " be part of a synergy."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The animations of the Sawed-Off are physically inconsistent, with empty shells being ejected both on reload and the chambering of each new round."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The line \""
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "No Butts About It",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "\" is a pun on the 'butt' or end of the stock of the gun being removed (sawed off in this case). It might also be a play on the phrase \"no buts.\""
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The entry for the Sawed-Off in the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Physical Ammonomicon",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " has a small doodle of the Convict."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Winchester",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/e/e6/Winchester.png",
    "notes": "Slightly less bullet spread than the Regular Shotgun",
    "quote": "Better Than A Box Of Roses",
    "quality": "C",
    "type": "Semiautomatic",
    "dps": "36.9",
    "magazine_size": "8",
    "ammo_capacity": "100",
    "damage": "24 (4x6)",
    "fire_rate": "0.60",
    "reload_time": "1.7",
    "shot_speed": "23",
    "range": "15",
    "force": "30",
    "spread": "7",
    "class": "SHOTGUN",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Winchester is wielded by "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Blue Shotgun Kin",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The quote \"Better Than A Box Of Roses\" is a reference to a scene in the movie "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Terminator 2: Judgement Day",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Terminator_2:_Judgment_Day"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", where the Terminator pulls a Winchester out of a box full of roses.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "When reloading the Winchester, the player will spin the weapon backwards around the trigger hand. This is in imitation of what the Terminator does in the movie."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Winchester is inspired by the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "model of 1887 shotgun",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Winchester_Model_1887/1901"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " by the eponymous company. This gun was the first truly successful repeating shotgun, ahead of the invention of the pump action that eventually eclipsed the lever action. While it is possible to reload a lever action one-handed as seen in the game and movie, it is not recommended, as it puts a lot of strain on the reloading mechanism."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The entry for the Winchester in the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Physical Ammonomicon",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " has a small doodle of a rose."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Rattler",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/1/1a/Rattler.png",
    "notes": "Simultaneously fires a shotgun blast and a beam that has a chance to poison enemies.",
    "quote": "Snakes On A Gun",
    "quality": "B",
    "type": "Semiautomatic",
    "dps": "35.6",
    "magazine_size": "8",
    "ammo_capacity": "200",
    "damage": "21 (3x7)",
    "fire_rate": "0.20",
    "reload_time": "1.2",
    "shot_speed": "23",
    "range": "20",
    "force": "30",
    "spread": "0",
    "class": "POISON",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Fires 7 regular projectiles in a shotgun blast, and an instantaneous green laser that "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Status Effects",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " enemies.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Bullets from the main shotgun blast travel smoothly, and do not have the slight speed variance seen in other shotguns like the  "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Regular Shotgun",
                  "kind": "gun"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Despite visually appearing to be and firing like a shotgun, the Rattler is not a part of the SHOTGUN "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Guns",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " and as such does not benefit from the  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Shotgun Affinity"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " synergy."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The pickup line, \"Snakes on A Gun,\" is a reference to the film "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Snakes on a Plane",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Snakes_on_a_Plane"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Twin Snakes synergy is a reference to the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Metal Gear Solid",
              "url": "https://metalgear.fandom.com/wiki/Metal_Gear_Wiki"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " series."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The gun's name is likely a reference to the poem \"The Rattler,\" in which a man is confronted by a snake similar in color to the one wrapped around the gun."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The entry for the Rattler in the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Physical Ammonomicon",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " has a small doodle of a snake with a headband and cigarette. This is another reference to "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Solid Snake",
              "url": "https://metalgear.fandom.com/wiki/Solid_Snake"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " of the "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Metal Gear Solid",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " franchise."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Bubble Blaster",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/0/04/Bubble_Blaster.png",
    "notes": "Fires bubbles which move slowly towards enemies. Reloading the gun launches bubbles away from the player at high speed.",
    "quote": "The Suds",
    "quality": "C",
    "type": "Automatic",
    "dps": "105.3",
    "magazine_size": "100",
    "ammo_capacity": "500",
    "damage": "12",
    "fire_rate": "0.12",
    "reload_time": "1.4",
    "shot_speed": "N/A",
    "range": "15",
    "force": "10",
    "spread": "12",
    "class": "SILLY",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Rapidly fires slow moving bubble projectiles. These bubbles are off various sizes, but all deal the same amount of damage.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Bubbles create a pool of "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Goop",
                  "kind": "lore"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " when popping on impacting a wall, object, or enemy. This allows them to extinguish "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Chest",
                  "kind": "lore"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " fuses and the "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Fireplace",
                  "kind": "unresolved"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Only 10 bubbles can be in the air at once. Firing any more bubbles will cause the oldest bubble to instantly pop."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Reloading the Bubble Blaster prompts the lizard to burp, causing all nearby bubbles to quickly accelerate.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Bubbles always accelerate along their existing trajectory, regardless of their angle to the player."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " Possible Bug Pressing the reload key "
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "while",
                  "style": "i"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " the Bubble Blaster is already reloading will also cause nearby bubbles to accelerate. Spamming the reload key can allow the player to accelerate bubbles to great speeds."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Because the Bubble Blaster uses the "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Water",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " damage type, it deals 2x damage to "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Muzzle Wisp",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " and "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Muzzle Flare",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", and does not ignite "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Coaler",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ".\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The Bubble Blaster also puts out decorative torches and burning skeletons."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "item_interactions": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Battery Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " /  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Shock Rifle",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - Can electrify the water left by popped bubbles, dealing a considerable amount of damage to enemies that stand on it."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Scattershot",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " /  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Helix Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " /  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Double Vision",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " /  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Backup Gun",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " /  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Table Tech Sight",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - These items multiple the amount of bullets fired without raising the 10 bubble cap. This can severely inhibit the Bubble Blaster by causing it to hit the 10 bubble cap and pop the oldest bullets before they have been able to travel any practical distance.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Helix Bullets",
                  "kind": "item"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " - Bubbles fired travel in a helical motion, at a much greater speed than normal. Accelerating these helix bubbles by reloading the Bubble Blaster can cause glitchy behaviour, causing them to teleport forwards."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Shadow Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " /  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Hip Holster",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " /  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Y.V. Shrine",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - Extra bubbles created by these effects are independent of the 10 bubble cap."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Orbital Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - Bubbles in orbit around the player are still considered part of the 10 bubble cap. As bullets order close to the player, they can be accelerated to extreme speeds by mashing the reload button."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Bubble Blaster appears to be a  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Gunzookie",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ".\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Like the Gunzookie, the Bubble Blaster is a reference to "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ext",
                  "v": "Bub",
                  "url": "https://bubblebobble.fandom.com/wiki/Bub"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " from the "
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Bubble Bobble",
                  "style": "i"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " franchise, a green lizard that creates bubbles."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "This is further evidenced by the sprites of the Bubble Blaster being labelled "
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "bub_gun",
                  "style": "code"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Ammonomicon",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " quote "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "\"The Suds\"",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " is a reference to the "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Spongebob Squarepants",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " episode \""
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Suds",
              "url": "https://spongebob.fandom.com/wiki/Suds"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "\", where Spongebob contracts a disease that causes him to sneeze bubbles."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "While reloading, the Bubble Blaster takes a swig from a can of what appears to be  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Shotga Cola",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " Bug After firing the Bubble Blaster, it will not return to its idle animation until being reloaded, or until the player swaps to another gun. Instead, the lizard will linger on the first frame of its swelling firing animation.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "This also applies to the weapons out of ammo animation. After emptying the gun of its ammo, it will not begin to play its out of ammo animation until the player swaps to and from another gun."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The entry for the Bubble Blaster in the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Physical Ammonomicon",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " has a small doodle of what is either a "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
