  {
    "name": "Elephant Gun",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/a/a0/Elephant_Gun.png",
    "notes": "Fires a cone spread of bullets with high knockback.",
    "quote": "Shoots Elephants",
    "quality": "C",
    "type": "Semiautomatic",
    "dps": "31.4",
    "magazine_size": "2",
    "ammo_capacity": "120",
    "damage": "33 (5.5x6)",
    "fire_rate": "0.60",
    "reload_time": "1.5",
    "shot_speed": "23",
    "range": "15",
    "force": "30",
    "spread": "0",
    "class": "SHOTGUN",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " Fires a conical spread of bullets with strong knockback."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "So called "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "elephant guns",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elephant_gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " were large guns designed for the hunting of large animals (such as elephants) during safaris in Africa in the 19th century. Real-world elephant guns fired single large slugs, rather than shot.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The Ammonomicon description "
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "\"These guns were once used to make pianos out of teeth.\"",
                  "style": "i"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " is a reference to the practice of hunting elephants to harvest their tusks for ivory, a material once used to make piano keys."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Ammonomicon description "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "\"An inelegant weapon for a less civilized age\"",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " is a reference to the iconic line "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "\"This is the weapon of a Jedi Knight. Not as clumsy or random as a blaster; an elegant weapon for a more civilized age.\"",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " spoken by Obi-Wan Kenobi in the film "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Star Wars: A New Hope",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Star_Wars_(film)"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", in reference to lightsabers."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The appearance of the bullets fired by the  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "The Elephant In The Room"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " may be a reference to the euphemism "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "\"",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "seeing pink elephants",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Seeing_pink_elephants"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "\"",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", meaning to hallucinate."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The entry for the Elephant Gun in the "
            },
