  {
    "name": "Mass Shotgun",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/f/fb/Mass_Shotgun.png",
    "notes": "Shoots a large slow projectile that will split up in a barrage of small bullets shortly afterwards.",
    "quote": "My Favorite Gun",
    "quality": "B",
    "type": "Semiautomatic",
    "dps": "20.0/60.0",
    "magazine_size": "1",
    "ammo_capacity": "200",
    "damage": "Ball: 30 Split: 72 (6x12)",
    "fire_rate": "0.40",
    "reload_time": "1.2",
    "shot_speed": "23",
    "range": "60",
    "force": "30",
    "spread": "0",
    "class": "SHOTGUN",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Fires a single, large, slow moving projectile with a 5 tile range."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "After hitting a wall or reaching the end of its exceptionally short range, this ball will split apart into 12 smaller, faster projectiles.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The angle that the smaller shards fly at depends on how the initial projectile was destroyed. If the ball reached the end of its range, they will travel along the same trajectory. If the ball impacted a wall, the shards will be propelled away from the wall surface."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The ball will not split upon hitting an enemy or obstacle (such as "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Tables",
                  "kind": "unresolved"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": ")."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "item_interactions": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Most "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Bullet Modifiers",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " only affect the initial ball fired by the Mass Shotgun, and have no effect on its pellets."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Flak Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - No effect on the initial ball. The smaller pellets created by the ball will "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "further",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " split into even more, even smaller shrapnel upon hitting an obstacle or reaching the end of their range.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Additionally, if Flak Bullets is held, "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Bullet Modifiers",
                  "kind": "unresolved"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " and other items can now affect the pellets fired from the initial shot."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Mass Shotgun is best used at a medium range, where the initial projectile will split close enough to the target to maximise the amount of pellets that hit. Hitting enemies with the inital bullet does considerably less damage."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This gun is a reference to collapsible weapons in the "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Mass Effect",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " franchise. While there is not an exact weapon in the series that the Mass Shotgun is based on, it is somewhat similar in function to the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Geth Plasma Shotgun",
              "url": "https://masseffect.fandom.com/wiki/Geth_Plasma_Shotgun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", which shoots 3 plasma pellets when uncharged and 1 plasma slug when charged.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "In "
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Mass Effect",
                  "style": "i"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": ", the "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ext",
                  "v": "Geth",
                  "url": "https://masseffect.fandom.com/wiki/Geth"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " are a race of androids. This may be why the Mass Shotgun is a part of the  "
                },
                {
                  "t": "synref",
                  "v": "To Serve Android"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " synergy."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Ammonomicon",
                  "kind": "lore"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " quote "
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "\"My Favorite Gun\"",
                  "style": "i"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " is a reference to a side-quest in Mass Effect 2, where the player can choose to sponsor a store by saying "
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "\"I'm Commander Shepard, and this is my favorite store on the Citadel.\"",
                  "style": "i"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The name of the   "
                },
                {
                  "t": "synref",
                  "v": "Massive Effect"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " synergy is also a reference to this franchise."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Mass Shotgun and the  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Mine Cutter",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " synergising for  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Mass Cutter"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " is likely based on the fact that "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Mass Effect",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " and "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Dead Space",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " are both published by Electronic Arts."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The entry for the Mass Shotgun in the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Physical Ammonomicon",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " has a small doodle of "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Sara Ryder",
              "url": "https://masseffect.fandom.com/wiki/Sara_Ryder"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " from "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Mass Effect: Andromeda",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Shotgun Full of Hate",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/b/b1/Shotgun_Full_of_Hate.png",
    "notes": "Shoots a shotgun burst of skulls, nails, regular bullets, and poison bullets that leave pools of poison goop.",
    "quote": "Hate Is Power!",
    "quality": "A",
    "type": "Semiautomatic",
    "dps": "54.5",
    "magazine_size": "8",
    "ammo_capacity": "150",
    "damage": "6x4 (bullets) + 5 (skull) + 3 (nail)",
    "fire_rate": "0.45",
    "reload_time": "1.2",
    "shot_speed": "23",
    "range": "60",
    "force": "30",
    "spread": "14",
    "class": "SHOTGUN",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Fires a spread of 6 disparate bullets with different effects.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "2 regular bullets with lower range than the other projectiles."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "2 poison bullets that create pools of "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Status Effects",
                  "kind": "lore"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Goop",
                  "kind": "lore"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " on impact. As poison is a non-flammable liquid, these bullets are capable of extinguishing fused "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Chests",
                  "kind": "lore"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " and the "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Fireplace",
                  "kind": "unresolved"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "A piercing nail."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "A fast moving bouncing skull."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Shotgun Full of Hate being in the SHOTGUN gun class makes it inherently less common than its counterpart, the Shotgun Full of Love which exists in the CHARM class.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "This is due to the SHOTGUN class being a more common class, meaning more guns exist where possessing them will make the Shotgun Full of Hate less common."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Love/Hate"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "'s name is based off having a \"Love/Hate relationship\" with something, a common name for appreciating one's strengths but also disliking the flaws heavily."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The entry for the Shotgun Full of Hate in the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Physical Ammonomicon",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " has a small doodle of an angry skull and nail. This mirrors the entry doodle of the  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Shotgun Full of Love",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
