            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "This is due to the CHARM class being a less common class, meaning fewer guns exist where possessing them will make the Shotgun Full of Love less common."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " Fixed Bug Prior to version "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "V1.0.9",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " the Shotgun Full of Love consumed 2 ammo per shot."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The entry for the Shotgun Full of Love in the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Physical Ammonomicon",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " has a small doodle of a happy heart and star. This mirrors the entry doodle of the  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Shotgun Full of Hate",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Shotgrub",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/e/eb/Shotgrub.png",
    "notes": "Fires a spread of 5 bullets that leave small pools of poison goop.",
    "quote": "No Worries!",
    "quality": "C",
    "type": "Semiautomatic",
    "dps": "46.5",
    "magazine_size": "8",
    "ammo_capacity": "250",
    "damage": "25 (5x5)",
    "fire_rate": "0.9",
    "reload_time": "1.5",
    "shot_speed": "23",
    "range": "60",
    "force": "30",
    "spread": "0",
    "class": "POISON",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Contrail"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If the player has "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Alien Engine",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", its flame turns green, igniting enemies with  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Status Effects",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " (Dur: 120s DPS: 4). Alien Engine also grants flight while held."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Just Like The Real Thing"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If the player has "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Sixth Chamber",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Yellow Chamber",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Holey Grail",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", or "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Bullet Idol",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", Shotgrub's bullets will act like those of the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Shotgrub (Enemy)",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", no longer causing poison, firing in a static spread, but gaining penetration and splitting into wavy bullets upon hitting a wall or enemy."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Monster Grub"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If the player also has "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Monster Blood",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", Shotgrub's bullets will home in on enemies."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Despite firing like a shotgun, the Shotgrub is not part of the SHOTGUN "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Guns",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", and as such does not benefit from the  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Shotgun Affinity"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " synergy."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "In September of 2016, "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Dodge Roll",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " programmer "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Brent Sodman",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " listed the  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Alien Engine",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " as his favourite gun in "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Enter the Gungeon",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", and  Shotgrub as his least favourite. He did however disclaim that his opinions on "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Enter the Gungeons",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " weapons change often, so these preferences may have changed over time and with the addition of more weapons."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "trivia": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "\"No Worries\" is a reference to the song Hakuna Matata, which is sung by Timon and Pumba from the movie "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "The Lion King",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Lion_King"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", who are notorious for eating grubs."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Shotgrub is very similar to Slim's Leech gun from Evolve, which is fed grubs and has the same projectile colour."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Gilded Hydra",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/1/13/Gilded_Hydra.png",
    "notes": "Fires a large burst of piercing, bouncing bullets. Clip size is increased by 1 for each half heart the player is missing, and healing decreases clip size.",
    "quote": "Heads Up!",
    "quality": "1S",
    "type": "Semiautomatic",
    "dps": "30.0-83.3",
    "magazine_size": "1+",
    "ammo_capacity": "50",
    "damage": "60 (7.5x8)",
    "fire_rate": "0.40",
    "reload_time": "2.0",
    "shot_speed": "23",
    "range": "15",
    "force": "30",
    "spread": "0",
    "class": "SHOTGUN",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Ecstasy of Gold"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If the player also has "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Gilded Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", Gilded Hydra's damage is increased by 25%."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Gilded Hydra is part of the SHOTGUN "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Guns",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", and as such benefits from the  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Shotgun Affinity"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " synergy."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Magazine size will not increase when playing as "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "The Robot",
              "kind": "character"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Gilded Hydra always starts with a magazine size of 1, regardless of health missing when it is picked up. It will increase to the correct size upon healing or taking damage."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Dropping the gun will reset the magazine size."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The gun's bullet spread is always symmetrical, though extra bullets due to passives such as "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Shadow Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " do not necessarily share the symmetry.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The gun is still affected by accuracy increasing items, which simply cause the spread to narrow symmetrically."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "trivia": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The decreasing health adding to the clip size is an allusion to the Lernaean Hydra of Greek mythology, a beast that would sprout two heads in the place of one that was severed."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The description is a reference to Revelation 2:1 in the Bible which says \"these are the words of him who holds the seven stars in his right hand and walks among the seven golden lampstands.\""
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Synergy  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Ecstasy of Gold"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " is a reference to Ennio Morricone's song \"The Ecstasy of Gold\" from the Western film \"The Good, the Bad, and the Ugly.\""
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
