  {
    "name": "The Membrane",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/1/19/The_Membrane.png",
    "notes": "Fires a shotgun blast of bouncing green bullets that split into more bouncing green bullets.",
    "quote": "Green Or Yellow?",
    "quality": "C",
    "type": "Semiautomatic",
    "dps": "38.9",
    "magazine_size": "6",
    "ammo_capacity": "120",
    "damage": "Before split: 24 (4x6) After split: 36 (3x12)",
    "fire_rate": "0.45",
    "reload_time": "1.2",
    "shot_speed": "22",
    "range": "30",
    "force": "6",
    "spread": "8",
    "class": "SHOTGUN",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Absent Minded"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " synergy is a reference to the movie The Absent-Minded Professor, which features an extremely bouncy material known as Flubber. It is also possibly a reference to the television show Invader Zim, which has a character named Professor Membrane."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Due to its overpenetration, high range, and high projectile count, the Membrane works extremely well with  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Flak Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " and  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Scattershot",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ".\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "This works even better with the synergy due to homing."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Membrane is a part of the SHOTGUN "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Guns",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", and as such benefits from the  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Shotgun Affinity"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " synergy."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The bullets after the split will not be connected by  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Shock Rounds",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Membrane's split shots will immediately hit the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Ammoconda",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " once the main shots hit it, allowing the player to do great amounts of damage."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Huntsman",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/7/75/Huntsman.png",
    "notes": "Fires a shotgun blast of bullets. Reloading destroys nearby bullets. Increases curse by 1.",
    "quote": "Axes Of Evil",
    "quality": "C",
    "type": "Semiautomatic",
    "dps": "28.3",
    "magazine_size": "6",
    "ammo_capacity": "150",
    "damage": "21 (3.5x6)",
    "fire_rate": "0.65",
    "reload_time": "1.2",
    "shot_speed": "23",
    "range": "15",
    "force": "10",
    "spread": "10",
    "class": "FULLAUTO",
    "curse": 1.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Peculiarly, the Huntsman is a part of the FULLAUTO "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Guns",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " despite not being remotely fully automatic.  This is probably to classify it with other weapons that delete bullets on reload, such as "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Excaliber",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " and "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Fightsabre",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ".\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Because the Huntsman is not SHOTGUN type despite being a shotgun, it does not benefit from the  "
                },
                {
                  "t": "synref",
                  "v": "Shotgun Affinity"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " synergy."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "trivia": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The fact that the weapon increases "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Curse",
              "kind": "stat"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " while being carried stems from the Gungeon rejecting non-bullet based weapons."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Executioner",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " wield this weapon."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Huntsman appears to be a "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Regular Shotgun",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " with an axe blade attached to the underside of the barrel. Statistically, The Huntsman is weaker overall, with a slightly worse magazine size, damage, and fire rate."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Huntsman is a reference to the game Bloodborne where there is a transforming weapon called \"Hunter Axe\". This is further supported by the fact that the Huntsman has a synergy with the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Trick Gun",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " (another item with multiple Bloodborne references) called insight,  the key item in Bloodborne that allows hunters to perceive the \"Great Ones\" who are the primary antagonists of the game."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": []
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The tagline \"Axes Of Evil\" is a play on words in reference to a speech by George W. Bush where he referred to foreign governments allegedly aiding terrorists as belonging to an "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Axis of Evil.",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": []
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": []
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "The Red Hood"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " synergy is an allusion to the fairy tale \"Little Red Riding Hood,\" where a young girl who has never been taught not to talk to strangers is eaten by a wolf and is rescued by a lumberjack (or a hunter in some versions)."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
