  },
  {
    "name": "Klobbe",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/f/fd/Klobbe.png",
    "notes": "Rapidly fires low-damage bullets.",
    "quote": "Everyone's Favorite",
    "quality": "D",
    "type": "Automatic",
    "dps": "11.9",
    "magazine_size": "32",
    "ammo_capacity": "900",
    "damage": "1.2",
    "fire_rate": "0.04",
    "reload_time": "2.0",
    "shot_speed": "14",
    "range": "1,000",
    "force": "1",
    "spread": "20",
    "class": "FULLAUTO",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "item_interactions": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Cog of Battle",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - After succeeding an active reload, the Klobbes damage and knockback are multiplied by 10, and the gun gains perfect accuracy for a portion of the next magazine. The amount of the next magazine affected by the bonus depends on how many bullets were reloaded using the active reload. Active reloading a fully empty magazine gives the entirety of the next magazine the bonus.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "This effect persists when the player switches away from, and back to the Klobbe."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This gun is among those "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Gunsling King and Manservantes",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " can challenge the player to clear a room with."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This gun is a reference to the Klobb from "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "GoldenEye 007",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/GoldenEye_007_(1997_video_game)"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " (itself based on the real-life "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Škorpion",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/%C5%A0korpion"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "), a notoriously bad gun with similar weaknesses as the Klobbe."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Klobbering Time"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " synergy is a reference to Fantastic Four member The Thing, whose catchphrase is \"It's clobbering time\"."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "No Odd Job"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " synergy is a reference to the split-screen multiplayer mode in "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "GoldenEye 007",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/GoldenEye_007_(1997_video_game)"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", in which the playable character \"Oddjob\" was often house-ruled to be banned because he was too hard to aim at due to his small size, and considered overpowered."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Klobbe has unused sprites relating to a unique fire animation that would only play when the gun was fired by an enemy (The "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Magnum",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " and "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Regular Shotgun",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " both also have similar 'enemy shoot' animations), despite the fact that the regular Klobbe is never held or used by an enemy in the final game.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "It's possible that the base Klobbe may have been intended to be held by "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Gummy",
                  "kind": "unresolved"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": ", but was eventually replaced with the "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Mummified Gun?action=edit&redlink=1",
                  "kind": "unresolved"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " (an alternate version of the Klobbe)."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The entry for the Klobbe in the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Physical Ammonomicon",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " has a small doodle of "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Boris Grishenko",
              "url": "https://goldeneye.fandom.com/wiki/Boris_Grishenko"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " from "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "GoldenEye 007",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " with the weapon."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Machine Pistol",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/6/63/Machine_Pistol.png",
    "notes": "",
    "quote": "Rapid Fire",
    "quality": "D",
    "type": "Automatic",
    "dps": "29.7",
    "magazine_size": "30",
    "ammo_capacity": "600",
    "damage": "3.2",
    "fire_rate": "0.07",
    "reload_time": "1.2",
    "shot_speed": "23",
    "range": "16",
    "force": "6",
    "spread": "10",
    "class": "FULLAUTO",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This gun resembles a "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Mini Uzi",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Uzi#Military_variants"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", a compact, blowback-operated machine pistol developed in 1980, chambered in 9x19mm Parabellum."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This gun is used by "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Bandana Bullet Kin",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", and is one of the six guns wielded by the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Beholster",
              "kind": "shrine"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ".\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "As it is held by the Beholster, it can be placed on the "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Shrines",
                  "kind": "lore"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "According to "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Dodge Roll",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " artist "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Joe Harty",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", the machine pistol sprite has remained unchanged since the 2014 builds of "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Enter the Gungeon",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "- to his apparent dissatisfaction."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The entry for the Machine Pistol in the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Physical Ammonomicon",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " has a small doodle of what appears to be the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "The Convict",
              "kind": "character"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " holding the weapon."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Thompson Sub-Machinegun",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/6/62/Thompson_Sub-Machinegun.png",
    "notes": "",
    "quote": "Myeah, See!",
    "quality": "C",
    "type": "Automatic",
    "dps": "40.8",
    "magazine_size": "30",
    "ammo_capacity": "350",
    "damage": "5",
    "fire_rate": "0.10",
    "reload_time": "0.78",
    "shot_speed": "23",
    "range": "1,000",
    "force": "9",
    "spread": "10",
    "class": "FULLAUTO",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " The Thompson Sub-Machinegun is wielded by "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Hollowpoint",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "\"Myeah, See!\" references a line spoken by Edward G. Robinson's gangster character in the 1931 film "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Little Caesar",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This gun is used in "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "The Convict",
              "kind": "character"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " past."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Future Gangster"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " synergy may be a reference to the Laser RCW, a weapon from "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Fallout: New Vegas,",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " which resembles a Thompson SMG but is a rapid-fire laser assault rifle."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Thompson Sub-Machinegun does not appear in "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Exit the Gungeon",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", however it still exists in the assets and text string database of the game. Like all real-world guns in Exit the Gungeon, the unused Thompson Sub-Machinegun has a different name in the "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Apple Arcade",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " string database, where it is called the Gungeon Typewriter."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The entry for the Thompson Sub-Machinegun in the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Physical Ammonomicon",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " has a small doodle of a detailed "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Bullet Kin",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " dressed as a mafioso wielding the weapon."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "AK-47",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/f/f8/AK-47.png",
    "notes": "",
    "quote": "Accept No Substitutes",
    "quality": "B",
    "type": "Automatic",
    "dps": "44.7",
    "magazine_size": "30",
    "ammo_capacity": "500",
    "damage": "5.5",
    "fire_rate": "0.11",
    "reload_time": "0.6",
    "shot_speed": "23",
    "range": "1,000",
    "force": "9",
    "spread": "4",
    "class": "FULLAUTO",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The AK-47 is wielded by "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Bullet Kin",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Tanker",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", and "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Hollowpoint",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " If the player feeds the AK-47 and either the  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Flame Hand",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " or  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Megahand",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " to a regular "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Muncher",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", it will always spit out a  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Machine Fist",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The description of the AK-47 is a reference to the film Jackie Brown."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The AK-47 that the player uses in the tutorial has less ammo than the one that can be found in runs, having 350 instead of 500."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This is the gun that the developers use to test bosses as they're making/tweaking them, due to the balance of ammo to damage."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "AK-47 (Island Forme)"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " is a reference to the games Pokémon Sun and Moon, in which Pokémon had different sub-species or \"Formes\" adapted to an island setting."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "The Killing Joke"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " is a reference to "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "“The Killing Joke”",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Batman:_The_Killing_Joke"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", a graphic novel by Alan Moore."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The name 'AP-13' in the Apple Arcade version of Exit the Gungeon may be a vague "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "leet",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Leet"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " translation of the word 'apple'."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Strafe Gun",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/b/be/Strafe_Gun.png",
    "notes": "Fires nails that explode upon releasing the trigger.",
    "quote": "Bleeding Edge Gameplay",
    "quality": "1S",
    "type": "Automatic",
    "dps": "46.5",
    "magazine_size": "20",
    "ammo_capacity": "400",
    "damage": "Impact: 1 Explosion: 8",
    "fire_rate": "0.13",
    "reload_time": "1.4",
    "shot_speed": "500",
    "range": "?",
    "force": "?",
    "spread": "?",
    "class": "FULLAUTO",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Rapidly fires extremely fast moving nails that stick into walls and enemies.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Nails that stick into enemies will trigger a cosmetic "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Status Effects",
                  "kind": "lore"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " effect, with the enemy gushing blood onto the ground."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Nails will explode after a short time, or all at once when the trigger is released."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "item_interactions": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Metronome",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - Killing an enemy with explosive damage from the nails of the Strafe Gun will "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "not",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " increase the bonus of the metronome. Only direct damage from the nail impact counts."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Nails from this gun cannot be caught by "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Gunjurer",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Emptying an entire magazine into a boss all at once is inadvisable, as the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Bosses",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " will severely limit the damage potential of a large number of nails exploding simultaneously. Firing in brief bursts can circumvent this issue by spreading the explosion damage out over several seconds."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This gun is a reference to the game "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Strafe",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Strafe_(video_game)"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", specifically to the nail gun upgrade for the machine gun. The gun's tagline and bleed effect are a reference to the game being described as featuring \"bleeding edge gameplay\"."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The synergy  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "In The Mood!"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " is a reference to the DOOM movement technique "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "straferunning",
              "url": "https://doomwiki.org/wiki/Straferunning"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", in which a player moves both forward and sideways to achieve higher speeds."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The entry for the Strafe Gun in the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Physical Ammonomicon",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " has a small doodle of a "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Glutton",
              "url": "https://strafe-archive.fandom.com/wiki/Glutton"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " enemy from "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Strafe",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "AKEY-47",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/8/80/AKEY-47.png",
    "notes": "Opening a locked chest or door with the gun equipped opens it for free. Alternatively, shooting a locked chest or door unlocks it.",
    "quote": "Unlocked And Loaded!",
    "quality": "1S",
    "type": "Automatic",
    "dps": "44.7",
    "magazine_size": "30",
    "ammo_capacity": "500",
    "damage": "5.5",
    "fire_rate": "0.11",
    "reload_time": "0.6",
    "shot_speed": "23",
    "range": "1,000",
    "force": "9",
    "spread": "4",
    "class": "SILLY",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The AKEY-47 Has identical statistics to the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "AK-47",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Once unlocked, the AKEY-47 may appear for sale in "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Flynt",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " shop for 3 "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Keys",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Its bullets cannot open the padlocks on the trapdoor to the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Oubliette",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " and the tunnel to the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Resourceful Rat's Lair",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "; however, they can be opened by hand for free with the AKEY-47 equipped.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "However, AKEY-47 cannot be used in place of the "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Gnawed Key",
                  "kind": "unresolved"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " to open the lock on the hatch that drops down to the "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Resourceful Rat's Lair",
                  "kind": "lore"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": ", and as of "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "V2.0.6",
                  "kind": "unresolved"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": ", cannot open the doors and chests that require special keys dropped by Resourceful Rat."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "If a chest lock has been broken by the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Trusty Lockpicks",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", shooting it with the AKEY-47 will not open it.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Door locks that have been broken by the "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Trusty Lockpicks",
                  "kind": "item"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " can still be opened with AKEY-47."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Shooting a chest with AKEY-47 can still break it, if it has already been damaged and is close to breaking.  For this reason it is always better to open a chest with the gun equipped instead of shooting it."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The inscription \"Ex Archa, Libertas\" is a reference to the Latin phrase \"Ex gladio libertas\", or 'From the sword, freedom', with 'Archa', the word for 'Chest', replacing 'gladio', the word for sword."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The synergy Akey Breaky is probably a reference to the song "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Achy Breaky Heart",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Achy_Breaky_Heart"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " popularized by Billy Ray Cyrus."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "While the AKEY-47 does not appear in "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Exit the Gungeon",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", its sprites and description are present in the games assets."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Stone Dome",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/d/d8/Stone_Dome.png",
    "notes": "Sits on the player's head and rapidly fires homing bullets. While held, inflicts fear on nearby enemies. Increases curse by 1.",
    "quote": "Big Head Mode",
    "quality": "B",
    "type": "Automatic",
    "dps": "26.5",
    "magazine_size": "750",
    "ammo_capacity": "750",
    "damage": "4.5",
    "fire_rate": "0.20",
    "reload_time": "2.0",
    "shot_speed": "25",
    "range": "1,000",
    "force": "10",
    "spread": "8",
    "class": "FULLAUTO",
    "curse": 1.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Rapidly fires homing projectiles."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "While held, any non-boss enemies within 90° of the angle the player is aiming will become "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Status Effects",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", fleeing the player.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "This effect works over any distance, however enemies will only start to flee the player after coming within a 6 tile range."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Increases  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Curse",
              "kind": "stat"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " by 1 while in the inventory."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Sits visually over the players head."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The fear status effect can compel enemies to walk backwards into hazards such as dangerous "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Goop",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " or "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Pits",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " Bug Switching to another gun causes currently afraid enemies to be "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "permanently",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " afraid. These enemies will always flee the player after coming within a 6 tile range, regardless of the direction the player is aiming. This persists forever, or until the player switches back to the Stone Dome."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This gun is likely a reference to the 1974 sci-fi movie "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Zardoz",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Zardoz"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", where a giant flying stone head named Zardoz serves as the evil god of a primitive caste of humans. Zardoz provides these humans with guns and ammunition, vomited forth from his great stone mouth."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Ammonomicon",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " quote "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "\"Big Head Mode\"",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " is a reference to the classic '"
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Big Head Mode",
              "url": "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BigHeadMode"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "' cheat code, which appeared in many early video games and typically inflated characters heads to ridiculous sizes."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The only other gun which utilises the fear "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Status effect",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " is the  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "JK-47",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The material mentioned in this gun's "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Ammonomicon",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " entry, 'cranium', is a joke. 'Cranium' is another name for the skull."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This gun plays a unique rolling animation whenever the player "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Dodge Roll (Move)",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The gun used to be called \"Giant Stone Head\" with the pickup quote \"Headshot\"."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The entry for the Stone Dome in the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Physical Ammonomicon",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " has a small doodle of the weapon."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Crown of Guns",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/d/dc/Crown_of_Guns.png",
    "notes": "Sits atop the player's head and spreads bullets in all directions.",
    "quote": "All Hail",
    "quality": "C",
    "type": "Automatic",
    "dps": "220.0",
    "magazine_size": "3000",
    "ammo_capacity": "3000",
    "damage": "5.5",
    "fire_rate": "0.04",
    "reload_time": "2.0",
    "shot_speed": "?",
    "range": "40",
    "force": "9",
    "spread": "360",
    "class": "SILLY",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Fires rapidly in all directions simultaneously.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " Consumes 3 ammo and fires 3 bullets per shot."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Bullets slightly home towards enemies."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "item_interactions": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Items that reduce "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Accuracy",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " will reduce the 360° spread of the Crown of Guns just like any other weapon, narrowing the spread towards the player's aim direction the more are acquired."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Remote Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - All bullets will be redirected towards the player's cursor/in the player's aim direction, allowing the player to easily consolidate their dps onto a single target."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Backup Gun",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - As the Crown of Guns has 360° spread, shooting backwards is functionally identical to shooting forwards. This makes Backup Gun a x2 increase to bullets fired and by extension potential dps."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Singularity",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " /  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Black Hole Gun",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - Active black holes will suck all bullets from the Crown of Guns towards them, potentially resulting in extremely high dps to enemies trapped within the black hole or bosses in between the hole and the player."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Shock Rounds",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - The wide spread of bullets fired by Crown of Guns makes the electric arcs of Shock Rounds extremely potent."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Eyepatch",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If no "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Accuracy",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " reducing items have been acquired, Eyepatch will have functionally no effect on the Crown of Gun's accuracy."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Duct Tape",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - Taping Crown of Guns onto another gun will attach it in the form of three separate modules in the hud. In addition, it will still consume 3 ammo when fired, in addition to the host gun's ammo cost."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This gun is likely a reference to the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Crown of Guns",
              "url": "https://nuclear-throne.fandom.com/wiki/Crowns"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " in "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Nuclear Throne",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", a passive companion that increases the amount of gun drops in levels.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The name of the  "
                },
                {
                  "t": "synref",
                  "v": "Blast Crown"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " synergy is also a reference to a crown in "
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Nuclear Throne",
                  "style": "i"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "It may also be a reference to the eponymous crown in the book "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ext",
                  "v": "A Crown of Swords",
                  "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/A_Crown_of_Swords"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": ", seventh book in the "
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Wheel of Time",
                  "style": "i"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " series."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The synergy  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Two Heavy"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " is a reference to the quote "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "\"Heavy is The Head That Wears The Crown\"",
              "url": "https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/uneasy_lies_the_head_that_wears_a_crown"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " from Shakespeare's "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "King Henry IV",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Crown of Guns has the highest non-infinite maximum ammo out of any gun in "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Enter the Gungeon",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Alas, Sniperion"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " is a reference to "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Sniperion",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", one of the moons of Gunymede."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The entry for the Crown of Guns in the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Physical Ammonomicon",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " has a small doodle of the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Chancellor",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "M16",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/e/ea/M16.png",
    "notes": "Reloading alternates between bursts of 3 bullets and burst grenade launcher.",
    "quote": "Underslung",
    "quality": "A",
    "type": "Burst",
    "dps": "35.6",
    "magazine_size": "30 (machine gun) 3 (grenade launcher)",
    "ammo_capacity": "500",
    "damage": "Gun: 5.5 Grenade: 10 (impact) + 25 (explosion)",
    "fire_rate": "0.10",
    "reload_time": "1.2",
    "shot_speed": "23",
    "range": "1,000",
    "force": "11",
    "spread": "7",
    "class": "FULLAUTO",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Reloading the M16 alternates between a burst-fire mode which shoots a burst of three bullets with every trigger pull, and a grenade launcher mode which lobs explosive projectiles.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " Grenades are affected by gravity, falling quickly towards the bottom of the screen."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Grenades consume 1 ammo each, the exact same as a regular bullet. As such, reloading immediately when in machine gun mode allows the gun to spend most of its time in grenade launcher mode at no additional ammo cost. This can be desirable for an increased dps, and the ability to hit multiple enemies at once with each explosion."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Allowing the M16 to reload passively by switching to another weapon for a few seconds does not switch the gun's form."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "An old, unused appearance for the M16 exists within Enter the Gungeons assets.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Tanker",
                  "kind": "lore"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " that periodically pops up out of the "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Treadnaught",
                  "kind": "unresolved"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " uses what appears to be this old unused form of the M16 to shoot bullets at the player."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " Bug Immediately switching weapons after initiating a reload while holding the M16 results in the sounds for firing normally and firing grenades being swapped."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The entry for the M16 in the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Physical Ammonomicon",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " has a small doodle of a "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Pinhead",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Combined Rifle",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/2/2b/Combined_Rifle.png",
    "notes": "Reloading alternates between a rapid-fire rifle and a bouncing, piercing, destructive energy ball that consumes 10 ammo per shot.",
    "quote": "Halve Lives",
    "quality": "B",
    "type": "Automatic",
    "dps": "36.6",
    "magazine_size": "30 (gun) 1 (ball)",
    "ammo_capacity": "500",
    "damage": "5 (gun) 100 (ball)",
    "fire_rate": "0.12",
    "reload_time": "1.0",
    "shot_speed": "23 (Rifle) 19 (Energy Ball)",
    "range": "50 (Rifle) 150 (Energy Ball)",
    "force": "9 (Rifle) 2.5 (Energy Ball)",
    "spread": "7 (Rifle) 0 (Energy Ball)",
    "class": "FULLAUTO",
