  {
    "name": "The Fat Line",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/3/39/The_Fat_Line.png",
    "notes": "Fires purple bullets, which start at the wall the gun is aimed at and travel back towards the gun. Bullets will curve and home in on enemies as they travel.",
    "quote": "Technobabble",
    "quality": "B",
    "type": "Automatic",
    "dps": "38.4",
    "magazine_size": "100",
    "ammo_capacity": "500",
    "damage": "4",
    "fire_rate": "0.075",
    "reload_time": "3.0",
    "shot_speed": "?",
    "range": "?",
    "force": "0",
    "spread": "?",
    "class": "FULLAUTO",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Fires purple particles, which start at the furthest wall in the direction that the gun is aimed, and travel back towards the gun. These particles will travel through walls to reach the player.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "These projectiles are spread out in the same way as regular bullets, but in reverse. Just like how a regular guns spread increases with distance, The Fat Line's spread increases with the players distance from the target wall."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "These bullets travel to where the barrel of The Fat Line "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "was",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " when they were fired. Moving with the gun while the particle is in-flight will not update its trajectory."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Bullets will curve and home in on enemies as they travel."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "item_interactions": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Orbital Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - As bullets from The Fat Line rarely collide with walls, Orbital Bullets is largely useless. Despite this, it "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "is",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " still possible for shots from The Fat Line to orbit if they hit an obstacle they cannot pierce through, such as the pillars in the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Treadnaught",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " boss-room."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Backup Gun",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - Interacts as expected, with a secondary group of particles moving towards the gun from behind the player."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Remote Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - Affects effectiveness very negatively, as bullets coming from the walls will quickly curve back into the wall no matter where the player aims, making the ability to hit enemies near impossible."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Does not reveal "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Secret Rooms",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " Fixed Bug In early versions of the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "AG&D",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " Update, this gun could appear in "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Sorceress",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "- despite not being finished or officially released."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "In hypothetical physics, "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Tachyons",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tachyon"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " are particles which always travel faster than the speed of light, allowing them to travel backwards in time. The existence of such particles would violate the known laws of physics, and no examples of this behaviour have ever been observed."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This gun is a reference to the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Fatline",
              "url": "https://hyperioncantos.fandom.com/wiki/Fatline"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", a faster-than-light communications system used by the Hegemony of Man in the Dan Simmons novel "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Hyperion",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ". This communications system functioned by the use of tachyons."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Mr. Accretion Jr.",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/e/ee/Mr._Accretion_Jr..png",
    "notes": "Fires planets which start orbiting the player if they hit a wall or obstacle.",
    "quote": "Music of the Spheres",
    "quality": "B",
    "type": "Semiautomatic",
    "dps": "21.9",
    "magazine_size": "20",
    "ammo_capacity": "100",
    "damage": "Varies",
    "fire_rate": "0.7",
    "reload_time": "2.0",
    "shot_speed": "19",
    "range": "1,000",
    "force": "?",
    "spread": "0",
    "class": "SILLY",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Mr. Accretion Jr. fires planets that resemble the 8 planets of the solar system. Each planet has different effects, and will start orbiting the player upon hitting a wall or obstacle."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "item_interactions": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Black Hole Gun",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " +  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Outer Limits"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - Firing three planets into black holes created by the Black Hole Gun will also trigger the effect of the synergy."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Firing or reloading Mr. Accretion Jr.  releases a cloud of gas with a space texture. This effect is purely visual.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "If the player attempts to reload when the gun is already full, it will still release this gas."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "This gas is very similar to that released by the time rip that unlocks "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "The Paradox",
                  "kind": "character"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The name "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Mr. Accretion Jr.",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " is a reference to "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Accretion",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Accretion_(astrophysics)"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", the process that forms planets out of stellar dust. It is also a reference to the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Scooty-Puff Jr.",
              "url": "https://futurama.fandom.com/wiki/Scooty-Puff,_Jr."
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", a comically ineffective vehicle resembling a childrens toy that appears in the "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Futurama",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " episode "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Why Of Fry",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Ammonomicon",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " quote "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "\"Music of the Spheres\"",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " is a reference to "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Musica Universalis",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Musica_universalis"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " (also known as "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Music of the Spheres",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "), a long-standing ancient mathematical concept which relates the rotation of the heavenly bodies to various mathematical proportions, as well as the pitch of a string to its size. The phrase, and concept, was popularized in philosophy by Pythagoras, and later Plato."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The line "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "\"Due to a trick in perspective, these two-dimensional planets appear spherical.\"",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " in this guns "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Ammonomicon",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " description is a reference to "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "flat earth theory",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Flat_Earth"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", an archaic belief in the world being flat instead of round. It is also a reference to the fact that all sprites in "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Enter the Gungeon",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " are literally two-dimensional, but exploit perspective and shading to appear three-dimensional."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "In the real world, an "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Orrery",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Orrery"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " is a mechanical model of the Solar System that illustrates the relative positions of the planets and their moons.  The  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Orrery"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " synergy likely uses this name due to the resemblance the player has to an orrery when surrounded by orbiting planets, each of which is being orbited by its own bullet-moon."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "VertebraeK-47",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/8/84/VertebraeK-47.png",
    "notes": "Bullets close to each other will form links between each other, which hurts enemies on touch.",
    "quote": "Nervous Yet?",
    "quality": "B",
    "type": "Automatic",
    "dps": "27.3",
    "magazine_size": "30",
    "ammo_capacity": "250",
    "damage": "4 (bullet) 2 (chain)",
    "fire_rate": "0.10",
    "reload_time": "1.5",
    "shot_speed": "18",
    "range": "1,000",
    "force": "6",
    "spread": "5",
    "class": "FULLAUTO",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Rapidly fires homing ghost-shaped bullets that can pierce once."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "When close together, these bullets form chain links between each other that damage enemies.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " Each chain deals 2 damage to enemies it overlaps. Enemies hurt by a chain have a 1 second cooldown before they can be harmed by the same chain again."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The weapon's name is a portmanteau of 'vertebrae' and '"
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "AK-47",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "'. Vertebrae are bones which a spine consists of, and the AK-47 is an assault rifle."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The description of the gun is a reference to the Jake Clover game, "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Nuign Spectre",
              "url": "https://gamejolt.com/games/nuign-specter/10175"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The freezing aspect of the  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Jolly Roger"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " synergy may be a reference to the skeleton "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Brook",
              "url": "https://onepiece.fandom.com/wiki/Brook"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " from "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "One Piece",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", who freezes his opponents."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The entry for the VertebraeK-47 in the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Physical Ammonomicon",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " has a small doodle of a ghost."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Balloon Gun",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/6/69/Balloon_Gun.png",
    "notes": "Fires small homing tornadoes. While held, grants flight but loses all ammo on taking damage.",
    "quote": "Hot Air",
    "quality": "C",
    "type": "Automatic",
    "dps": "44.1",
    "magazine_size": "10",
    "ammo_capacity": "250",
    "damage": "12",
    "fire_rate": "0.25",
    "reload_time": "1.6",
    "shot_speed": "?",
    "range": "?",
    "force": "?",
    "spread": "?",
    "class": "FULLAUTO",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "item_interactions": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Helix Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - Vortexes fired by the Balloon gun will never lose their momentum."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Full Metal Jacket",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - Damage that is prevented by the Full Metal Jacket will not pop the Balloon Gun."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Rocket-Powered Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - Increases the effective range of the Balloon Gun by increasing the initial velocity of its vortexes."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Angry Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - The slow movement speed and homing of the Balloon Gun's projectiles allows them to rebound repeatedly around the same group of enemies indefinitely, with low risk of missing."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Holey Grail",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If Holey Grail was picked up "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "after",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " the Balloon Gun, it will restore part of the Balloon Guns ammo after the player takes damage, effectively preventing it from popping.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "This effect "
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "does not work",
                  "style": "i"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " if the Holey Grail was picked up first, however this order can be easily rectified by dropping the Holey Grail and picking it up again."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Balloon gun will still pop if the player takes damage to "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Armor",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " If the Balloon Gun loses its ammo due to taking damage, it will be rendered invisible, having no sprite until ammo is restored. Running out of ammo in the regular fashion does not 'pop' the balloon gun or alter its sprite.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "If the Balloon Gun is dropped while 'popped', it can be very difficult to retrieve due to being completely invisible. It is not, however, impossible to recollect the weapon."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "If the Balloon Gun is thrown while 'popped', it will completely disappear, and cannot be retrieved. The "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Resourceful Rat",
                  "kind": "lore"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " can still steal the weapon in this state, however."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The Balloon Gun can be sold to the "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Sell Creep",
                  "kind": "lore"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": ", given to a "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Muncher",
                  "kind": "unresolved"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": ", or "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Duct Tape",
                  "kind": "item"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " while popped."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The Balloon Gun does not appear in the death or win pages of the Ammonomicon if it is popped."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Balloon Gun is a reference to the art of "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "balloon twisting",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", which involves bending and twisting long cylindrical balloons into recognisable shapes. The most well known form of balloon twisting is balloon animals, however imitations of weapons such as swords and guns made out of balloons are also popular."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Ammonomicon quote "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "\"Hot Air\"",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " is a reference to "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "hot air baloons",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hot_air_balloon"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", which are also used for flight."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The entry for the Balloon Gun in the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Physical Ammonomicon",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " has a small doodle of a whirlwind."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "MAC10",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/6/62/MAC10.png",
    "notes": "Fires 4-round bursts with no delay.",
    "quote": "$#!^@ Never End",
    "quality": "C",
    "type": "Burst",
    "dps": "34.7",
    "magazine_size": "30",
    "ammo_capacity": "600",
    "damage": "3.5",
    "fire_rate": "0.07",
    "reload_time": "1.0",
    "shot_speed": "23",
    "range": "1,000",
    "force": "3",
    "spread": "10",
    "class": "FULLAUTO",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The item's subtext is a reference to the Biggie Smalls song 'Come On'."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The synergy with the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Eyepatch",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " is a reference to Kurt Russell as Snake Plissken in the 1981 movie "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Escape from New York",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Escape_from_New_York"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ". Snake wears an eyepatch over his left eye and primarily uses a MAC10. 'Iroquois Plissken' is also an alias used by Snake in the Metal Gear series. The character of Snake is heavily based on Snake Plissken, including wearing an eyepatch."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The MAC10 is based on the real life "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "machine pistol of the same name",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/MAC-10"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The MAC10 does not appear in "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Exit the Gungeon",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", however it still exists in the assets and text string database of the game. Like all real-world guns in Exit the Gungeon, the unused MAC-10 has a different name in the "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Apple Arcade",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " string database, where it is called the APP-10."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The entry for the MAC10 in the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Physical Ammonomicon",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " has a small doodle what seems to be Snake Plissken from "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Escape From New York",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", as well as a cracked egg with a face. The cracked egg may be a reference to the egg-shaped escape pod used by the President to escape a crashing Airforce 1 in the film."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Triple Gun",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/a/a0/Triple_Gun.png",
    "notes": "Changes form based on how much ammo it has left.",
    "quote": "Bullet the Stampede",
    "quality": "B",
    "type": "Varies",
    "dps": "16.7/ 46.2/ 160.0",
    "magazine_size": "9 (revolver) 32 (machine gun) 500 (beam)",
    "ammo_capacity": "250 (revolver) 500 (machine gun/beam)",
    "damage": "10 (revolver) 6.5 (machine gun)",
    "fire_rate": "0.5 (revolver) 0.11 (machine gun)",
    "reload_time": "1.4",
    "shot_speed": "?",
    "range": "?",
    "force": "?",
    "spread": "?",
    "class": "PISTOL",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Transitions between different forms based on its current ammo count.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "When at 70% ammo on the Revolver form (175 ammo if "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Ammo Capacity Multiplier",
                  "kind": "unresolved"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " has not been modified) it will transition to Machine Gun form."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "When at 10% ammo on the Machine Gun form (50 ammo if "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Ammo Capacity Multiplier",
                  "kind": "unresolved"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " has not been modified) it will transition to Beam Form."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Any ammo gain which puts the Triple Gun back over these thresholds will cause it to return to its previous form."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "item_interactions": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Magazine Rack",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If the Triple Gun is given infinite ammo, it will remain indefinitely in the form it was in until its ammo count returns to normal. This allows the use of powerful forms like the Beam for much longer."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Duct Tape",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If the Triple Gun is duct taped onto another weapon, it will permanently remain in the form it was in when it was taped.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Duct Taping a high firerate weapon to the Triple Gun allows it to expend ammo faster in the first phase, making it easier to get to the more powerful ammo thresholds. However, this also causes the Triple Gun to expend ammo faster when in its more powerful forms, making them less efficient."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This gun is a reference to the anime "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Trigun",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Trigun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", with its first form's appearance resembling the revolver used by its main character, Vash the Stampede. Its second form is in reference to the main character's arm machine gun, and the third to his Angel Arm.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The line, "
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "\"this gun is in actuality a very rare plant,\"",
                  "style": "i"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " is a reference to the "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ext",
                  "v": "Plants",
                  "url": "https://trigun.fandom.com/wiki/Plants"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " in "
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Trigun",
                  "style": "i"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": ", interdimensional beings whose bodies produce seemingly endless amounts of luminous yellow energy, similar to the third form's beam attack."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Triple Gun was first shown in the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "release trailer",
              "url": "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=x3YN0qhy8R8"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " for the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Supply Drop Update",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", despite not being properly added until "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "A Farewell to Arms",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ".\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " Fixed Bug Prior to "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "A Farewell to Arms",
                  "kind": "lore"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": ", the Triple Gun could still be encountered in "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Blessed Mode?action=edit&redlink=1",
                  "kind": "unresolved"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " Bug If the Triple Gun is in beam form, and it regains ammo over the 10% threshold "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "while",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " firing its beam, it will revert into its previous forms but will continue to fire its beam so long as the fire button is pressed. This can happen multiple times if the Triple Gun continues to cross over the beam form ammo threshold, stacking multiple beams."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " Bug The beam form of the Triple Gun can struggle to damage the heart of the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "High Dragun",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " in its second phase, possibly due to its large footprint."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Heck Blaster",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/9/9f/Heck_Blaster.png",
    "notes": "Rapidly fires invisible bullets. Jammed enemies hit will revert to normal.",
    "quote": "Whoa, Nelly",
    "quality": "B",
    "type": "Automatic",
    "dps": "31.4",
    "magazine_size": "999",
    "ammo_capacity": "999",
    "damage": "2.5",
    "fire_rate": "0.05",
    "reload_time": "0.3",
    "shot_speed": "40",
    "range": "14",
    "force": "3",
    "spread": "8",
    "class": "FULLAUTO",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Rapidly fires invisible bullets."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Jammed",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Enemies",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " and "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Bosses",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " hit by the Heck Blaster will revert to normal."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "item_interactions": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Battery Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " /  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Cursed Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - The visual effects of these items render the bullets of the Heck Blaster mostly visible."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This gun is useful in high  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Curse",
              "kind": "stat"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " runs, as it gives players a counter to the high spawn rates of Jammed enemies. This gun has no effect on the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Lord of the Jammed",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", however, and reverted enemies will only drop the usual amount of money upon death."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Gunjurer",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " cannot absorb Heck Blaster's bullets."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This gun is also capable of reverting Jammed bosses to normal, including the Jammed Lich that appears in the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Lich",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " fight."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This gun is a reference to the Plasma Blaster from "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Earthworm Jim",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Earthworm_Jim"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ".\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Whoa, Nelly",
                  "style": "i"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " is a catchphrase Jim uses."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Planet \"Heck\" is a location in the game."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The  "
                },
                {
                  "t": "synref",
                  "v": "Dr Worm"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " synergy's effect refers to the Plasma Blaster's ability to slowly regain ammo if it was under 100 ammo."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The  "
                },
                {
                  "t": "synref",
                  "v": "Great Queen Ant"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " synergy is a reference to the final boss in Earthworm Jim, "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ext",
                  "v": "The Evil Queen Pulsating, Bloated, Festering, Sweaty, Pus-filled, Malformed, Slug-for-a-Butt.",
                  "url": "http://earthwormjim.wikia.com/wiki/Queen_Slug-for-a-Butt"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Dr Worm"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " synergy is a reference to "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "the song of the same name",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Doctor_Worm"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " by the band They Might Be Giants."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The entry for the Heck Blaster in the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Physical Ammonomicon",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " has a small doodle of a smiling earthworm."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Patriot",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/1/12/Patriot.png",
    "notes": "Fires piercing bullets. Fire rate increases rapidly as the trigger is held.",
    "quote": "Gun Eater",
    "quality": "1S",
    "type": "Automatic",
    "dps": "69.0",
    "magazine_size": "100",
    "ammo_capacity": "500",
    "damage": "7",
    "fire_rate": "0.30",
    "reload_time": "1.0",
    "shot_speed": "30",
    "range": "1,000",
    "force": "15",
    "spread": "1",
    "class": "FULLAUTO",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Fires high-accuracy bullets that can pierce up to 3 times."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Rate of fire increases the longer the trigger is held."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "item_interactions": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Duct Tape",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - The Patriot reacts differently with Duct Tape depending on if it is the host gun.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "If another gun is Duct Taped onto Patriot, that gun will "
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "also",
                  "style": "i"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " increase its rate of fire the longer the trigger is held. This can be hard to see, however, as most guns do not have a large enough magazine size to properly witness it."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "If Patriot is Duct Taped onto another gun, it will lose its ability to ramp up its firerate, always firing at its slowest speed."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This gun is a reference to the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "weapon of the same name",
              "url": "https://metalgear.fandom.com/wiki/The_Patriot"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " in "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Metal Gear Solid 3: Snake Eater",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ".\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Ammonomicon",
                  "kind": "lore"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " quote "
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "\"Gun Eater\"",
                  "style": "i"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " is a reference to the title of the game- "
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "\"Snake Eater\"",
                  "style": "i"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "This gun's description is a reference to the convoluted and hard to follow plot of the "
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Metal Gear",
                  "style": "i"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " series, and how people still enjoy it regardless."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "It could also be a reference to The Patriot's actual mechanism in the Metal Gear Solid series, where the gun is stated to have infinite ammo due to its internal feed mechanism being "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ext",
                  "v": "shaped like an infinity symbol (∞)",
                  "url": "https://metalgear.fandom.com/wiki/The_Patriot#Information"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The Patriot's bullets "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ext",
                  "v": "tumble",
                  "url": "https://metalgear.fandom.com/wiki/The_Patriot#Design_and_presentation"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " in "
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Metal Gear Solid 3",
                  "style": "i"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": ", which would make the bullets incapable of piercing anything outside of the Gungeon."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The  "
                },
                {
                  "t": "synref",
                  "v": "What a Thrill"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " synergy is a reference to the opening line of the song "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ext",
                  "v": "Snake Eater",
                  "url": "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=tfLzcPHW_Rs"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " from "
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Metal Gear Solid 3",
                  "style": "i"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Gunderlord"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " synergy is a reference to the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Thunderlord",
              "url": "https://www.destinypedia.com/Thunderlord"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " weapon in "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Destiny",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", which has a similar ramping rate of fire mechanic to the Patriot."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This gun's real life counterpart is a modified "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "XM16E1 Assault rifle",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/M16_rifle"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " with a cut down barrel, smaller stock and C-MAG 100-round magazine."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The entry for the Patriot in the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Physical Ammonomicon",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " has a small doodle of a snake."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
