  {
    "name": "AC-15",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/f/f6/AC-15.png",
    "notes": "Becomes more powerful if the player has armor.",
    "quote": "Metalled Gear",
    "quality": "B",
    "type": "Automatic",
    "dps": "25.8/27.9",
    "magazine_size": "40",
    "ammo_capacity": "300",
    "damage": "Unarmored: 3.8 Armored: 15",
    "fire_rate": "Unarmored: 0.125 Armored: 0.5",
    "reload_time": "1.8",
    "shot_speed": "30 (Unarmored) 50 (Armored)",
    "range": "1,000 (Unarmored) 25 (Armored)",
    "force": "8 (Unarmored) 50 (Armored)",
    "spread": "10 (Unarmored) 1 (Armored)",
    "class": "SILLY",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Has two different forms, transforming between them depending on whether or not the player has  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Armor",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ".\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Without Armor, this gun fires low-damage purple laser blasts at a high rate of fire."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "With Armor, this gun fires fast blue blasts with slower rate of fire and high knockback. These blue blasts can pierce up to 3 times."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "If all armor is lost while AC-15 is in its armored form, it plays a short breaking animation when returning to its original form."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "The Robot",
              "kind": "character"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " will always have the armored form due to The Robot having armor instead of hearts."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " Possible Bug When obtaining the AC-15 from a chest without  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Armor",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", it will briefly appear upgraded before quickly reverting to un-armored form."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This gun is a reference to the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Armor Class",
              "url": "https://roll20.net/compendium/dnd5e/Armor#content"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", or "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "AC",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " system in "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Dungeons & Dragons",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", used to assess a character's defensive capabilities. In "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Dungeons & Dragons",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", wearing armour increases a character's AC, making them harder to hurt.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The unintuitive system mentioned in this gun's "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Ammonomicon",
                  "kind": "lore"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " entry is a reference to "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ext",
                  "v": "THAC0",
                  "url": "https://dungeonsdragons.fandom.com/wiki/THAC0"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " (short for "
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "To Hit Armor Class 0",
                  "style": "i"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": ") system used in "
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Dungeons & Dragons 2nd Edition",
                  "style": "i"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": ". THAC0 provided die-rolling tables to determine if an attack would hit a target, with the requirement to hit increasing depending on a target's AC value. This system was complex and confusing, and as such was discontinued in later editions."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The unused  "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Unused and Cut Content/Synergies",
                  "kind": "lore"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " synergy is also a reference to "
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Dungeons & Dragons",
                  "style": "i"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": ", where Constitution is one of the core six "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ext",
                  "v": "ability scores",
                  "url": "https://dnd-wiki.org/wiki/Canon:Ability_Score"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": ". Rolling a 'Constitution Check' is necessary to determine a character's fortitude, stamina, and resilience."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Armored Corps"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - synergy may be a reference to the mecha-shooter series "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Armored Core",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Armored_Core"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The entry for the AC-15 in the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Physical Ammonomicon",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " has a small doodle of a figure hunched behind a "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Dungeon Master's Screen",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dungeon_Masters_Screen"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", a folded board used by Dungeon Masters to conceal sensitive information from players in "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Dungeons & Dragons",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ". This screen appears to have a "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Bullet Kin",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " and the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "High Dragun",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " printed on it.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Furthermore, this entry is actually misprinted, using the pickup quote "
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "\"Metalled Gear\"",
                  "style": "i"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " instead of the appropriate "
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Armor Class Non-Zero",
                  "style": "i"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Vulcan Cannon",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/c/cf/Vulcan_Cannon.png",
    "notes": "",
    "quote": "Boundless Slaughter",
    "quality": "1S",
    "type": "Automatic",
    "dps": "100.0",
    "magazine_size": "900",
    "ammo_capacity": "900",
    "damage": "5",
    "fire_rate": "0.05",
    "reload_time": "0.6",
    "shot_speed": "35",
    "range": "1,000",
    "force": "15",
    "spread": "12",
    "class": "FULLAUTO",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "According to its ammonomicon entry, the Vulcan Cannon is wielded by the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Gatling Gull",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", however its visual appearance is starkly different to the minigun the Gatling Gull can be seen holding in battle."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The gun is a reference to a common trope of action films where people will carry "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "handheld M134 Miniguns",
              "url": "https://www.imfdb.org/wiki/M134_Minigun#Handheld_M134_Minigun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", which in reality is very difficult and impractical.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The  "
                },
                {
                  "t": "synref",
                  "v": "Not Quite As Mini"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " synergy is a reference to the "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ext",
                  "v": "Minigun from Team Fortress 2",
                  "url": "https://wiki.teamfortress.com/wiki/Minigun"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " in appereance and function and subsequently reaffirms this."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This gun's name references the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "M61A1 Vulcan",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/M61_Vulcan"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", a Gatling-style rotary cannon.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The  "
                },
                {
                  "t": "synref",
                  "v": "Vulcan Raving"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " synergy is a play on words on the name of "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ext",
                  "v": "Vulcan Raven",
                  "url": "https://metalgear.fandom.com/wiki/Vulcan_Raven"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
