  {
    "name": "Gungine",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/d/da/Gungine.png",
    "notes": "Greatly increases movement speed while held. Reloading clears nearby goop and refills the gun's magazine. Gets fire immune while held.",
    "quote": "12 Cylinder",
    "quality": "1S",
    "type": "Automatic",
    "dps": "80.6",
    "magazine_size": "100",
    "ammo_capacity": "800",
    "damage": "5",
    "fire_rate": "0.05",
    "reload_time": "1.14",
    "shot_speed": "35",
    "range": "1,000",
    "force": "15",
    "spread": "6",
    "class": "FULLAUTO",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Fires rapidly."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Increases movement speed by 2.25 while held."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Reloading while standing in "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Goop",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " clears all goop in a small radius around the player and restores all missing ammo in the current magazine.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Does not work while flying."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Grants "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Status Effects",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " immunity while held."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "item_interactions": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Wax Wings",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " /  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Ring of Ethereal Form",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " /  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Cat Bullet King Throne",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " /  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Jetpack",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - While flying, the player is no longer considered to be standing on any goop- even while flying above it. This prevents the player from being able to utilise the Gungine's free reload."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Items that generate "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Goop",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " can be used to reload the Gungine extremely cheaply.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Bug Boots",
                  "kind": "item"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " - As Bug Boots generates goop at no ammo or item charge cost, it can generate potentially infinite ammo for the Gungine totally free."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Zombie Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If Zombie Bullets refunds ammo during a magazine that is then refunded with goop, the Gungine will be left with "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "more",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " ammunition that was initially used to fire the magazine."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Oil Sconces in the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Black Powder Mine",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ",  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Blobulon",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " (and their variants), and goop "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Barrels",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " in the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Oubliette",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " are all extremely useful naturally occurring sources of goop within the Gungeon."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This gun is a reference to the Vlambeer game "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Luftrausers",
              "url": "http://luftrausers.com/"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", which features a bullet-firing engine of the same name."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "It is also likely a play on 'Gungeon'.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "This would explain the  "
                },
                {
                  "t": "synref",
                  "v": "Contractual Obligation"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " synergy, as Devolver Digital is the publisher for the game, and therefore would logically have a contractual obligation to support it."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "In addition to this, the  "
                },
                {
                  "t": "synref",
                  "v": "what engine do you use"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " synergy is a reference to the game's development in the Unity engine."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Judging by its Ammonomicon Entry tagline and overall appearance, the Gungine is likely modeled after the real-world "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "V-12",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/V12_engine"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " engine."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The entry for the Gungine in the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Physical Ammonomicon",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " has a small doodle of a car with eyes."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " Bug Since the Gungine replenishes ammo at the start of reloading, interrupting the reload by swapping to another weapon will give the missing ammo without reloading the Gungine. This can allow a single puddle of liquid to give several hundred rounds."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " Possible Bug If the Gungine has a full clip, pressing the Reload button will still clear liquids, but will not give the player ammo as no shots were fired in the current clip."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " Possible Bug If the player is holding the Gungine while entering the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Aimless Void",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", the speed increase of the weapon persists despite it not being visually held. This effect does not carry over into "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "The Past",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "The Predator",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/2/2e/The_Predator.png",
    "notes": "Locks onto enemies and fires high speed homing lasers. Invisibility while reloading an empty magazine.",
    "quote": "High-tech $#!*",
    "quality": "B",
    "type": "Semiautomatic",
    "dps": "29.4",
    "magazine_size": "8",
    "ammo_capacity": "150",
    "damage": "25",
    "fire_rate": "0.80",
    "reload_time": "1.2",
    "shot_speed": "72",
    "range": "32",
    "force": "10",
    "spread": "5",
    "class": "PISTOL",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Thermal Imaging"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If the player also has "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Sunglasses",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", The Predator fires two lasers instead of one.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "This synergy negatively interacts with "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Helix Bullets",
                  "kind": "item"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": ". The Predator shots will retain homing, but their trajectories become unstable. This can be offset somewhat by aiming slightly away from the target."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Mimic",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " are revealed differently from other mimics with the weapon. When the player's cursor is near Wall Mimics, their mimic state will be shown with the weapon's crosshair, even if they haven't been exposed yet."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This gun can be used to "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Stealing",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " items from "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Shop",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Unlike the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Grey Mauser",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", the Predator's invisibility buff does not come with a damage boost."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Like with other homing weapons, "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Gunjurer",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "s won't be able to reclaim its projectile to shoot it back at the player."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "trivia": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This gun is a reference to the film "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Predator",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Predator_(film)"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ".\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "This gun's description is a reference to a quote from the film, \"If it bleeds, we can kill it.\""
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The portrait of this gun moves around in the same direction that the player points it."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Dragunfire",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/c/c9/Dragunfire.png",
    "notes": "Rapidly fires burning bullets that have a chance to inflict Burn .",
    "quote": "Roar",
    "quality": "A",
    "type": "Automatic",
    "dps": "42.4",
    "magazine_size": "30",
    "ammo_capacity": "600",
    "damage": "5",
    "fire_rate": "0.05",
    "reload_time": "1.6",
    "shot_speed": "25",
    "range": "1,000",
    "force": "27",
    "spread": "7",
    "class": "FULLAUTO",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The design of the Dragunfire is that of the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Bolter",
              "url": "http://warhammer40k.wikia.com/wiki/Bolter"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " from the dystopian science-fantasy universe of "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Warhammer 40,000",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Warhammer_40,000"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ".\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The name of the gun comes from the Dragonfire round which the Bolter can fire. Dragonfire Bolts are hollow-shelled bolts that explode with a gout of superheated gas that can eliminate the value of cover."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The tagline \"Roar\" is a reference to the Bolter's unique roaring sound when fired."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Despite igniting enemies, the Dragunfire is not in the FIRE "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Guns",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "A special version of the Dragunfire, the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "High Dragunfire",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", can be found in a special "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Secret Rooms",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Sniper Rifle",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/c/cf/Sniper_Rifle.png",
    "notes": "Fires a high-velocity bullet that can pierce through one enemy.",
    "quote": "Scope Creep",
    "quality": "C",
    "type": "Semiautomatic",
    "dps": "24.8",
    "magazine_size": "10",
    "ammo_capacity": "80",
    "damage": "26",
    "fire_rate": "1.00",
    "reload_time": "1.5",
    "shot_speed": "200",
    "range": "1,000",
    "force": "15",
    "spread": "1",
    "class": "RIFLE",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The synergy  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "360 Yes Scope"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " is a reference to the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "360 No Scope",
              "url": "https://knowyourmeme.com/memes/360-no-scope"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " meme spawned by "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Call of Duty 4: Modern Warfare",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Call_of_Duty_4:_Modern_Warfare"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Diazepam"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " and  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Sniper Woof"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " synergies are referencing Metal Gear Solid's "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Sniper Wolf",
              "url": "https://metalgear.wikia.com/wiki/Sniper_Wolf"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " character."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "\"Scope Creep\" is a reference to a common problem in many projects where the original goals expand while the project is in progress."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Sniper Rifle's shots are able to penetrate flipped tables, provided the table is the first thing the shot hits."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "A.W.P.",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/8/85/A.W.P..png",
