    "wiki": {
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Due to its slow rate of fire it is easy to fire another gun between A.W.P. shots without A.W.P. downtime."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "A.W.P is an acronym for Arctic Warfare Police."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "\"Noob Cannon\"",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " is a reference to the AWP weapon in "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Counter-Strike",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", popular among new and experienced players alike for its ability to one-shot opposing players. The line \"banned in certain sectors\" is a reference to the fact that the AWP is often banned in certain public Counter-Strike servers due to its overuse and perceived lack of balance."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The last sentence of the Ammonomicon is a reference to older versions of the game "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Counter-Strike",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", where if the player switched to another weapon and back to the sniper rifle after firing, they would be able to skip the bolt animation and therefore be able to fire again quicker."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The synergy  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Sniper Woof"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " is a reference to the character "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Sniper Wolf",
              "url": "https://metalgear.wikia.com/wiki/Sniper_Wolf"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " from "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Metal Gear Solid",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Arctic Warfare"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " synergy changes the sprite of the A.W.P to the Asiimov, an A.W.P skin available in "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Counter-Strike 2",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " (previously Counter-Strike: Global Offensive).\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The white camouflage itself is a reference to the real life "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ext",
                  "v": "Accuracy International Arctic Warfare sniper rifle",
                  "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Accuracy_International_Arctic_Warfare"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The synergy  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "360 Yes Scope"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " is a reference to the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "360 No Scope",
              "url": "https://knowyourmeme.com/memes/360-no-scope"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " meme spawned by "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Call of Duty 4: Modern Warfare",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Call_of_Duty_4:_Modern_Warfare"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The entry for the A.W.P. in the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Physical Ammonomicon",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " has a small doodle of a curved knife with a 150 dollar price tag. This is a reference to the secondary resale markets for "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Counter-Strike",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", where cosmetic knife skins have historically commanded extreme prices."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "M1",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/5/59/M1.png",
    "notes": "Fires a high-velocity piercing bullet.",
    "quote": "Bolt Action",
    "quality": "C",
    "type": "Semiautomatic",
    "dps": "22.6",
    "magazine_size": "6",
    "ammo_capacity": "100",
    "damage": "20",
    "fire_rate": "0.80",
    "reload_time": "1.3",
    "shot_speed": "200",
    "range": "60",
    "force": "25",
    "spread": "2",
    "class": "RIFLE",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Bullets from the M1 pierce through enemies and decorations, and travel at an extremely high speed. Bullets from the M1 leave a trail of smoke in the air behind them, although this effect is purely visual. \nOn reload, the M1 makes a distinctive \"ping\" sound."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Although classified as semi-automatic, the M1 is functionally automatic, as its rate of fire does not benefit from tapping the fire button instead of holding it down."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "There are several real guns with the name 'M1', however the shape (such as the band around the rifle's forend), distinctive pinging reload sound, and Ammonomicon entry of the weapon (Coupled with the fact that it is referred to as the 'Grand Rifle' in the Apple Arcade version of Exit the Gungeon) suggest that this rifle is the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "M1 Garand",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/M1_Garand"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", a famous semi-automatic rifle that served as the mainstay of the US Army in World War 2."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The synergy  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "M1 Multi-Tool"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " is a reference to the MIDA Multi-Tool from the Destiny series. The boost to movement speed is based on MIDA's unique perk, and its appearance resembles a scout rifle from the Destiny series.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "It resembles an M14 battle rifle, which was a replacement for the M1 Garand battle rifle using box magazines rather than an internal en-bloc-clip-fed magazine, and was capable of select-fire."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The synergy  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Smile, you son of a..."
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " is a reference to the final scene of the movie Jaws, where Martin Brody shoots a gas tank in a shark's mouth with an M1 Garand, making it explode."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The synergy  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Sniper Woof"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " is a reference to Metal Gear Solid's "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Sniper Wolf",
              "url": "https://metalgear.wikia.com/wiki/Sniper_Wolf"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " character."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Winchester Rifle",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/8/80/Winchester_Rifle.png",
    "notes": "",
    "quote": "Guns And Deviltry.",
    "quality": "D",
    "type": "Semiautomatic",
    "dps": "19.7",
    "magazine_size": "12",
    "ammo_capacity": "130",
    "damage": "15",
    "fire_rate": "0.72",
    "reload_time": "1.2",
    "shot_speed": "32",
    "range": "1,000",
    "force": "9",
    "spread": "5",
    "class": "RIFLE",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Winchester Rifle appears to be based off the real world "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Winchester Model 1866",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Winchester_rifle#Model_1866"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", the first 'Winchester Rifle' created by the "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Winchester Repeating Arms Company",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ". This gun was known for its distinctive yellow receiver, made of a bronze-brass alloy which earned it the nickname "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Yellow Boy",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Although classified as semi-automatic, the Winchester Rifle is functionally automatic, as its rate of fire does not benefit from tapping the fire button instead of holding it down."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Ammonomicon description \"Guns and Deviltry\" is a direct reference to "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Swords and Deviltry",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Swords_and_Deviltry"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", the first collected volume of Fafhrd and the Gray Mouser short stories. Both "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Frifle and the Grey Mauser",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " are references to "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Fafhrd and the Gray Mouser",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fafhrd_and_the_Gray_Mouser"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Like the  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Sawed-Off",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", the animations of the Winchester Rifle are physically inconsistent, with empty casings being ejected both on reload and the chambering of each new round."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Winchester Rifle does not appear in "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Exit the Gungeon",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", however it still exists in the assets and text string database of the game. Like all real-world guns in Exit the Gungeon, the unused Winchester Rifle has a different name in the "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Apple Arcade",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " string database, where it is called the Repeating Rifle."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Corsair",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/4/4f/Corsair.png",
    "notes": "Fires slow, bouncing bullets that accelerate and curve towards enemies, leaving a dashed line of trail.",
    "quote": "Plot A Course",
    "quality": "C",
    "type": "Charged",
    "dps": "12.5",
    "magazine_size": "1",
    "ammo_capacity": "200",
    "damage": "10",
    "fire_rate": "0",
    "reload_time": "0.5",
    "shot_speed": "26",
    "range": "1,000",
    "force": "25",
    "spread": "5",
    "class": "CHARGE",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Fires slow moving bullets that accelerate and bounce around the room."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "These bullets have a slight homing effect, curving towards enemies."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Upon reaching the end of their lifespan, these bullets explode- creating a large red X at the position of the explosion."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "item_interactions": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "iBomb Companion App",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - As the projectiles of the Corsair are explosive, using the iBomb Companion App will prematurely detonate them wherever they are in the room."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Prior to the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Supply Drop Update",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", the bullets did not curve."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Corsair's bullets cannot be caught by "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Gunjurers?action=edit&redlink=1",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "\"Corsair\" is a common name for a pirate or a privateer operating on the high seas, especially ones operating along the southern coast of the Mediterranean in the 16th–18th centuries who were often slavers."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " Bug Corsair bullets can travel through locked cells, potentially damaging chests on the other side."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The entry for the Corsair in the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Physical Ammonomicon",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " has a small doodle of a sailboat with a small figure (possibly a "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Bullet Kin",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ") in its "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "crow's nest",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Crow%27s_nest"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Railgun",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/a/ab/Railgun.png",
    "notes": "Charges to fire a high-velocity, piercing bullet that bounces many times.",
    "quote": "Calibrating",
    "quality": "1S",
    "type": "Charged",
    "dps": "27.0-243.2",
    "magazine_size": "1",
    "ammo_capacity": "40",
    "damage": "50",
    "fire_rate": "N/A",
    "reload_time": "0.6",
    "shot_speed": "250",
    "range": "1,000",
    "force": "50",
    "spread": "0",
    "class": "CHARGE",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Dead Cell"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If the player also has "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Fortune's Favor",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", the charge time is 10% faster and its damage to bosses is increased by 30%."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "When this gun is charged, the beam of light coming from the end is usually stopped by walls. However, passages to secret rooms will let the light through, revealing their location. If the weapon is switched before it is discharged, no ammo will be used. Sometimes the laser glitches through random areas of wall. To make sure it is a door and not a glitch, strafe and make sure the laser highlights a door-sized area."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": []
        },
        {
          "tokens": []
        }
      ],
      "trivia": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Its appearance is near identical to the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "man-portable rail gun",
              "url": "https://metalgear.fandom.com/wiki/Rail_gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " from the "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Metal Gear Solid",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " franchise.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The synergy with Fortune's Favor is a reference to the character Fortune from "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ext",
                  "v": "Metal Gear Solid 2",
                  "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Metal_Gear_Solid_2:_Sons_of_Liberty"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": ", who wields the weapon.\n"
                }
              ],
              "sub": [
                {
                  "tokens": [
                    {
                      "t": "text",
                      "v": "Ironically, Fortune doesn't wield the final production model seen in "
                    },
                    {
                      "t": "ext",
                      "v": "Metal Gear Solid 4",
                      "url": "https://metalgear.fandom.com/wiki/Metal_Gear_Solid_4:_Guns_of_the_Patriots"
                    },
                    {
                      "t": "text",
                      "v": "; she wields the "
                    },
                    {
                      "t": "ref",
                      "v": "Prototype Railgun",
                      "kind": "gun"
                    },
                    {
                      "t": "text",
                      "v": "."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The synergy  "
                },
                {
                  "t": "synref",
                  "v": "Dead Cell"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " is a reference to Fortune's squad, the Dead Cell Unit."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The flavor text is a reference to the character "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Garrus Vakarian",
              "url": "https://masseffect.fandom.com/wiki/Garrus_Vakarian"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " of the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Mass Effect",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mass_Effect"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " franchise. A running joke (both in universe and in real life among fans of the series) is that Garrus really likes to calibrate guns."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Railgun does not need to be charged until the guiding lines fully converge. In fact, the weapon will fire around halfway through its full charging animation, because it is \"charged\" as soon as the small cloud of smoke emerges around the player."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Prototype Railgun",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/4/43/Prototype_Railgun.png",
    "notes": "Charges to fire a high-velocity, piercing bullet.",
    "quote": "DANGER: HIGH VOLTAGE",
    "quality": "A",
    "type": "Charged",
    "dps": "51.0",
    "magazine_size": "1",
    "ammo_capacity": "40",
    "damage": "150",
    "fire_rate": "N/A",
