    "spread": "7",
    "class": "PISTOL",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Fires purple lasers that can each bounce up to 2 times."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "RUBE-ADYNE MK.II is the upgraded version of the  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "RUBE-ADYNE Prototype",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The RUBE-ABYNE MK.II multiplies the loot weight of the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "RUBE-ADYNE Prototype",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " by 2, doubling its likelihood of appearing. This is likely to aid players in obtaining the  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Rubenstein's Monster"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " synergy.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Curiously, this does not work in reverse. Obtaining the RUBE-ADYNE Prototype does "
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "not",
                  "style": "i"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " make the RUBE-ADYNE MK.II more likely to appear."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The RUBE-ADYNE weapons may be named after "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "David Rubel",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", one of the programmers of "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Enter the Gungeon",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ".\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "As Rubel is one of the lead programmers at "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Dodge Roll",
                  "kind": "lore"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": ", the "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Ammonomicon",
                  "kind": "lore"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " entry of this gun may be a reference to the development of "
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Enter the Gungeon",
                  "style": "i"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " itself, with Rubel needing to program the physics of bouncy projectiles."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Rubenstein's Monster",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/0/08/Rubenstein%27s_Monster.png",
    "notes": "Created when both RUBE-ADYNE Prototype and RUBE-ADYNE MK.II are picked up. Rapidly fires bouncing lasers.",
    "quote": "Unit 00",
    "quality": "N",
    "type": "Automatic",
    "dps": "102.2",
    "magazine_size": "100",
    "ammo_capacity": "900",
    "damage": "7",
    "fire_rate": "0.07",
    "reload_time": "0.9",
    "shot_speed": "26",
    "range": "1,000",
    "force": "9",
    "spread": "11",
    "class": "SHITTY",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Rapidly fires pink laser blasts that can bounce once."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "item_interactions": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Ring of the Resourceful Rat",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - As this gun does not have a standard item quality, the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Resourceful Rat",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " will give "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "nothing",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " in return when trading for it."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This gun is not needed for completion. The  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Finished Gun",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " can be unlocked without having this gun's "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Ammonomicon",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " entry filled."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Despite its considerable power, Rubenstein's Monster is in the SHITTY "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Guns",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ".\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Since Rubenstein's Monster is excluded from the normal loot pool, this has no effect on the player's likelihood to obtain the gun, but it will still reduce the chance of finding other SHITTY class weapons in the future by an additional 90%."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Since the Rubenstein's Monster is technically a different gun from either of its components, any guns  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Duct Tape",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " to either of them will be lost upon completing this synergy."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This is the only SPECIAL quality gun obtainable in regular play that is not a starter weapon."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Rubenstein's Monster has extensive visual similarities to its component guns. Strangely, the barrel of the  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "RUBE-ADYNE MK.II",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " seems to have been repurposed as a scope."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The name of this gun is a reference to "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Frankenstein's Monster",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frankenstein%27s_monster"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", a creature made by combining different human body parts in the 1818 novel "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Frankenstein; or, The Modern Prometheus",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This gun may be a reference to the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Wave Gun",
              "url": "https://callofduty.fandom.com/wiki/Wave_Gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " in the zombies gamemode of "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Call of Duty: Black Ops",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ". The Wave Gun has two firing modes, a pair of laser pistols that can be dual wield, and a singular weapon that fires a purple laser which explodes zombies. When transitioning from dual wield form to combined form, the two laser pistols are combined end-to-end to create the rifle."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Chamber Gun",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/1/16/Chamber_Gun.png",
    "notes": "Transforms based on the current chamber.",
    "quote": "Product of Environment",
    "quality": "C",
    "type": "Semiautomatic",
    "dps": "Varies",
    "magazine_size": "Varies",
    "ammo_capacity": "Varies",
    "damage": "Varies",
    "fire_rate": "Varies",
    "reload_time": "Varies",
    "shot_speed": "Varies",
    "range": "Varies",
    "force": "Varies",
    "spread": "Varies",
    "class": "NONE",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Master's Chambers"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - Each "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Master Round I",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " the player carries permanently unlocks the mode of its respective floor. Reloading the Chamber Gun with a full magazine cycles through the unlocked modes.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "This synergy does not work with "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Lich's Eye Bullets",
                  "kind": "item"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "In the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Keep of the Lead Lord",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", the Chamber Gun is a single target, semi-automatic gun."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "In the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Oubliette",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", the Chamber Gun fires poison skulls."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "In the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Gungeon Proper",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", the Chamber Gun is a shotgun that is somewhat similar to "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "The Membrane",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "In the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Abbey of the True Gun",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", the Chamber Gun is a piercing crossbow."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "In the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Black Powder Mine",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", the Chamber Gun is a melee-range, high damage drill.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Having "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Flak Bullets",
                  "kind": "item"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " equipped, this form will fire small, spark-like bullets in front of it, with significant damage output. This is a good combination with "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Orbital Bullets",
                  "kind": "item"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "In the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Resourceful Rat's Lair",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", the Chamber Gun is a rocket launcher which fires cheese wheels that "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Status Effects",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " enemies, similar to those fired by the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Elimentaler",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "In the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Hollow",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", the Chamber Gun is a combination of "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Glacier",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " and "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "The Exotic",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "; it fires an ice cube projectile that bounces off walls and enemies, leaves a trail of water, and eventually bursts into several homing rockets."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "In the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "R&G Dept.",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", the Chamber Gun is a pencil which functions similarly to the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Wood Beam",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", except that when you reload it, it flips to the other side (Pencil-> Eraser -> Pencil)."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "In the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Forge",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", the Chamber Gun is a beam weapon that shoots 2 homing beams of lava in a V-pattern."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "In "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Bullet Hell",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", the Chamber Gun is a homing chain beam similar to the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Raiden Coil",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", hitting all visible enemies at once for high damage."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "All modes share the same ammo pool. Firing a shot in one mode reduces the ammo of the other modes by a proportional amount. For example, firing one shot in its Hollow mode uses up 10 shots of the base mode, because the base mode has 10 times the max ammo."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Chamber Gun is one of the three weapons in the NONE "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Guns",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " that can be obtained in normal play, the others being the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Slinger",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " and the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Kruller Glaive",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "If the player has "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Chance Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " and does not switch to the Chamber Gun from a floor that does not have a Master Round (such as the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Oubliette",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Abbey of the True Gun",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Resourceful Rat's Lair",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", or the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "R&G Dept.",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "), other guns have a chance to shoot bullets from that firing mode."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Gunderfury",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/a/a7/Gunderfury.png",
    "notes": "Gains persist experience and levels up with kills, changing its appearance and stats.",
    "quote": "Gun of Guncraft",
    "quality": "A",
    "type": "Automatic",
    "dps": "25.5-181.2",
    "magazine_size": "8-50",
    "ammo_capacity": "200-500",
    "damage": "3.4-20x2",
    "fire_rate": "Varies",
    "reload_time": "Varies",
    "shot_speed": "Varies",
    "range": "Varies",
    "force": "Varies",
    "spread": "Varies",
    "class": "FULLAUTO",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Gunderfury has multiple forms, which it slowly levels up through as it gains experience over the course of multiple runs. Killing an enemy while Gunderfury is in the inventory (it does not need to be the active weapon) will grant the weapon experience equal to the maximum health of the slain enemy. Experience is permanent, and persists across the entire save file."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "After acquiring enough experience to reach a level up milestone, Gunderfury will instantaneously switch forms."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "While Gunderfury only changes it's forms at specific level-up milestones, it still progresses through every level between each form. When switching to Gunderfury, it's current level is briefly shown alongside it's name in the UI."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "item_interactions": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Duct Tape",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - Gunderfury does "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "not",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " gain experience while duct taped onto another gun. If another gun is duct taped onto Gunderfury, it will lose any extra added ammo capacity from the duct tape combo upon levelling up into a new form."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Eyepatch",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - As eyepatch multiplies bullet spread, it has no effect on the accuracy of Gunderfury's final form. Any multiplier of zero will always be zero."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Rainbow Mode",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " is an effective way to farm experience for Gunderfury, as it is possible to restart until it is acquired in the very first  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Rainbow Chest",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Killing infinitely spawnable enemies, such as  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Zombullet",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ",  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Killithid",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " illusions, or  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Misfire Beast",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " projections will still grant Gunderfury experience."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This gun is a reference to the legendary sword "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Thunderfury, Blessed Blade of the Windseeker",
              "url": "https://warcraft.wiki.gg/wiki/Thunderfury,_Blessed_Blade_of_the_Windseeker"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " from "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "World of Warcraft",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ". The leveling system is also reflective of many roleplaying games, such as WoW, wherein killing enemies grants the player experience which will cause them to level up and grow in level, becoming more powerful and unlocking more abilities. Level 60 was also the maximum level when "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "World of Warcraft",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " was released."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The line "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "\"Mishandled by idiots for countless hours.\"",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " line in the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Ammonomicon",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " entry for this gun is a reference to a meme in the "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "World of Warcraft",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " community where people will spam the item 'Thunderfury, Blessed Blade of the Windseeker's name in the in game chat. It is also a reference to the fact that, in the same game, any player can potentially obtain Thunderfury, despite its legendary status."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Mine Cutter",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/c/c2/Mine_Cutter.png",
    "notes": "Reloading alternates between firing three small, piercing, parallel lasers and single large lasers.",
    "quote": "Safety First",
    "quality": "B",
    "type": "Semiautomatic",
    "dps": "45.0",
    "magazine_size": "12",
    "ammo_capacity": "250",
    "damage": "Triple: 10 Single: 8",
    "fire_rate": "0.10",
    "reload_time": "1.2",
    "shot_speed": "23",
    "range": "60",
    "force": "30",
    "spread": "7",
    "class": "PISTOL",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Dead Place"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If the player also has "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Melted Rock",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", Mine Cutter's damage is increased by 25%."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Mass Cutter"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If the player also has "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Mass Shotgun",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", when the Mass Shotgun shot splits, 6-10 piercing Mine Cutter lasers will be fired in a cone in the direction the shotgun was fired.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "If the Mass Shotgun shot hits an enemy before it splits, the lasers will not fire."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Mine Craft"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If the player also has "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Cluster Mine",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", mines created by Cluster Mine home in on enemies while Mine Cutter is equipped."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Even though the three parallel lasers appear to be separate, they are all effectively part of one wide laser. The gun will deal the same amount of damage regardless of how many of the lasers appear to hit the enemy, unless the player has modifiers like "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Scattershot",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ".\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "However the gun's projectiles do gain piercing when firing in triple mode. This may be to simulate multiple lasers instead of actually doing so."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "When Mine Cutter is in the single laser mode it has a higher maximum fire rate than normal."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "trivia": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This gun is a reference to the plasma cutter from "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Dead Space",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dead_Space_(series)"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ".\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The alternating fire mode refers to the plasma cutter's rotator module, which allows the cutter to fire either vertically or horizontally."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Mine Craft"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " synergy is a reference to the game "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Minecraft",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Minecraft"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
