  {
    "name": "Void Core Assault Rifle",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/d/d0/Void_Core_Assault_Rifle.png",
    "notes": "Fires bursts of three lasers.",
    "quote": "Rapid Fire",
    "quality": "B",
    "type": "Burst",
    "dps": "27.8",
    "magazine_size": "30",
    "ammo_capacity": "300",
    "damage": "6.5",
    "fire_rate": "0.35",
    "reload_time": "1.2",
    "shot_speed": "23",
    "range": "20",
    "force": "15",
    "spread": "3",
    "class": "FULLAUTO",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " Fires a 3-shot burst of lasers."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " Rapid-fires laser blasts."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "item_interactions": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Duct Tape",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - Duct taping another weapon onto any of the three guns in  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "The Void Corps"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - synergy will cause its orbital form (appearing when holding one of the other two) to "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "also",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " fire projectiles from the duct taped gun."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Lich's Eye Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - Lich's Eye Bullets successfully provides both orbiting guns for  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "The Void Corps"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " synergy, despite most synergies that rely on other guns being in the inventory not working this way."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Prior to release, this gun was originally known as the Space Core Assault Rifle with 250 ammo and 30 magazine size."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The name of the synergy \"Armored Corps\" is a homophone to the Armored Core game series."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Void Core Captain described in this gun's Ammonomicon entry is Alistair, the Thunderbolt, referenced in the Ammonomicon entries of many electricity-themed guns and items. A note written by him can also appear in secret rooms.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "It can be presumed from the VCAR's entry that Alistair made his way into the Gungeon to try and make sure that the Void Core was never disbanded."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Flash Ray",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/d/d0/Flash_Ray.png",
    "notes": "Shoots piercing laser beams.",
    "quote": "Ah Ahhh!",
    "quality": "D",
    "type": "Semiautomatic",
    "dps": "23.1",
    "magazine_size": "8",
    "ammo_capacity": "350",
    "damage": "7.5",
    "fire_rate": "0.20",
    "reload_time": "1.2",
    "shot_speed": "600",
    "range": "1,000",
    "force": "4",
    "spread": "10",
    "class": "PISTOL",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Ice Cap"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If the player also has "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Freeze Ray",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", it freezes enemies much quicker."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Savior of the Universe"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If the player also has "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Camera",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", Flash Ray gains double magazine size, unlimited piercing, a thicker beam, one bounce, increased fire rate, and causes a Camera flash when reloading an empty magazine. Camera also fires two laser beams whenever fired."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Whiter Guon Stone"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If the player also has "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "White Guon Stone",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", the size of the Guon Stone is increased, it rotates at a fixed distance from the player while they are moving instead of on a slight delay, and "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Daruma",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "'s recharge is halved. However, Daruma itself is not part of the synergy."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "With  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Challenge Mode",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " enabled, this gun's shot will bounce for a short distance before becoming a slow-moving red bullet."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The gun is very inaccurate, despite the instant travel speed of its laser beams.  It will often miss small targets at medium range and large targets at long range, and is most effective on clusters of enemies."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This gun deals very high damage against chests and "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Secret Rooms",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ". It's not recommended to check for mimics using this gun."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The gun's incredibly high projectile speed makes it synergize well with "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Heavy Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", as the speed decrease is negligible meaning it serves as an almost pure stats up."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "trivia": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Everything about this gun is a reference to Flash Gordon.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The quote "
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "\"Ah Ahhh!\"",
                  "style": "i"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " is a reference to Queen's song "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ext",
                  "v": "Flash",
                  "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Flash_(Queen_song)"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": ",",
                  "style": "i"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " which is Flash Gordon's theme song."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The synergy  "
                },
                {
                  "t": "synref",
                  "v": "Savior of the Universe"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " is the line after \"Ah Ahh!\""
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Wind Up Gun",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/9/99/Wind_Up_Gun.png",
    "notes": "In each magazine, the first 10 bullets pierce. The last 10 deal half damage.",
    "quote": "Charge It",
    "quality": "D",
    "type": "Automatic",
    "dps": "18.9",
    "magazine_size": "20",
    "ammo_capacity": "600",
    "damage": "5",
    "fire_rate": "0.13",
    "reload_time": "1.5",
    "shot_speed": "30",
    "range": "35",
    "force": "10",
    "spread": "8",
    "class": "FULLAUTO",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Breakfast Club"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If the player also has "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Seven-Leaf Clover",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", reload time is halved, fire rate is increased by 60%, damage is increased by 50%, magazine size is increased to 27, and all but the last 10 shots of each magazine will be stronger piercing lasers."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Wound Up"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If the player also has "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Oiled Cylinder",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", the bottom half of the magazine retains full damage and piercing, and the damage and bullet size is increased by 25%."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "With increased magazine size, all shots except for the last ten deal full damage and pierce, and only the last ten shots deal less damage."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "With both of its synergies, Wind Up Gun becomes very powerful, and even capable of killing bosses on its own."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "trivia": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This gun is a reference to a weapon from "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Futurama",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Futurama"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "; specifically the episode \"War Is the H-Word\".\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The fact that the weapon synergises with the Seven-Leaf Clover is due to said item also being a "
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Futurama",
                  "style": "i"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " reference, specifically the episode \"Luck of the Fryrish\". The name of the synergy is a reference to the fact that Fry hid a seven-leaf clover in a copy of the Breakfast Club on vinyl."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "When the Wind Up Gun is reloaded, it will play a segment of the nursery rhyme \"Pop Goes the Weasel\". The gun in the aforementioned episode plays the same tune."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "H4mmer",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/5/59/H4mmer.png",
    "notes": "Fires a barrage of bullets. The last shot in the magazine is a hammer, which deals extra damage and can stun enemies.",
    "quote": "Many Bullets",
    "quality": "B",
    "type": "Automatic",
    "dps": "63.5",
    "magazine_size": "30",
    "ammo_capacity": "450",
    "damage": "Bullets: 3.8 Hammer: 20",
    "fire_rate": "0.05",
    "reload_time": "0.6",
    "shot_speed": "23",
    "range": "1,000",
    "force": "6",
    "spread": "7",
    "class": "FULLAUTO",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Rapid-fires a barrage of bullets."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The last shot in every magazine is a high-damage hammer.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " This hammer has a 20% chance to "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Stun",
                  "kind": "lore"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " enemies for 3.5 seconds."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This gun may be a reference to the trick of "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "\"fanning the hammer\"",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", where a single-action revolver is fired by flicking the hammer of the weapon rather than pulling the trigger in order to make it shoot faster."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " Bug There is an issue with the  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Hammer and Nail"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " synergy where if the ammo count exceeds what the base gun would have without the 50% maximum ammo, the current ammo count would revert to that amount. Additionally, partial ammo kits cannot have the ammo go above the base gun's amount, unless it is applied to H4mmer itself."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Snakemaker",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/9/9c/Snakemaker.png",
    "notes": "Has a chance to transmogrify enemies into snakes.",
    "quote": "SSSSSSSSSSS",
    "quality": "A",
    "type": "Semiautomatic",
    "dps": "34.8",
    "magazine_size": "10",
    "ammo_capacity": "200",
    "damage": "12",
    "fire_rate": "0.25",
    "reload_time": "1.2",
    "shot_speed": "50",
    "range": "1,000",
    "force": "10",
    "spread": "0",
    "class": "SILLY",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Bosses",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " are immune to transmogrification."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Unlike chickens caused by other transmogrification, snakes cannot be killed and will not block shots."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Snakes can block enemies\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Jammed snakes will not deal contact damage as they cannot be touched."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Snakes can be touched and pushed around by companions such as the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Dog",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The name, \"Snakemaker\" is a reference to a scene from "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Rick and Morty",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rick_and_Morty"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", in which the titular Rick turns two armed guards into snakes, after which The President requests that he stop his \"snake-makery.\"\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The appearance of the gun also closely resembles Rick's "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ext",
                  "v": "laser pistol.",
                  "url": "https://rickandmorty.fandom.com/wiki/Laser_gun"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The synergy \"Twin Snakes\" is a reference to the game "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Metal Gear Solid: The Twin Snakes",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Metal_Gear_Solid:_The_Twin_Snakes"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " Bug If the player has interacted with "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Shrines",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " the blood particle effect will still be absorbed into the player sprite from some snakes, but the snakes don't die, and it doesn't seem to count towards regaining any health."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Turbo-Gun",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/8/85/Turbo-Gun.png",
    "notes": "Damage increases for the next magazine depending on the number of reload attempts during its reload.",
    "quote": "Repetitive Strain",
    "quality": "C",
    "type": "Automatic",
    "dps": "32-80",
    "magazine_size": "6",
    "ammo_capacity": "180",
    "damage": "8.4 (base)",
    "fire_rate": "0.10",
    "reload_time": "1.0",
    "shot_speed": "21",
    "range": "20",
    "force": "6",
    "spread": "4",
    "class": "SHITTY",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Pressing the reload button while this gun is reloading will increase the damage of its next magazine.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The first 5 button presses each add an additional 20% damage, while any subsequent presses add 10%."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Capped at an additional 300% damage after 25 button presses."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "item_interactions": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Super Hot Watch",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - Allows the player to reach the maximum damage boost every reload with ease."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Requiring a click rate of 25 clicks per second, the player will likely be unable to achieve full damage every time.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "This can be worked around on PC by temporarily binding the player's reload keys to ScrollUp and ScrollDown on the scroll wheel."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Autoclickers make the Turbo-Gun an excellent choice against bosses."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Using "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Duct Tape",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " and the reload ability of this gun will usually override the other guns' projectiles with this one's."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "While "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Reload Speed",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " Boosts may seem counterproductive, items such as "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Oiled Cylinder",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " are actually a net increase in DPS, provided the reload speed stays above 50%.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "If a player wishes to conserve ammo without sacrificing their reload speed boost, the passive can be dropped in the room prior to the enemy/boss room and gone back for later, provided the player scares the "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Resourceful Rat",
                  "kind": "lore"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " firsthand."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The description references the Turbo button that was often present on third-party controllers for older consoles. The turbo button would rapidly keep sending inputs for whatever button it was binded to, allowing the user to constantly press a button faster than they were physically capable. Using a turbo button while reloading this gun would grant a very large damage boost to it."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Hegemony Carbine",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/b/b2/Hegemony_Carbine.png",
    "notes": "Rapidly fires white lasers.",
    "quote": "All The Same",
    "quality": "C",
    "type": "Automatic",
    "dps": "23.0",
    "magazine_size": "25",
    "ammo_capacity": "600",
    "damage": "3.5",
    "fire_rate": "0.10",
    "reload_time": "1.4",
    "shot_speed": "30",
    "range": "50",
    "force": "4",
    "spread": "5",
    "class": "FULLAUTO",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The tagline \"All The Same\" is possibly a reference to the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Rifleman's Creed",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rifleman%27s_Creed"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This gun is used in "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "The Marine",
              "kind": "character"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " past.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "It's possible to bring the "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Galactic Medal of Valor",
                  "kind": "item"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " over to his past, which will allow you to acquire the  "
                },
                {
                  "t": "synref",
                  "v": "Decorated"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " synergy. This is the only synergy you can receive in a past, and it makes the fight among the easiest of any past kill."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Screecher",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/2/2d/Screecher.png",
    "notes": "Rapidly fires piercing sound waves that have a small chance to stun.",
    "quote": "Cover Your Ears!",
    "quality": "C",
    "type": "Automatic",
    "dps": "30.0",
    "magazine_size": "1,000",
    "ammo_capacity": "1,000",
    "damage": "1.5",
    "fire_rate": "0.05",
    "reload_time": "0.6",
    "shot_speed": "12",
    "range": "12",
    "force": "0",
    "spread": "0",
    "class": "SHITTY",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Rapidly fires piercing sound waves that grow in width the further they travel."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Waves have a 1% chance to "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Stun",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " enemies for 3 seconds on impact."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The sound waves destroy "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Chests",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " very quickly; it is not recommended to check for mimics using this gun."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The sound waves also crack the walls of "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Secret Rooms",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " very quickly, making it a great, ammo efficient gun for locating them."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The gun could be a reference to anti-riot weapons such as the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Long Range Acoustic Device",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Long_Range_Acoustic_Device"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " (LRAD), which uses a form of non-kinetic and non-lethal form of crowd dispersal. This also appears to be referenced in the Ammonomicon Entry."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This gun could also be a reference to the Pulse Gun from "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Crimsonland",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Crimsonland"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", which made such an annoying sound that players often had to mute their game, \"losing their purpose and conviction\" in reference to the gun's description. The stun effect is also similar to the Pulse Gun, which confused enemies, except without the added knock-back effect."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This gun could also be a reference to the Address Disruptor from "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Axiom Verge",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Axiom_Verge"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ". The shape of the bullets match that of the disruptor, and both not only make rather weird noises, they also hinder enemies in some way."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This gun could be a reference to the Ripple Laser from the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Gradius",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gradius"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " series. In its first appearance, it took the form of multiple orange \"hoops\" that grew in a stilted manner as they travelled, much like the Screecher. Additionally, the Ripple Laser made a somewhat annoying sound when fired, reminiscent of the Screecher."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Laser Lotus",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/b/b0/Laser_Lotus.png",
    "notes": "Fires piercing lasers.",
    "quote": "Level 5",
    "quality": "A",
    "type": "Semiautomatic",
    "dps": "50.3",
    "magazine_size": "10",
    "ammo_capacity": "150",
    "damage": "16",
    "fire_rate": "0.20",
    "reload_time": "1.38",
    "shot_speed": "45",
    "range": "1,000",
    "force": "26",
    "spread": "5",
    "class": "RIFLE",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Fires blue laser blasts capable of each piercing 1 enemy.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "These lasers electrify any "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Goop",
                  "kind": "lore"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " that they pass over."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The Laser Lotus does "
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "not",
                  "style": "i"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " grant electric immunity, making electrified puddles of water potentially very dangerous to the player."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This gun is a reference to "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Community",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Community_(TV_series)"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ". The character Pierce is a \"Level 5 Laser Lotus\" in his Buddhist renewal community."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Hegemony Rifle",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/f/f4/Hegemony_Rifle.png",
