    "damage": "10",
    "fire_rate": "0.25",
    "reload_time": "1.2",
    "shot_speed": "35",
    "range": "15",
    "force": "15",
    "spread": "13",
    "class": "RIFLE",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Fires blue energy bolts with considerable spread."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This gun appears to be based on the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "DH-17 Carbine",
              "url": "https://starwars.fandom.com/wiki/DH-17_blaster_carbine"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " from "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Star Wars",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The comment about accuracy likely references the historically bad aim of Stormtroopers in "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Star Wars",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ". However, Stormtroopers never used the DH-17.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The weapon's sprites refer to it as \"E12\", which is a reference to the "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ext",
                  "v": "E-11 Carbine",
                  "url": "https://starwars.fandom.com/wiki/E-11_carbine"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " which is the actual standard-issue weapon of Stormtroopers."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Fightsabre",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/c/c2/Fightsabre.png",
    "notes": "Reloading swings the gun around, reflecting nearby bullets. Increases curse by 2.",
    "quote": "Heresy",
    "quality": "1S",
    "type": "Automatic",
    "dps": "29.4",
    "magazine_size": "25",
    "ammo_capacity": "500",
    "damage": "6",
    "fire_rate": "0.15",
    "reload_time": "1.5",
    "shot_speed": "23",
    "range": "50",
    "force": "10",
    "spread": "8",
    "class": "FULLAUTO",
    "curse": 2.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Automatic weapon with a consistent firerate."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "While reloading, the weapon is swung around and reflects nearby enemy bullets back towards their owners.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Reflected bullets deal 10 damage each."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Increases  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Curse",
              "kind": "stat"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " by 2 while in the inventory."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The reflect timing (and animation) is longer than the audio cue would suggest."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Fightsabre can deflect the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "High Dragun",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " rocket attack."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Fightsabre cannot deflect enemy lasers."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Dodge rolling while reloading will deflect any bullets moved through. If timed properly, this can protect the player even during the vulnerable section of the roll."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "When reloading, any nearby enemies and companions will be knocked back a significant distance, although they will be dealt no damage."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "While Fightsabre is reloading, rapidly quick-swapping to another gun and back to the Fightsabre will reset its reload duration. With good timing, this can keep the player in a state of perpetual reload and make them effectively immune to enemy bullets."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The gun's name is a reference to the lightsaber from "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Star Wars",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Star_Wars"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ". Much like the Jedi in Star Wars, the player is able to reflect bullets while swinging the Fightsabre around."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Heresy also refers to the gun's swinging \"attack,\" which is not bullet based and therefore rejected by the Gungeon.  This attack is also why the gun is cursed, similar to the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Huntsman",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The appearance of the gun is based on the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "lasgun",
              "url": "https://warhammer40k.fandom.com/wiki/Lasgun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " from Warhammer 40K.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The description of the weapon being \"ancient\" could also be a reference to Warhammer 40K, where the lasgun is an ancient invention by the time of the 41st Millennium."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The description of the weapon being \"ancient\" is likely a reference to the fact the Star Wars films take place before modern times."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Heresy may also be a reference to Warhammer 40k, as it is common to hear inquisitors from that universe yell \"Heresy!\" at anything that is not made by the imperium, and subsequently shoot the owner."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Fightsabre Training"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " synergy is a reference to a scene in Star Wars Episode IV: A New Hope in which Luke Skywalker trains with a lightsaber while wearing a blast helmet that covers his eyes."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Helix",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/c/c1/Helix.png",
    "notes": "Fires two bullets in a helix pattern.",
    "quote": "Splice 'n' Dice",
    "quality": "C",
    "type": "Semiautomatic",
    "dps": "34.0",
    "magazine_size": "12",
    "ammo_capacity": "250",
    "damage": "15 (7.5x2)",
    "fire_rate": "0.25",
    "reload_time": "2.0",
    "shot_speed": "35",
    "range": "35",
    "force": "10",
    "spread": "7",
    "class": "POISON",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Double Double Helix"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If the player also has "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Helix Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", instead of the Helix Bullets effect being applied to each bullet, Helix's projectiles will be doubled (2 bullets will fire on each side while following the original pattern), damage is increased by 25%, and shot speed is increased by 50%."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Helix is a surprisingly powerful weapon, though difficult to use against regular enemies due to the way it fires. The Helix is best used against large enemies or "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Bosses",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " to maximize accuracy and damage."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "If the player also has "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Remote Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", the spread of the two bullets is reduced as they follow the crosshair, making it easier to use on smaller enemies."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Despite not inflicting poison on enemies, the Helix exists within the POISON "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Guns",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", meaning holding the Helix reduces the player's chances of finding poisoning weapons."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "trivia": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The gun likely refers to "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "DNA",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DNA"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", which has a double helix shape that is similar to the bullets' path. The phrase \"Splice n' Dice\" is a reference to gene splicing."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Laser Rifle",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/0/0d/Laser_Rifle.png",
    "notes": "Fires a burst of three laser beams.",
    "quote": "Blast Off!",
    "quality": "C",
    "type": "Burst",
    "dps": "25.5",
    "magazine_size": "24",
    "ammo_capacity": "500",
    "damage": "5",
    "fire_rate": "0.50",
    "reload_time": "1.2",
    "shot_speed": "200",
    "range": "60",
    "force": "16",
    "spread": "5",
    "class": "FULLAUTO",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Diazepam"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If the player also has "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Muscle Relaxant",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", the gun's damage is increased by 50%"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Laser Light Show"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If the player also has "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Scattershot",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", Laser Rifle becomes blue and gold, and fires 3 sets of 3 shots in a spread per trigger pull. Each shot bounces once."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Starburst Fire"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If the player also has "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "The Emperor",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", firing either The Emperor or Laser Rifle once will cause it to rapidly fire its entire magazine. Increases damage by 20% and doubles fire rate.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "You can cancel the effect by reloading or dodge-rolling while firing."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "trivia": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The weapon is likely a reference to the Laser Rifle from X-COM: UFO Defense, which it strongly resembles in both appearance and function.  In addition, the description may be a reference to the fact that the Laser Rifle could be manufactured for a low cost and sold at a profit, in addition to costing nothing but money; these factors made it an extremely ubiquitous weapon, much like the AK-47 in modern culture."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "It may also be a reference to the more recent X-COM games, which also sport similar looking laser weapons."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "If the player also has "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Vorpal Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " while they have the  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Starburst Fire"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " synergy, it is possible for Vorpal Bullets to trigger multiple times in a row, and will deal massive damage to bosses. With damage increases, it can instantly kill them, too."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
