  {
    "name": "Magic Lamp",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/3/3b/Magic_Lamp.png",
    "notes": "Hitting an enemy three times causes a genie to punch them.",
    "quote": "One Wish, Three Times",
    "quality": "B",
    "type": "Semiautomatic",
    "dps": "63.2",
    "magazine_size": "3",
    "ammo_capacity": "100",
    "damage": "8 (shots) 115 (genie)",
    "fire_rate": "0.50",
    "reload_time": "1.2",
    "shot_speed": "12",
    "range": "1,000",
    "force": "10",
    "spread": "5",
    "class": "SILLY",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " Shooting an enemy causes a mote of blue energy (a wish) to appear above their head. Accumulating three 'wishes' on a single enemy summons a muscular Gunie (Gun Genie) to punch them for massive damage."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " Shooting an enemy summons a Gunie to punch them for large damage. Each shot summons a gunie, with no need to accumulate three wishes."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "item_interactions": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Scattershot",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ",  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Helix Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ",  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Double Vision",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ",  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Table Tech Sight",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - Items that multiply the amount of fired projectiles are extremely useful with the Magic Lamp, as each projectile counts as a wish. Items that fire 3 bullets in one shot can stack all three wishes in a single trigger pull.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Gunies are not affected by the player's "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Damage",
                  "kind": "lore"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " stat, meaning that  "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Scattershot",
                  "kind": "item"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " effectively triples the rate at which Gunies can be summoned, without reducing their damage."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Sweetness and Light"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " +  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Super Hot Watch",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - Switching away from Magic Lamp and switching back while time is stopped resets the guns cooldown, allowing it to be spam-fired."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Ammonomicon entry is a reference to the Disney film "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Aladdin",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", where one of the rules of the Genie character was that he won't kill anybody."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Sweetness and Light"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " synergy is a reference to "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "an English idiom.",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sweetness_and_light"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " The Magic Lamp has the distinction of being item ID 0 in the "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Enter the Gungeon",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " loot database."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Dave Crooks",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " has implied that "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Dodge Roll",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " lead artist "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Joe Harty",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " is responsible for the design of the Magic Lamp."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Teapot",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/8/81/Teapot.png",
    "notes": "While reloading, ignites nearby enemies.",
    "quote": "Monocular Monster",
    "quality": "C",
    "type": "Semiautomatic",
    "dps": "14.7",
    "magazine_size": "12",
    "ammo_capacity": "250",
    "damage": "8.5 15 (pink shot)",
    "fire_rate": "0.40",
    "reload_time": "3.0",
    "shot_speed": "20",
    "range": "1,000",
    "force": "7",
    "spread": "4",
    "class": "PISTOL",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Fires heart-shaped clouds of steam."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The final shot of every magazine is pink, and deals additional damage.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "In "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Co-op",
                  "kind": "lore"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " mode, if the final shot hits the other co-op player it will heal them for half a heart. Healing another player consumes an additional 24 ammo from the Teapot."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "While reloading, the Teapot creates a burning aura in a 5 tile radius around the player, dealing 10 damage per second to enemies caught within and setting them on  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Status Effects",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " (Dur: 4s DPS: 4)."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The AoE effect only lasts as long as the weapon's reload time. This means that any item that decreases reload speed (such as "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Galactic Medal of Valor",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ") nerfs the AoE effect by ending it early.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "This also applies to "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Cog of Battle",
                  "kind": "item"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": ", in which case the effect is also canceled early by the active reload, making it often favorable to not use the active reload to prolong the AoE effect."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Gunslinger's Ashes",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/d/d2/Gunslinger%27s_Ashes.png",
    "notes": "Fires slow homing ghosts that shoot and deal contact damage.",
    "quote": "Spirit, Willing",
    "quality": "C",
    "type": "Semiautomatic",
    "dps": "21.4",
    "magazine_size": "6",
    "ammo_capacity": "80",
    "damage": "Contact: 12 Shots: 15 (5x3)",
    "fire_rate": "0.60",
    "reload_time": "1.2",
    "shot_speed": "1",
    "range": "6",
    "force": "25",
    "spread": "0",
    "class": "SILLY",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Gunslinger's Ashes fires spectral gunslingers that walk slowly forward. Every 2 seconds, these gunslingers will fire a bullet at the nearest enemy which deals 5 damage. These spirits typically dissipate after shooting three times."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The damage dealt by the spirits themselves making contact with enemies is considerably higher than that of their shots."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Due to the high damage dealt by the spirits themselves making contact with enemies, it is most effective to fire this gun at close range."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Despite this gun's name and the spirits' visible resemblance, it is unknown whether the spirit contained within this gun is "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "The Gunslinger",
              "kind": "character"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "'s or not.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "It is most likely his physical body from when the Great Bullet fell."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This gun resembles a canopic jar, specifically Duamutef's, which would contain the stomach."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Ghost With The Most"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " is a reference to the movie Beetlejuice."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Dawn of the Gundead"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " is a reference to the movie Dawn of the Dead."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Luxin Cannon",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/9/94/Luxin_Cannon.png",
    "notes": "Fires laser shots at enemies. The last bullet of magazine fires a crystal, which splits into 5 small crystals on impact.",
    "quote": "Omnichrome",
    "quality": "C",
    "type": "Automatic",
    "dps": "43.8",
    "magazine_size": "30",
    "ammo_capacity": "600",
    "damage": "4.5",
    "fire_rate": "0.07",
    "reload_time": "1.5",
    "shot_speed": "60",
    "range": "1,000",
    "force": "10",
    "spread": "6",
    "class": "FULLAUTO",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This gun is a reference to The Lightbringer book series by "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Brent Weeks",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Brent_Weeks"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ". The main character's last name is Guile, he is the Prism, Luxin is the name of the solidified light that is used by the magic users of that world, and Lord Omnichrome is a major antagonist of the series."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "\"Falsely rumored to have natural healing abilities\" is a reference to "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "crystal healing",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Crystal_healing"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", a pseudoscientific alternative medicine technique that employs stones and crystals."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "The Return"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " synergy is a reference to Ganon from the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Legend of Zelda",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Legend_Of_Zelda"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " video game series. The synergy being named \"The Return\" may be a reference to the game-over screen from Legend of Zelda 2: Adventure of Link, which included the line \"RETURN OF GANON\"."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Luxin Cannon will display a special reload animation if the clip is completely empty, where the broken tip reforms.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "If the player dodge rolls during the animation, the gun will briefly disappear but the reforming section will remain visible. Its animation will pause for the duration of the roll."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Gunther",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/3/3d/Gunther.png",
    "notes": "Cannot be used to reveal hidden walls. Grows stronger with each room cleared.",
    "quote": "Jealous Weapon",
    "quality": "1S",
    "type": "Semiautomatic",
    "dps": "34.6-69.2",
