  {
    "name": "Flame Hand",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/9/9d/Flame_Hand.png",
    "notes": "Fires fireballs that pierce enemies and have a chance to set enemies on fire.",
    "quote": "2D6 + Int Mod",
    "quality": "B",
    "type": "Semiautomatic",
    "dps": "23.6",
    "magazine_size": "100",
    "ammo_capacity": "200",
    "damage": "Varying (~11.7)",
    "fire_rate": "0.50",
    "reload_time": "0.0",
    "shot_speed": "23",
    "range": "1,000",
    "force": "35",
    "spread": "0",
    "class": "FIRE",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Flings piercing fireballs that set enemies on  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Status Effects",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " (Dur: 4s DPS: 4)."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The damage dealt by the gun is approximately equal to 2d6 * 1.3846 + 2, which is an average of 11.7 damage per shot. The possible damage values and their frequencies are:"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "When playing as "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "The Robot",
              "kind": "character"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", the gun deals an extra 1 damage, implying that the Robot has a higher intelligence modifier than other characters."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "When playing as "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "The Bullet",
              "kind": "character"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", the gun deals 1 less damage, implying that the Bullet has a lower intelligence modifier than other characters."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The scale of each fireball is proportional to the result of the dice roll, with larger fireballs dealing greater damage."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Flings burning, bouncing balls of fire that are affected by gravity, travelling in arcs."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "item_interactions": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Chance Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " /  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Duct Tape",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "- Projectiles from other guns also have their damage and scale multiplied when fired out of the Flame Hand."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "As the Flame Hand deals fire-type damage, it deals no damage to "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Muzzle Wisp",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " and "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Muzzle Flare",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " Due to the high knockback and large size of the fireballs, they can hit the same enemy multiple times."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "2D6 + Int mod",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " is a reference to "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Dungeons and Dragons",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dungeons_and_Dragons"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "In D&D, \"2D6\" means to roll two six sided dice and \"Int mod\" to add a character's intelligence modifier."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The \"Maximize Spell\" synergy is another reference to a feat in Dungeons and Dragons, which maximizes all of the variable numeric effects of a chosen spell."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The \"Phoenix Up\" synergy is likely a reference to the item Phoenix Down from the "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Final Fantasy",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " series of games."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The flames turning green is a reference to the long running live play Dungeons and Dragons game "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Acquisitions Incorporated.",
              "style": "i"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Sunlight Javelin",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/1/11/Sunlight_Javelin.png",
    "notes": "Shoots fiery javelins that make enemies take damage over time.",
    "quote": "Brilliant Aura",
    "quality": "B",
    "type": "Charged",
    "dps": "30.0",
    "magazine_size": "100",
    "ammo_capacity": "150",
    "damage": "45",
    "fire_rate": "1.00",
    "reload_time": "0.0",
    "shot_speed": "120",
    "range": "1,000",
    "force": "90",
    "spread": "0",
    "class": "FIRE",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "\\o/"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - While holding "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Gun Soul",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " or "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Old Knight's Flask",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", when Sunlight Javelin's initial impact kills an enemy, it will spawn a circular zone that ignites all enemies within it. This does not apply to the damage-over-time effect."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This gun is an excellent room clearing weapon, as it one-shots most enemies even into the Forge, and is extremely accurate and ammo-efficient."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This gun can be reloaded immediately after firing to activate "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Hip Holster",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " if above 100 ammo."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "trivia": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This gun is a reference to the Sunlight Spear, a miracle in the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Dark Souls",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dark_Souls"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " series whereby the caster hurls a bolt of lightning, though the Dark Souls version does not deal damage over time.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "\"Grossly incandescent\" and \"brilliant aura\" is reference to Solaire, an NPC from Dark Souls who says this quote (\"If only I could be so grossly incandescent\", \"Spot my summon signature easily by its brilliant aura\" )."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Solaire introduces the player to co-op in Dark Souls, which is referenced by both the description text and the unlock methods both being forms of cooperation."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Both the "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Gun Soul",
                  "kind": "item"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " and "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Old Knight's Flask",
                  "kind": "item"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": ", the items which complete the \\o/ synergy, are also references to Dark Souls."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The \"\\o/\" synergy name is a reference to the \"praise the sun\" gesture in Dark Souls."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": []
        },
        {
          "tokens": []
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Prior to patch "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "V2.1.5",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " the game would not set the necessary flag to unlock this gun, therefore making it impossible to unlock without the use of a save editor or mod."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This weapon can also be used to damage bosses when disappeared, such as "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Cannonbalrog",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " or the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "High Priest",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ".\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Ammoconda",
                  "kind": "unresolved"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " must be hit in the head to apply the glowing effect."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This weapon is proficient at room clearing with items that grant piercing or bouncing effects such as "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Ghost Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " or "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Bouncy Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Machine Fist",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/5/5a/Machine_Fist.png",
    "notes": "Reloading alternates between firing a gatling gun, and a single shot exploding rocket punch that is guided by the player's reticle. The rocket punch consumes 10 ammo.",
    "quote": "Avalanche Of Bullets",
    "quality": "A",
    "type": "Automatic",
    "dps": "46.0",
    "magazine_size": "50 (gun) 1 (rocket)",
    "ammo_capacity": "500",
    "damage": "Bullet: 4 Rocket: 20 (impact) + 30 (explosion)",
    "fire_rate": "0.07",
    "reload_time": "1.0",
    "shot_speed": "27",
    "range": "1,000",
    "force": "15",
    "spread": "6",
    "class": "FULLAUTO",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "With keyboard and mouse controls, the rocket fist will home in towards the players cursor."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "With gamepad controls, the rocket will update its direction to match the currently held aim direction on the controller."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This homing rocket consumes 10 ammo when fired, instead of 1."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Like other single shot weapons, firing a rocket fist causes the player to reload the gun immediately after, transforming it."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "In order to reload, the gun must have remaining ammo greater than the size of the magazine. Therefore, once the last of the gun's ammo is loaded in machine gun mode, none of that ammo can be used for rocket punches, even if there is more than 10 ammo remaining."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This gun is a reference to a weapon of the same name from "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Final Fantasy VII",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Final_Fantasy_VII"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " along with its user, Barret, and the group of eco-guerilla fighters he founded: \"Avalanche\".\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The flavor text is a reference to Barret's Subplot with his former friend Dyne who also had a Machine Fist installed."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The synergy  "
                },
                {
                  "t": "synref",
                  "v": "that &^#$# 'pizza'"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " is a reference to an insult Barret once directed at the city of Midgar, calling it \"that &^#$# 'pizza'\", referring to the way that the upper level of the city was built on an enormous circular metal plate suspended above the lower level of the city."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " Bug Dropping the Machine Fist while it is in rocket mode, and then picking it back up will cause it to visually return to minigun mode. This bug is purely visual, as the gun will still fire a rocket, and will correct itself next reload."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
