  {
    "name": "Anvillain",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/2/28/Anvillain.png",
    "notes": "Fires piercing anvils with strong knockback and a chance to stun .",
    "quote": "Practical And Safe",
    "quality": "C",
    "type": "Charged",
    "dps": "47.7",
    "magazine_size": "3",
    "ammo_capacity": "60",
    "damage": "35",
    "fire_rate": "0.10",
    "reload_time": "0.5",
    "shot_speed": "20",
    "range": "1,000",
    "force": "8",
    "spread": "5",
    "class": "CHARGE",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This gun can reliably hit an enemy twice due to high knockback, slow travel speed, and pierce."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This guns projectiles are among the few affected by gravity.."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Anvillain is a reference to the "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Looney Tunes",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " cartoon, "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Wile E. Coyote and the Road Runner",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ". Anvils were a common running gag within the series, where the lead villain (Wile E.) would order anvils from the ACME corporation in an attempt to catch the Road Runner. ACME delivers their products in crates, much like this weapon.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The item's quote and description is an ironic jab to the Coyote's constant failures with catching the Road Runner, which almost always results in his own devices harming himself."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Fossilized Gun",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/7/77/Fossilized_Gun.png",
    "notes": "Fires a stream of oil that leaves oil puddles on floor. Reloading spits fire , which can ignite the oil.",
    "quote": "Proof That Guns Once Existed",
    "quality": "D",
    "type": "Beam",
    "dps": "15.0",
    "magazine_size": "500",
    "ammo_capacity": "500",
    "damage": "15/s",
    "fire_rate": "0.10",
    "reload_time": "N/A",
    "shot_speed": "15",
    "range": "20",
    "force": "40",
    "spread": "0",
    "class": "FIRE",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "item_interactions": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Bouncy Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - The bouncing effect is extremely effective at coating whole rooms in oil. Additionally, oil streams that bounce back towards the player will not leave oil goop underneath them, leaving a safe patch in which to stand while igniting the oil."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Ring of Fire Resistance",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ",  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Hazmat Suit",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ",  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Wax Wings",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ",  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Ring of Ethereal Form",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ",  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Cat Bullet King Throne",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - These items provide immunity to burning goop, rendering the Fossilized Gun significantly safer to use."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Jetpack",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - In addition to providing flight and safety from the fire, the Jetpack will also automatically ignite goop underneath the player while active."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Sponge",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - The sponge will remove oil in a radius around the player, making the Fossilized Gun safer to use, but also potentially reducing its effectiveness."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The plume of flame belched by the Fossilized Gun when reloading solely has the effect of igniting flammable "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Goop",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ". It does not harm enemies, trigger explosive barrels, or anger "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Bello",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ". Additionally, the Fossilized Gun can be reloaded and made to spit fire regardless of its current ammo count- it can even be used this way when empty."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Is is possible to pre-clear rooms by firing blindly into them from the doorway without fully entering, and then igniting the placed oil. This strategy is however inconsistent due to the high variance in room layouts in Enter the Gungeon."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This gun is a combined reference to dinosaur fossils, fossil fuels (ie; oil, so named because it is formed from organic remains), and fire-breathing dragons."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " Bug Pausing the game for a long time while Fossilized Gun oil streams are mid-flight can result in severe lag when un-pausing the game. This is because the streams continue to place oil underneath themselves while the game is paused, resulting in a large number of goop visual effects which all attempt to play at once when the game is unpaused."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
