  {
    "name": "Plunger",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/3/30/Plunger.png",
    "notes": "Fires a continuous stream of poison. Has a chance to poison enemies and leaves poison puddles on impact.",
    "quote": "Take Your Best Shot!",
    "quality": "C",
    "type": "Beam",
    "dps": "5.0",
    "magazine_size": "500",
    "ammo_capacity": "500",
    "damage": "5/s",
    "fire_rate": "0.10",
    "reload_time": "N/A",
    "shot_speed": "20",
    "range": "20",
    "force": "40",
    "spread": "0",
    "class": "POISON",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Plunger fires a constant stream of green liquid that inflicts the poison "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Status Effects",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " on enemies after 0.5 seconds of contact with the beam. Additionally, this poison stream leaves a pool of toxic goop on the ground after hitting an enemy or wall."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Reloading the Plunger while standing on any goop, including goop that it has created, fully restores the guns ammo."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "item_interactions": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Sponge",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - Absorbs goop below the player, preventing them from accidentally poisoning themselves with the Plunger- but also preventing them from being able to use its goop ammo recovery."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Wax Wings",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ",  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Jetpack",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ",  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Ring of Ethereal Form",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ",  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Cat Bullet King Throne",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - Flight of any form prevents the player from using the goop ammo recovery of the Plunger, as they are unable to stand on goop."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Duct Tape",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - Duct taping other weapons to the Plunger is extremely ammo efficient, as both guns will benefit from the Plungers goop ammo recovery."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The phrase "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Médecins Sans Diplôme",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " in the description is French for "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Doctors Without Diplomas.",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " This is a reference to the real-life organisation "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Doctors Without Borders",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", commonly known as "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Médecins",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Sans Frontières.",
              "style": "i"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " Bug The diacritic marks on é and ô are not supported by Enter the Gungeons font, causing \"Médecins Sans Diplôme\" to display as \"Mdecins Sans Diplme\" when read ingame."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Raiden Coil",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/1/1e/Raiden_Coil.png",
    "notes": "Fires a continuous laser bean that homes in on all on-screen enemies one by one.",
    "quote": "Shoot Em' Up",
    "quality": "A",
    "type": "Beam",
    "dps": "17.5",
    "magazine_size": "500",
    "ammo_capacity": "500",
    "damage": "17.5/s",
    "fire_rate": "0.10",
    "reload_time": "N/A",
    "shot_speed": "",
    "range": "30",
    "force": "10",
    "spread": "5",
    "class": "SILLY",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Like other guns, this will not fire if the player is up against a wall and trying to shoot into the wall, even though this gun shoots through walls."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Backup Gun",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " indirectly doubles this gun's damage due to its direct homing."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This gun is a large reference to the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Raiden",
              "url": "http://raidenbase.wikia.com/wiki/Raiden_IV#Main_shots"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " series.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Its name and sole synergy both refer to the series.\n"
                }
              ],
              "sub": [
                {
                  "tokens": [
                    {
                      "t": "text",
                      "v": "Additionally, the synergy grants it wings similar to the fighter airplanes featured in the game."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Its color scheme matches the titular ship featured in Raiden."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Its tagline, \"Shoot Em' Up\", refers to the genre that the series belongs to."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The gun's behavior mimics the behavior of the purple \"toothpaste laser\" (officially known as Bend Plasma) from "
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Raiden II",
                  "style": "i"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " onward."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "According to the Ammonomicon, this gun was designed to be attached to a combat vehicle, but is available as a man-portable weapon. It shares this trait with the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Com4nd0",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " and the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Void Core Cannon",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Moonscraper",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/b/ba/Moonscraper.png",
