  {
    "name": "Light Gun",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/4/44/Light_Gun.png",
    "notes": "Fires zaps of light beam at enemies. The last bullet in the magazine is a duck, which will automatically seek out the nearest enemy and attack them.",
    "quote": "Third-Party",
    "quality": "B",
    "type": "Semiautomatic",
    "dps": "28.8",
    "magazine_size": "6",
    "ammo_capacity": "150",
    "damage": "7",
    "fire_rate": "0.20",
    "reload_time": "1.0",
    "shot_speed": "400",
    "range": "60",
    "force": "30",
    "spread": "5",
    "class": "SILLY",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Fires an incredibly fast zap of white light capable of piercing through enemies."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The final bullet in each magazine is a mallard duck, which automatically seeks out enemies to attack them. This duck is capable of piercing once, and  has extremely tight homing.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Like all other piercing projectiles, the duck's damage will halve after piercing an enemy for the first time."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This gun is a reference to the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "NES Zapper",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/NES_Zapper"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ".\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The duck being shot is a reference to "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ext",
                  "v": "Duck Hunt",
                  "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Duck_Hunt"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": ", one of the most well-known games to use the NES Zapper."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The gun's appearance with the synergy  "
                },
                {
                  "t": "synref",
                  "v": "Peripheral Vision"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " is a reference to the NES Zapper's original US colors, rather than the redesigned orange."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The description heavily implies that the Light Gun originally belonged to "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "The Cultist",
              "kind": "character"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The synergy  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Peripheral Vision"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " is a reference to the NES Zapper being sold as a peripheral for the NES. The dog that appears is a reference to the NES game Duck Hunt."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Dueling Laser",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/a/af/Dueling_Laser.png",
    "notes": "Fires a large, piercing, high-damage laser beam. Recharges like an active item after each shot.",
    "quote": "More interesting this way!",
    "quality": "B",
    "type": "Semiautomatic",
    "dps": "70.4",
    "magazine_size": "1",
    "ammo_capacity": "",
    "damage": "100",
    "fire_rate": "N/A",
    "reload_time": "1.0",
    "shot_speed": "?",
    "range": "?",
    "force": "?",
    "spread": "?",
    "class": "SILLY",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Banshee Cry"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If the player has "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Screecher",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", it fires three sound waves per shot instead of one."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Death Square"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If the player has "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Dueling Pistol",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", damaging enemies with the Dueling Pistol rapidly recharges the Dueling Laser."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "During a "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Sorceress",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", the Dueling Laser does not recharge like an active item. Instead, it automatically reloads in around 7 seconds."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Since it has infinite ammo, it cannot reveal secret rooms, nor be fed to "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Muncher",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This gun is affected by "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Ice Cube",
