                  "v": " it will be recharged immediately, but it often won’t update until you switch weapons and switch back"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "trivia": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This gun is a reference to the Dueling Laser Pistol from the book "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Dying of the Light",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dying_of_the_Light_(Martin_novel)"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", the first novel of "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "George R. R. Martin",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/George_R._R._Martin"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The sound effect for the Dueling Laser when it is fully charged up is the same sound effect as the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Gun That Can Kill The Past",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Wood Beam",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/7/78/Wood_Beam.png",
    "notes": "Melee weapon that extends itself to hit enemies. Increases curse by 1.",
    "quote": "Speak Softly",
    "quality": "B",
    "type": "Beam",
    "dps": "10.0 (no swing)",
    "magazine_size": "100",
    "ammo_capacity": "900",
    "damage": "Based on swing speed (Max: 26)",
    "fire_rate": "1.0",
    "reload_time": "0.9",
    "shot_speed": "40",
    "range": "10",
    "force": "?",
    "spread": "?",
    "class": "SHITTY",
    "curse": 1.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "While the trigger is held, this gun will extend in the form of a stiff beam until reaching the end of its range."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Swinging the beam into enemies deals considerably more damage and knockback than direct hits.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The beam deals 1 damage per second when used to hit directly like a normal beam weapon."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Deals 2, 8, 16, or 26 damage when swung into enemies, depending on how fast it is swung."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Expends 1 ammo per second while fired, and some ammo every time it is swung into enemies."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Increases  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Curse",
              "kind": "stat"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " by 1."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "item_interactions": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Bouncy Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - When ricocheting off walls, the range of the ricocheting beam is reset- allowing it to reach greater distances."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Wood Beam deals no damage to chests. For this reason, it can be an excellent way to check for "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Mimic",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ". Its length can also bypass locked doors, to check if the chest inside is a mimic."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Wood Beam's damage multiplier from swing speed applies after "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Unity",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "'s flat damage bonus. This makes Unity especially effective with Wood Beam, as Unity's damage bonus will be multiplied by 2, 8, 16, or 26 depending on how fast the beam is swung."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Wood Beam can reveal secret rooms, but it is ineffective at doing so, as it must be continuously fired at a wall for a long time before cracks begin to show."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Wood Beam's pickup quote is a reference to Teddy Roosevelt's \"speak softly and carry a big stick\" ideology."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Wood Beam being unlocked by donating blood to the vampire is a reference to vampire's alleged weakness to a wooden stake through the heart."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Wood Beam is a reference to a popular internet hoax/joke where users explained unlocking it as a secret, ultimate weapon in "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Super Metroid",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Super_Metroid"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ",",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " usually by having the player do ridiculous things."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Wood Beam's name is a pun, as it is a beam type weapon, but also a literal beam of wood."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The weapon increases "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Curse",
              "kind": "stat"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " while being carried, as melee weapons are considered sacrilege in "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "The Gungeon",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
