  {
    "name": "Buzzkill",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/7/7e/Buzzkill.png",
    "notes": "Fires piercing, bouncing sawblades.",
    "quote": "Sawed On!",
    "quality": "C",
    "type": "Semiautomatic",
    "dps": "24.7",
    "magazine_size": "12",
    "ammo_capacity": "350",
    "damage": "7",
    "fire_rate": "0.20",
    "reload_time": "1.2",
    "shot_speed": "25",
    "range": "1,000",
    "force": "10",
    "spread": "5",
    "class": "SHITTY",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Get Equipped With -M-"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If the player has "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Megahand",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", enables Metal Blade mode on Megahand, which fires Buzzkill shots while uncharged. Modes can be switched by reloading the Megahand with a full magazine."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "I Studied The Blade"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If the player has "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Super Meat Gun",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", the two guns are dual wielded."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Not So Sawed-Off"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If the player has "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Rattler",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Regular Shotgun",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", or "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Winchester",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", Buzzkill's saw blades move slower and are linked with lightning."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "trivia": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Buzzkill is slang for someone who ruins fun (in this case, the gun's designer from the Ammonomicon entry), and the gun's name is also a portmanteau of buzzsaw and kill."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The pickup text \"Sawed On!\" is a play on words, based on a \"sawed-off shotgun.\""
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "May be a reference to the Disc Gun in the game "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Nuclear Throne",
              "url": "http://nuclearthrone.com/"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " which also fires ricocheting saw blades."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This item may be a reference to the buzz blades from Ratchet And Clank: Tools Of Destruction."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "I Studied The Blade is a line from an infamously cringey post saying that while you were doing X, Y, and Z, the poster had been \"studying the blade,\" in reference to a katana."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Strangely, Not So Sawed-Off does not synergize with the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Sawed-Off",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " despite its name being in the title of the synergy. This might be because it is one of "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "The Convict",
              "kind": "character"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "'s starting items, although it is always unlocked for other characters to use."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Tear Jerker",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/2/2b/Tear_Jerker.png",
    "notes": "Fires tears that leave behind puddles of water.",
    "quote": "Q_Q",
    "quality": "C",
    "type": "Semiautomatic",
    "dps": "26.0",
    "magazine_size": "20",
    "ammo_capacity": "350",
    "damage": "7",
    "fire_rate": "0.22",
    "reload_time": "1.2",
    "shot_speed": "15",
    "range": "15",
    "force": "10",
    "spread": "0",
    "class": "SHITTY",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Shoots tears that pierce enemies and leave puddles of "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Goop",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " on collision.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The direction of these tears is affected by the player's momentum, meaning that tears angle in the direction the player is moving."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "item_interactions": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Super Hot Watch",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - Because Super Hot Watch requires the player to move to progress time, it can interfere with the Tear Jerker's projectiles due to them inheriting the players momentum. This makes the Tear Jerker extremely difficult to use."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Because the Tear Jerker uses the "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Water",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " damage type, it deals 2x damage to "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Muzzle Wisp",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " and "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Muzzle Flare",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", and does not ignite "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Coaler",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ".\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The Tear Jerker also puts out decorative torches and burning skeletons."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This gun and both of its synergies are references to "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "The Binding of Isaac",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Binding_of_Isaac_(video_game)"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ". The tears inheriting the player's momentum is based upon how player projectiles work in The Binding of Isaac.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The name of the  "
                },
                {
                  "t": "synref",
                  "v": "Wrath Of The Blam"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " synergy is a reference to "
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Wrath of the Lamb",
                  "style": "i"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": ", one of The Binding of Isaac's DLCs."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The maximum ammo capacity of 350 could be a reference to Isaac having a base starting damage of 3.50."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Starpew",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/0/0a/Starpew.png",
    "notes": "Fires water bubbles. Can be charged to increase the number of bubbles fired in fixed pattern.",
    "quote": "Reap And Sow",
    "quality": "A",
    "type": "Charged",
    "dps": "35-93. 3",
    "magazine_size": "1",
    "ammo_capacity": "100",
    "damage": "5",
    "fire_rate": "0.20",
    "reload_time": "1.0",
    "shot_speed": "?",
    "range": "?",
    "force": "?",
    "spread": "?",
    "class": "CHARGE",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Charges up to fire droplets of water. This gun has multiple levels of charge, and each level increases the number of droplets fired.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "No Charge - Fires a single droplet."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "0.25 Second Charge - Fires 3 droplets in a line."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "0.5 Second Charge - Fires 5 droplets in a line."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "0.75 Second Charge - Fires 3 parallel lines of 3 droplets each, resulting in 9 total droplets.\n"
                }
              ],
              "sub": [
                {
                  "tokens": [
                    {
                      "t": "text",
                      "v": " Bug After firing the Starpew once on a floor, two of the droplets that are part of this formation will no longer be fired, reducing the number of droplets to 7."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "1 Second Charge - Fires 3 parallel lines of 6 droplets each, resulting in 18 total droplets.\n"
                }
              ],
              "sub": [
                {
                  "tokens": [
                    {
                      "t": "text",
                      "v": " Bug After firing the Starpew once on a floor, two of the droplets that are part of this formation will no longer be fired, reducing the number of droplets to 16."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Droplets are fired in an evenly spaced grid, offset horizontally and vertically from the actual barrel of the Starpew.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "This makes it exceptionally easy to spawn these projectiles "
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "inside",
                  "style": "i"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " enemies, instantly damaging them."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "This also allows the Starpew to effectively shoot through some walls and obstacles by creating droplets on the other side."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Droplets create a pool of "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Goop",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " when splashing into a wall, object, or enemy. This allows them to extinguish "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Chest",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " fuses and the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Fireplace",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Because the Starpew uses the "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Water",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " damage type, it deals 2x damage to  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Muzzle Wisp",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " and  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Muzzle Flare",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", and does not ignite  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Coaler",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ".\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The Starpew also puts out decorative torches and burning skeletons."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Consumes 1 ammo per shot regardless of how long it is charged."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "item_interactions": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Backup Gun",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - Higher charge levels of the Starpew will create extra droplets at the "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "same starting position",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " as the original bullets, rather than being backwards offset by the barrel itself. This makes it especially easy to spawn twice the number of droplets "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "inside",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " an enemy, dealing a large amount of damage."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Double Vision",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - While active, Double Vision doubles the bullet output of the Starpew without meaningfully increasing it's spread, allowing for massive dps."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This gun is a reference to the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Watering Can",
              "url": "https://stardewvalleywiki.com/Watering_Cans"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " tool in the game "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Stardew Valley",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", a tile-based agricultural game. As the player upgrades their watering can, they can 'charge' it to cover a greater area of farmland. This is mirrored in the Starpew creating a wider grid of water projectiles the longer it is charged."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Originally, Starpew's magazine size was 100 and it did not need to reload. This was changed in the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Advanced Gungeons & Draguns Update",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", at which point it instead had a magazine size of 1, effectively slowing down the fire rate by requiring a reload after every shot. This change was reverted in "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "A Farewell to Arms",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", and the charging speed was increased as well, meaning it can fire fully-charged shots faster and has less delay in between them."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Eye of the Beholster",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/4/4c/Eye_of_the_Beholster.png",
    "notes": "The last shot of each clip spawns a friendly Beadie .",
    "quote": "What A Beauty!",
    "quality": "B",
    "type": "Semiautomatic",
    "dps": "23.2",
    "magazine_size": "12",
    "ammo_capacity": "300",
    "damage": "6",
    "fire_rate": "0.15",
    "reload_time": "1.2",
    "shot_speed": "200",
    "range": "1,000",
    "force": "4",
    "spread": "4",
    "class": "SILLY",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Fires instant laser projectiles."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The final shot of each cylinder fires a projectile shaped like a pink "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Beadie",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ". This beadie-projectile moves slowly forwards, periodically firing more bullets in the direction of the nearest enemy."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Beholster",
              "kind": "shrine"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " wields this gun.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "As it is held by the Beholster, it can be placed on the "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Beholster Shrine?action=edit&redlink=1",
                  "kind": "unresolved"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The friendly Beadie spawned at the end of each cylinder is actually a bullet, not a charmed enemy. This is why the player cannot kill it and why it only travels in a straight line.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Since the Beadie shot has a lot of piercing and is very slow, this can do a lot of damage to a boss when shot up close."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "This also means that the summoned Beadies are affected by bullet modifiers."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "With "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Orbital Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", missed non-Beadie shots will be invisible but still orbit the player."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This gun's pickup quote is a reference to the common saying \"beauty is in the eye of the beholder\"."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This gun's reload prompt is special, saying \"Behold\" instead of \"Reload\""
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Molotov Launcher",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/0/03/Molotov_Launcher.png",
    "notes": "Fires molotovs that create fire puddles on impact.",
    "quote": "Exactly What You Think",
    "quality": "C",
    "type": "Semiautomatic",
    "dps": "2.4",
    "magazine_size": "1",
    "ammo_capacity": "80",
    "damage": "6",
    "fire_rate": "1.50",
    "reload_time": "2.5",
    "shot_speed": "18",
    "range": "35",
    "force": "13",
    "spread": "5",
    "class": "FIRE",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Unlike the regular "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Molotov",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", the Molotov Launcher will work in "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "The Gorgun",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "'s arena."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Child projectiles created by "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Flak Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " will not create puddles of fire."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Extra shots fired by "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Hip Holster",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " will usually not create puddles of fire, however it rarely still does."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Takes three shots to reveal breakable wall, but the pool of flames just visible in the darkness even if the wall is not broken."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Having a long charge time and dealing almost exclusively flame damage, the Molotov Launcher is by far the lowest DPS gun in the game, dealing barely over half the damage of the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "3rd Party Controller",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " or "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Plunger",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " without poison damage when used against fire resistant "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Enemies",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "/"
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Bosses",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " such as "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Bullet King",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Glass Cannon",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/6/6e/Glass_Cannon.png",
    "notes": "Charges to fire a powerful piercing laser beam. Loses all ammo upon taking damage.",
    "quote": "Fragile, Fatal",
    "quality": "C",
    "type": "Charged",
    "dps": "50.0",
    "magazine_size": "1",
    "ammo_capacity": "25",
    "damage": "140",
    "fire_rate": "1.00",
    "reload_time": "2.0",
    "shot_speed": "600",
    "range": "1,000",
    "force": "20",
    "spread": "0",
    "class": "CHARGE",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Charges up to shoot a powerful piercing bolt of light.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "This projectile ignores the "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Bosses",
                  "kind": "lore"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "If the player takes damage while holding the Glass Cannon it will shatter, losing all its ammunition."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "item_interactions": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Lich's Eye Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - Grants the  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Max Pane"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " synergy permanently, causing the Glass Cannon to never break no matter how much damage is taken."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Holey Grail",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If Holey Grail was picked up "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "after",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " the Glass Cannon, it will restore part of the Glass Cannons ammo after the player takes damage, effectively preventing it from shattering.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "This effect "
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "does not work",
                  "style": "i"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " if the Holey Grail was picked up first, however this order can be easily rectified by dropping the Holey Grail and picking it up again."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "While shattered (empty due to taking damage), the Glass Cannon has no sprite, effectively making it invisible.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "If the Glass Cannon is emptied by using up its ammo reserve instead of taking damage, the gun remains unshattered and can be dropped and retrieved like any other. It can still be shattered if held while taking damage."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Unlike the "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Balloon Gun",
                  "kind": "gun"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": ", it's not possible to drop the weapon while it's shattered. This also makes selling it to the "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Sell Creep",
                  "kind": "lore"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " impossible in this state."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "However, it can still be "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Guns",
                  "kind": "lore"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": ". If the player throws the Glass Cannon while it is shattered, the gun will disappear, making retrieving it impossible."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "When in co-op mode, the  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Max Pane"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " synergy activates regardless of who has which item. If the wielder of the cannon doesn't have the stone, they can receive damage while holding the cannon and it will not shatter."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The gun is a reference to the Glass Cannon archetype in video games, referring to characters with high damage but low defense."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The synergy  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Max Pane"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " is a play on the title of the video game series "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Max Payne",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Both Glass Cannon and "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Void Core Cannon",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " have \"Cannon\" in their name, yet do not trigger the  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "The Return"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " synergy."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "With the Max Pane synergy, the game enters slow motion when hit, as a reference to Max Payne's bullet time feature."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Since the shattered sprite is invisible, if the player dies while the Glass Cannon is popped, it will appear to not be shown in their list of owned items on the end screen."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Throwing a shattered Glass Cannon doesn't show a weapon indicator on the map, indicating that throwing a shattered Glass Cannon really makes it disappear."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Shock Rifle",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/6/6a/Shock_Rifle.png",
    "notes": "Fires a zap of electricity.",
    "quote": "Zap",
    "quality": "B",
    "type": "Semiautomatic",
    "dps": "27.9",
    "magazine_size": "15",
    "ammo_capacity": "250",
    "damage": "8",
    "fire_rate": "0.20",
    "reload_time": "1.5",
    "shot_speed": "140",
    "range": "1,000",
    "force": "20",
    "spread": "5",
    "class": "RIFLE",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Assault and Battery"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If the player also has the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "M16",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", the guns are dual wielded."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Battery Powered"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If the player has "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "R2G2",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " or "
            },
