              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", Shock Rifle gains a smartphone battery-esque look and automatically regenerates 1 ammo every 4 seconds."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "When fired at a "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Gunjurer",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", the bullets are fired back at a slower speed. Instead of being fired back as a laser-like bullet, it now looks like a thunder bolt."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "trivia": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Unused and Cut Content",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If the player has "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Battery Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", shot speed is doubled. Likely removed because it includes a starting item."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Unused and Cut Content",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - Prior to the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Advanced Gungeons & Draguns Update",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", this gun was included in  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Diazepam"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This gun is stylized to look like an oversized Duracell AA Battery."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Bait Launcher",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/c/ca/Bait_Launcher.png",
    "notes": "Fires a steak that causes a tiger to appear and maul the target.",
    "quote": "Meat Your Maker",
    "quality": "C",
    "type": "Charged",
    "dps": "40.0",
    "magazine_size": "1",
    "ammo_capacity": "60",
    "damage": "10 (Steak) + 50 (Tiger)",
    "fire_rate": "0.50",
    "reload_time": "1.0",
    "shot_speed": "20",
    "range": "1,000",
    "force": "8",
    "spread": "5",
    "class": "SILLY",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Launches steaks.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Upon impact, a tiger will appear from off screen and run to the nearest enemy, mauling them before disappearing."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Steaks leave a small pool of "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Goop",
                  "kind": "lore"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " (likely intended to represent blood) upon landing."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "As blobulon goop is non-flammable, it is able to douse the "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Fireplace",
                  "kind": "unresolved"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " in the "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Keep of the Lead Lord",
                  "kind": "lore"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " as well as "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Chest",
                  "kind": "lore"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " fuses."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The tiger that appears won't necessarily chase the meat, but rather targets the enemy closest to where it lands, no matter how far the target actually is from the meat. This is very useful for attacking enemies from behind cover, as the damage dealt by the steaks themselves is negligible.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "If the player has "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Snowballets",
                  "kind": "item"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": ", the tigers' damage output will scale as their size increases. The tigers can get quite large, occupying a majority of the screen."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "If there's a "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Wall Mimic",
                  "kind": "unresolved"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " in the room, the tiger might attack it, whether or not it has already been revealed."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "If the meat is caught by a "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Gunjurer",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", the tiger that appears will attack the player instead."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "If a "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Lead Maiden",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " closes before the tiger can attack it, multiple tigers will spawn on the Lead Maiden and try to attack it, however they will deal no damage and despawn when it opens."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Enemies being attacked by tigers will have a "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Stun",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " animation."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Can be used to put out the fireplace."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The weapon may be a reference to "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Far Cry 4",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Far_Cry_4"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " where the player could throw bait to attract a random predator (including tigers). The predator would often proceed to maul anyone nearby."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Brick Breaker",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/5/51/Brick_Breaker.png",
    "notes": "Fires piercing turtle shells that bounce off of walls.",
    "quote": "Wrong Kind Of Mortar",
    "quality": "C",
    "type": "Semiautomatic",
    "dps": "15.6",
    "magazine_size": "5",
    "ammo_capacity": "200",
    "damage": "10",
    "fire_rate": "0.50",
    "reload_time": "1.2",
    "shot_speed": "20",
    "range": "1,000",
    "force": "10",
    "spread": "2",
    "class": "SILLY",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " Shells can also pierce up to 4 times.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " In "
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Exit the Gungeon",
                  "style": "i"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": ", instead of piercing through enemies, shells will bounce off of enemies, expending one of their six bounces without the need to pierce."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " The final shot in the Brick Breakers clip has a 75% chance to be a red turtle-shell that deals more damage and homes in on enemies but does not bounce, and a 25% chance to be a blue turtle-shell that deals slightly more damage, increased knockback, homes in on enemies, and retains the ability to bounce."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Despite appearing to travel over the ground, Brick Braker shells are in fact flying, and can travel over pits."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This weapon is a reference to the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Mario",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mario_(franchise)"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " franchise of video games, well known for hiding items in nondescript, breakable bricks."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The synergy  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Block Party"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " is likely a reference to the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Mario Party",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mario_Party"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " series of Mario games."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The weapon is also possibly a reference to "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Breakout",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Breakout_(video_game)"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", which is also known as Brick Breaker on many platforms."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The name of the achievement that unlocks this gun is a reference to the game Castle Crashers."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Betrayer's Shield",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/8/82/Betrayer%27s_Shield.png",
    "notes": "Upon reloading, leaves a protective shield on the ground. Players in that area will be protected until the shield has absorbed a number of bullets.",
    "quote": "Actually A Gun",
    "quality": "B",
    "type": "Automatic",
    "dps": "32.3",
    "magazine_size": "12",
    "ammo_capacity": "350",
    "damage": "7",
    "fire_rate": "0.10",
    "reload_time": "1.5",
    "shot_speed": "23",
    "range": "18",
    "force": "12",
    "spread": "5",
    "class": "PISTOL",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Betrayer's Lies"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If the player has "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Lies",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", Betrayer's Shield gains infinite ammo, a much larger magazine size, increased accuracy, and extremely high fire rate. Like other guns with infinite ammo, it cannot reveal secret rooms.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " "
                },
                {
                  "t": "synref",
                  "v": "Betrayer's Lies"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " can be combined with other guns using "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Duct Tape",
                  "kind": "item"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " by dropping Lies, using Duct Tape, and picking up Lies again.\n"
                }
              ],
              "sub": [
                {
                  "tokens": [
                    {
                      "t": "text",
                      "v": "However, using Duct Tape with a beam weapon such as "
                    },
                    {
                      "t": "ref",
                      "v": "Disintegrator",
                      "kind": "gun"
                    },
                    {
                      "t": "text",
                      "v": " will cause it to eventually run out of ammo. It can be refilled by simply dropping it and picking it up again."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Betrayer's Shield is peculiarly a member of the PISTOL "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Guns",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " despite almost certainly being more at home among the members of the FULLAUTO class."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "There are a few bullet patterns in certain boss fights that the shield will not block, such as the large bullets that the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Cannonbalrog",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " shoots when he disappears and the line of bullets that spins around the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Resourceful Rat",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " in his first phase."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Lower Case r",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/f/f4/Lower_Case_r.png",
    "notes": "Fires a burst of 6 bullets that spell out the word BULLET. Can spell out more words with synergy.",
    "quote": "Alphabetical!",
    "quality": "D",
    "type": "Burst",
    "dps": "18.0",
    "magazine_size": "36",
    "ammo_capacity": "900",
    "damage": "2. 2",
    "fire_rate": "0.07",
    "reload_time": "2.0",
    "shot_speed": "25",
    "range": "1,000",
    "force": "14",
    "spread": "0",
    "class": "SILLY",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Lower Case r is voiced by "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Doseone",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", the composer of "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Enter the Gungeons",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " soundtrack."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This gun, while obviously a surface level reference to the basic shape of the letter r, may also be a reference to early computer adventure games. These early games used ASCII art comprised of letters and numbers to render a game world."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The reload animation of the Lower Case r consists of a text cursor deleting the letter with a backspace, and typing an entirely new r."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The impact animation of Lower Case rs bullets consists of the spelled word 'BLAM!' rather than an actual impact."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Ammonomicon",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " quote "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "\"Alphabetical!\"",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " may be a reference to early seasons of the show "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Adventure Time",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", where the protagonist "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Finn",
              "url": "https://adventuretime.fandom.com/wiki/Finn"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " sometimes exclaims "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "\"Mathematical!\"",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The word \"TAFFER\" which can be fired with "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Angry Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " is a reference to the same word used as an insult by guards in "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Thief: The Dark Project",
              "url": "https://thief.fandom.com/wiki/Taffer"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The synergy "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Radiant",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " may be a visual pun referencing "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Radiant Silvergun",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Radiant_Silvergun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Dave Crooks",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " has agreed with Reddit suggestions that the Lower Case r should change the pitch and speed of "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Doseone",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " voice acting depending on the players "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Rate of Fire",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ". However, this was never implemented."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "All of Lower Case r's synergies which modify the words fired were created based on the suggestion of "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "a Reddit post",
              "url": "https://www.reddit.com/r/EnterTheGungeon/comments/6dysqn/suggestion_lower_case_r_awesome_rework_idea"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " by user u/XelNecra. The post directly describes the  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Rabid"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ",  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Ravishing"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ",  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Reinforced"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ",  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Root"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", and  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Remnant"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " synergies, while suggesting that more could be created for other "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Bullet modifiers",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Lower Case r appears held by a statue of "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Kaliber",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " in the reveal trailer for "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Enter the Gungeon 2",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Excaliber",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/5/5f/Excaliber.png",
    "notes": "Fires a burst of three piercing sword projectiles. Reloading swings the sword, destroying nearby bullets and damaging nearby enemies. Increases curse by 2.5.",
    "quote": "Once And Future",
    "quality": "B",
    "type": "Burst",
    "dps": "43.7",
    "magazine_size": "32",
    "ammo_capacity": "280",
    "damage": "7",
    "fire_rate": "0.15",
    "reload_time": "0.48",
    "shot_speed": "26",
    "range": "1,000",
    "force": "15",
    "spread": "0",
    "class": "FULLAUTO",
    "curse": 2.5,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Buster Gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If the player has "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "RPG",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", Excaliber fires three or four shots in a cone whenever it is reloaded."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Snicker-snack"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If the player has "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Vorpal Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", Excaliber fires a spread of 3 homing shots that deal 20% less damage."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Throw All Daggers"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If the player has "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Knife Shield",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", it generates two layers of knives upon use."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "If reloaded with a partially emptied magazine, the sword swing will deal approximately 27.5 damage."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "If reloaded with an empty magazine, the sword swing will deal 80 damage."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "trivia": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Unused and Cut Content/Synergies",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - ("
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "CustomSynergyType.SHARDBLADE",
              "style": "code"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ") If the player has "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Sprun",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", it will give Sprun a secondary trigger."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The fact that the weapon increases "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Curse",
              "kind": "stat"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " while being carried stems from the Gungeon rejecting melee weapons."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Snicker-snack"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " synergy is a reference to Lewis Carroll's poem "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Jabberwocky",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jabberwocky"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Buster Gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " synergy is likely a reference to the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Buster Sword",
              "url": "http://finalfantasy.wikia.com/wiki/Buster_Sword"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", a weapon from the Final Fantasy RPG Series."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The gun's name and sword-like appearance are a reference to the Excalibur, the sword associated with King Arthur, given to him by the Lady of the Lake.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The name of the weapon is a portmanteau of Excalibur, the sword, and caliber, the internal diameter of the barrel of a gun or of a projectile."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The weapon's quote is a reference to T. H. White's work "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ext",
                  "v": "The Once and Future King",
                  "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Once_and_Future_King"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": ", which is largely about King Arthur's life."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The gun's appearance when held by the character is likely a reference to the Qualta Blade carried by Ka D'Argo in "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Farscape",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ".\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Specifically, the stylized grip that splits off from the stock/handle, and the way the sword splits down the middle to reveal the rifle."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The physical Ammonomicon has a doodle of a crowd of Gundead, along with a crowned Bullet Kin. It's unknown if it's the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Bullet King",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " as a child, another Lead Lord, a possible Bullet Prince, or the mythical hero in the Entry for Excaliber."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The concept of slashing bullets out of the air is revisited with "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Blasphemy",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Huntsman",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " and "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Fightsabre",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " (although Fightsabre instead "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "redirects",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " midair bullets)."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Face Melter",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/4/4f/Face_Melter.png",
    "notes": "Simultaneously fires music notes in four directions. Places an amplifier on the ground at the player's position upon reloading. Whenever the Face Melter is fired, the amplifier will fire music notes in the same pattern. Reloading again will remove the amplifier and place a new one.",
    "quote": "Squiddley-squiddley-wheeyooo!",
    "quality": "B",
    "type": "Automatic",
    "dps": "40.0",
    "magazine_size": "600",
    "ammo_capacity": "600",
    "damage": "4",
    "fire_rate": "0.10",
    "reload_time": "1.2",
    "shot_speed": "15",
    "range": "15",
    "force": "13",
    "spread": "6",
    "class": "SILLY",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Simultaneously fires four streams of musical notes at 90° intervals."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Creates an amplifier on the ground when reloading. While firing, the active amplifier will fire bullets of its own in sync with the main gun, including aim angle.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Only one amplifier can be active at a time. Creating a new amplifier by reloading will remove any previous ones."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Plays a unique song while fired, replacing regular backing music."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "item_interactions": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Duct Tape",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If another gun is duct taped onto the Face Melter, the amp left by the Face Melter on reloading will "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "also",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " fire projectiles from the taped-on weapon."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Backup Gun",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - As the Face Melter already fires backwards, the backup gun effectively doubles the bullet output of the Face Melter with no downside."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Remote Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - All bullets created by the Face Melter will be remote controlled, allowing all streams from both the gun and its amplifier to be easily funneled into one enemy, dealing massive damage."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Amplifiers do not have hitboxes, meaning that enemies can potentially stand on top of them and be damaged by all four note streams at once. This is particularly easy to achieve with enemies with large hitboxes, such as "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Bosses",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " Possible Bug In co-op, if playing as "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "The Cultist",
              "kind": "character"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", reloading will drop the amplifier at the other player's location."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This gun is a reference to the musical slang for powerful heavy metal guitar solos."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The tooltip and name may be a reference to the game "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Brütal Legend",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Br%C3%BCtal_Legend"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", where there is a solo called Face Melter."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The amplifier dropped after reloading closely resembles that of a "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Marshall",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Marshall_Amplification"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " MG gold series amplifier."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The gun resembles a cherry Gibson Flying V, but when obtaining the synergy  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Alternative Rock"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " it will take the appearance of a blue Gibson Firebird."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Really Special Lute",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/5/56/Really_Special_Lute.png",
    "notes": "Fires in a very wide spread. Buffs the player's companions. Chance to Charm enemies.",
    "quote": "Purple Prose",
    "quality": "C",
    "type": "Automatic",
    "dps": "82.5",
    "magazine_size": "75",
    "ammo_capacity": "300",
    "damage": "42 (6x7)",
    "fire_rate": "0.5",
    "reload_time": "1.2",
    "shot_speed": "9",
    "range": "10",
    "force": "13",
    "spread": "?",
    "class": "SILLY",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Fires a spread of 7 musical note bullets that each have an 8.5% chance to "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Charm",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " enemies for 6 seconds."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "While firing, buffs the players "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Companions",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "- doubling their damage.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "This companion buff does not apply to most melee attacks, such as those of the  "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Wolf",
                  "kind": "item"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " or  "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Ser Junkan",
                  "kind": "lore"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Plays a unique song while fired."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "item_interactions": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Duct Tape",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - As the effect of the Really Special Lute is tied to the gun itself, if the lute is duct taped onto another gun it will no longer buff the players companions."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Battle Standard",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - The companion damage buff from firing the lute stacks with the companion damage buff of the Battle Standard in "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "most",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " cases."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Chicken Flute",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - While the lute is held, the number of hits the chicken companion has to take in order to summon a chicken swarm is halved. Unlike other companion effects of the lute, the lute does not need to actually be playing for this to be in effect.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Playing the lute on its own has no effect on the damage of the chicken swarm."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Battle Standard",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " +  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Chicken Flute",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If the lute is held "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "while",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " the player also has the battle standard in their inventory, the damage of the chicken swarm summoned by the chicken flute is increased by 80%."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This gun is completely unaffected by accuracy increasing items, such as  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Muscle Relaxant",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This gun’s description is a reference to Patrick Rothfuss’s "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Kingkiller Chronicle",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " book series. The main character, Kvothe, plays the lute, and searches throughout the series for a way to defeat the Chandrian, a magical group that cause flames to turn blue when they are near."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Three Part Harmony"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " synergy may be a reference to the "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Kingkiller Chronicle",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", as the main character at one point performs once a difficult ballad requiring them to play three melodies at once : two from the lute and one by singing."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This guns ability to buff companions is likely a reference to the Bard class in "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Dungeons & Dragons",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", and their ability to give allies inspiration."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "In the final scene of "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "The Bullet",
              "kind": "character"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "'s past, a "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Coaler",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " can be seen holding the lute.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "This is notable, as the Bullets Past was added in the "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Supply Drop Update",
                  "kind": "lore"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": ", while the Lute was only properly added in the "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Farewell To Arms",
                  "kind": "unresolved"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " Update."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Really Special Lute existed as an unfinished, unobtainable weapon in "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Enter the Gungeon",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " for years prior to its inclusion in the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Farewell To Arms",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " Update. This unused version of the Lute was a clone of the  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Face Melter",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", and behaved identically."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The song played by the Really Special Lute was composed by "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Dodge Roll",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " sound designer "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Erica Hampson",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ". The name of the song is unknown."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Trident",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/9/9a/Trident.png",
    "notes": "Fires a long-range piercing laser beam. Destroys nearby bullets and pushes enemies away while reloading.",
    "quote": "Under The Sea",
    "quality": "A",
    "type": "Semiautomatic",
    "dps": "46.5",
    "magazine_size": "6",
    "ammo_capacity": "300",
    "damage": "8",
    "fire_rate": "0.08",
    "reload_time": "1.0",
    "shot_speed": "600",
    "range": "1,000",
    "force": "4",
    "spread": "0",
    "class": "SILLY",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Fires an extremely fast moving ray of light that can pierce once."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "While reloading, nearby enemy bullets are destroyed, and nearby enemies are pushed away from the player."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "item_interactions": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Book of Chest Anatomy",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " +  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Brave New World"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - Because Book of Chest Anatomy raises the chance of broken chests dropping an item to 55%, all chests effectively have a 55% chance to drop the item they were predicted to contain when broken."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Spamming the fire button while "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Dodge Roll (Move)",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " causes the gun to fire considerably faster for a brief time after the dodge roll has concluded."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This weapon emits light from its tip, illuminating a small area."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Gunjurer",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " can catch shots from the Trident, despite them being extremely fast and piercing."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Under The Sea",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " is a reference to a song from "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "The Little Mermaid (1989 film)",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Little_Mermaid_(1989_film)"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Trident actually fires a small projectile, but it is covered up by the cosmetic beam."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The synergy  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Brave New World"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " may be a reference to the DC Comic Superhero \"Aquaman\" who rules an underwater kingdom, wields a trident as a symbol of authority, and has a prosthetic hand.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "It may also be a reference to the animated Disney film \"The Little Mermaid\", as the titular mermaid Ariel trades her voice for legs, her father Poseidon wields a trident, and the fish companion summoned by the synergy resembles Ariel's companion, Flounder. Additionally, Ariel sings a song titled \"Part of Your World\", alluded to in the synergy's name, \"Brave New World\"."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Kruller Glaive",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/4/48/Kruller_Glaive.png",
    "notes": "Throws a boomerang-like projectile that homes in on multiple enemies, damaging and sometimes stunning them.",
    "quote": "Studied the Blade",
    "quality": "B",
    "type": "Charged",
    "dps": "20.8",
    "magazine_size": "1",
    "ammo_capacity": "100",
    "damage": "25",
    "fire_rate": "0.2",
    "reload_time": "1.0",
    "shot_speed": "?",
    "range": "?",
    "force": "10",
    "spread": "?",
    "class": "NONE",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Charges up to throw a glaive projectile. This glaive travels in an arc, returning to the player like a boomerang.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "This glaive can come in on enemies while it travels, deviating from its arc."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Enemies struck by the glaive are "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Status Effects",
                  "kind": "lore"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " for 5 seconds."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Kruller Glaive is one of the three weapons in the NONE "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Guns",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " that can be obtained in normal play, the others being the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Chamber Gun",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " and the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Slinger",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "If the player has "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Helix Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", glaives lose their homing."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Due to the weapon's movement pattern, "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Gunjurer",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " can't reclaim the projectile to throw it back at the player, making it useful to deal with them."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Both the name and weapon are a reference to the science fiction film Krull. Unlike the Glaive in the film, the Kruller Glaive cannot disperse energy blasts, go through solid substances or kill in a single hit."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The weapon's tagline is a reference to an internet meme, "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "\"I studied the blade.\"",
              "url": "https://knowyourmeme.com/memes/i-studied-the-blade"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The weapon's description may be a reference to the term \""
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Mall Ninja,",
              "url": "https://www.urbandictionary.com/define.php?term=mall%20ninja"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "\" a derogatory term used to describe individuals who purchase useless items or specialty equipment purely to look more threatening.  The stereotypical Mall Ninja owns bladed weaponry that has little application in an actual combat situation."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "blade"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " synergy may be a reference to the superhero movie "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Blade",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Blade_(film)"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Crave The Glaive synergies’ function and design may be a reference to the Glaive Ricochet from Bloons TD."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Abyssal Tentacle",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/f/fe/Abyssal_Tentacle.png",
    "notes": "Fires a tentacle that homes in on and grips enemies, damaging them.",
    "quote": "Look Away",
    "quality": "A",
    "type": "Beam",
    "dps": "22.5",
    "magazine_size": "500",
    "ammo_capacity": "500",
    "damage": "22.5/s",
    "fire_rate": "0.10",
    "reload_time": "N/A",
    "shot_speed": "1,000",
    "range": "30",
    "force": "10",
    "spread": "0",
    "class": "SILLY",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "item_interactions": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Backup Gun",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - A second tentacle is fired behind the player, latching onto enemies of its own accord and essentially doubling damage output."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Ring of Triggers",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - Using an active item causes a great number of tentacles to erupt in all directions, latching onto enemies and clearing entire rooms extremely quickly.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "While effective on "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Bosses",
                  "kind": "lore"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": ", it is even more powerful against mini-bosses as they have no damage cap."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The tentacle can grip enemies through walls."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The tentacle can damage disappearing bosses like "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Cannonbalrog",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " and "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "High Priest",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " if they are connected and kept while vanished."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This gun is a reference to the character \"Purple Tentacle\" — a sentient, disembodied tentacle with plans for world domination — from the LucasArts game "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Day of the Tentacle.",
              "style": "i"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Decoy Octorok"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " synergy is a reference to the Metal Gear Solid character, "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Decoy Octopus",
              "url": "http://metalgear.wikia.com/wiki/Decoy_Octopus"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " and the purple, tentacled Legend of Zelda "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "enemies of the same name",
              "url": "https://zelda.gamepedia.com/Octorok"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ".\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "It is also a reference to Dave Crooks, one of Enter the Gungeon's developers, whose handle is DecoyOctorok."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The gun could also be a reference to the classic MMORPG RuneScape, where the Abyssal Tentacle is a power whip-like weapon."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Cosmic Horror"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " synergy is a reference to the Lovecraftian Horror genre, which is also sometimes called \"Cosmic Horror.\" Cosmic horror deals with malevolent, godlike aliens affecting our reality in various unpleasant ways, including tentacles coming out of black holes."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
