    "quote": "Tamagunchi",
    "quality": "C",
    "type": "Semiautomatic",
    "dps": "13.5-93.8",
    "magazine_size": "8-300",
    "ammo_capacity": "300 (first 5 forms) 150 (6th form)",
    "damage": "6-37.5",
    "fire_rate": "0.7 (snail form) 0.4 (other forms)",
    "reload_time": "1.5",
    "shot_speed": "Varies",
    "range": "Varies",
    "force": "Varies",
    "spread": "Varies",
    "class": "SILLY",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Has 6 different forms, starting as an amoeba and progressively evolving into more complex organisms. Every five different enemy "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "types",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " slain while the Evolver is in the players inventory (it does not need to be the active weapon) will evolve the gun."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "item_interactions": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Backup Gun",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - When the Evolver is in frog form, a second tongue is fired behind the player, latching onto enemies of its own accord and essentially doubling damage output."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Enemies do not need to be killed by Evolver's bullets for it to evolve."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The flavor text \"Tamagunchi\" is a reference to the digital pet brand "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Tamagotchi",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tamagotchi"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ". These digital pets progress through different life stages as they grow, much like the Evolver."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The gun's description is a reference to real-world "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "evolution denial",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Evolution#Social_and_cultural_responses"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", which remains prevalent in some communities."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The synergy  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "The Powerhouse of the Cell"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " is a reference to meme '"
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "The mitochondria is the powerhouse of the cell",
              "url": "https://knowyourmeme.com/sensitive/memes/mitochondria-is-the-powerhouse-of-the-cell"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "', which primarily serves to satirize the way in which modern education systems teach information that is not materially relevant to most people's everyday life."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
