  {
    "name": "Microtransaction Gun",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/f/f1/Microtransaction_Gun.png",
    "notes": "Shoots various figurines, books, and gems at the cost of 1 coin per shot.",
    "quote": "Pay To Win",
    "quality": "A",
    "type": "Semiautomatic",
    "dps": "44.4",
    "magazine_size": "Equal to Shells held",
    "ammo_capacity": "Equal to Shells held",
    "damage": "2/8/15/20",
    "fire_rate": "0.20",
    "reload_time": "N/A",
    "shot_speed": "?",
    "range": "?",
    "force": "?",
    "spread": "?",
    "class": "PISTOL",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Uses  instead of ammo."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Fires a variety of objects such as gems, books, money, and "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Gungeoneer",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " figurines. Different objects have different effects and damage values;"
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "item_interactions": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Duct Tape",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - Duct taping the Microtransaction Gun onto another weapon will no longer cause it to use  when fired.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Duct Taping the Microtransaction Gun onto another weapon will increase that weapons max ammo by 400, regardless of how much  the player holds."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The expression \"Pay To Win\" is derived from micro-transaction-heavy games, where an advantage over other players can be achieved by investing more money in the game."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The green crystals this gun fires and uses as its ammo counter may be a reference to \"Dungeon Keeper\", an iOS game by EA which famously blocked player progress unless they separately purchased green crystals which would greatly speed the game up."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The randomness of its projectiles may be a reference to lootboxes, a common in-game purchasable that provides random items to buyers."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Microtransaction Gun is available as an added DLC on Steam, thus allowing players to make a microtransaction to obtain the Microtransaction Gun immediately rather than unlocking it normally through gameplay."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Since the Microtransaction Gun's max ammo and current ammo are both equal to the player's , it always reads \"Full\" if the player tries to collect an ammo box while holding it."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Microtransaction Gun is the second most expensive item sold by "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Ox and Cadence",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Synergy  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "http://merch.devolverdigital.com"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - Is the link to the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Devolver Digital merchandise shop",
              "url": "https://merch.devolverdigital.com/"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
