  {
    "name": "Poxcannon",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/9/96/Poxcannon.png",
    "notes": "Shoots poisonous t-shirts with high knockback. Poisoned enemies create a poison puddle on death.",
    "quote": "Lousy T-Shirt",
    "quality": "C",
    "type": "Semiautomatic",
    "dps": "26.1",
    "magazine_size": "6",
    "ammo_capacity": "250",
    "damage": "15",
    "fire_rate": "0.35",
    "reload_time": "1.7",
    "shot_speed": "25",
    "range": "1,000",
    "force": "60",
    "spread": "5",
    "class": "SILLY",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "trivia": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Despite the Poxcannon poisoning enemies, the gun is not a member of the POISON "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Guns",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This weapon is a reference to the 'Pax Pox', a blanket term for diseases contracted at conventions, named after the Penny Arcade Expo, or 'PAX' convention.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "This is confirmed by a tweet released by the official Dodge Roll Games Twitter account on the 27th of April 2016 in which they announced "
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "\"Enter the Gungeon brought the PoxCannon back from PAX! Available in the latest update on PC!\"",
                  "style": "i"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " above a video demonstration of the weapon."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "This weapon may also be a reference to a practice of American colonists using smallpox infected blankets to spread disease among Native American peoples."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The tagline refers to the merchandising meme \"I [achieved something] and all I got was this lousy t-shirt\".\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The term \"Lousy\" in this case may also refer to Lice, which are parasitic insects."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
