  {
    "name": "Directional Pad",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/e/ef/Directional_Pad.png",
    "notes": "Fires bullets in four directions. Combos can be entered to fire fireballs or a grappling hook. After running out of ammo, it is destroyed but spawns a chest.",
    "quote": "Input Output",
    "quality": "B",
    "type": "Burst",
    "dps": "20.7",
    "magazine_size": "30",
    "ammo_capacity": "120",
    "damage": "8 (normal) 45 (fireball) 10 (grappling hook)",
    "fire_rate": "1.0",
    "reload_time": "1.6",
    "shot_speed": "?",
    "range": "?",
    "force": "?",
    "spread": "?",
    "class": "PISTOL",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Wrath Of The Blam"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If the player has "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Tear Jerker",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", Tear Jerker is replaced with a crying bullet head that can only fire in cardinal directions but deals double damage."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The grappling hook can be used to "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Stealing",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " items from "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Shop",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The chest spawned may be a "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Mimic",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Backup Gun",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " will effectively double the weapons damage, as it now shoots twice as many bullets per shot in each direction."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Should the player use "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Duct Tape",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " first on the Directional Pad, then on a second gun, the resulting combined gun will no longer be able to shoot grappling hooks or fireballs with the Directional Pad's special inputs. The gun will also not spawn a chest or be removed from the player's inventory if it runs out of ammo."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "trivia": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The inputs required to make the special shots are based on famous special attacks from fighting game series:\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The Fireball is the \"Hadouken\" attack performed by character Ryu in Street Fighter."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The Grappling Hook is the rope spear attack performed by character Scorpion in Mortal Kombat; this attack is referenced in the entry description."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Upon reloading, your character inputs the directional pad part of the Konami Code."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Wrath of the Blam"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " synergy is a reference to the \"Wrath Of The Lamb\" DLC for The Binding Of Isaac. The crying bullet head that Tear Jerker turns into resembles Isaac's face."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The \"ancient convocation of wizards\" referenced in the Ammonomicon entry could be a reference to the film \"The Wizard,\" as the Directional pad resembles the Dpad on the NES controller."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "In "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Sorceress",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " you could theoretically get infinite items by using the Directional Pad until it runs out of ammo but it is an extremely long process."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "3rd Party Controller",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/a/a1/3rd_Party_Controller.png",
    "notes": "Upon hitting an enemy, they will move in the same direction the player moves, and shoot towards the crosshair if the player shoots.",
    "quote": "Assuming Direct Control",
    "quality": "A",
    "type": "Semiautomatic",
    "dps": "4.7",
    "magazine_size": "10",
    "ammo_capacity": "300",
    "damage": "2.5",
    "fire_rate": "0.4",
    "reload_time": "1.75",
    "shot_speed": "30",
    "range": "1,000",
    "force": "13",
    "spread": "10",
    "class": "CHARM",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Mad Cats"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If the player also has "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Cat Bullet King Throne",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", the bullets shot from Cat Bullet King Throne home in on enemies while 3rd Party Controller is equipped."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Controlled enemies do not deal contact damage to the player, and can be killed safely by rolling over them."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Standing close to enemies also deals a small amount of constant damage to them while controlled."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Enemies can be controlled so that they walk into pits."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Some enemies can be made to fire much faster than usual, such as "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Shotgun Kin",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", who can shoot as fast as their animation with no reload time. This can be dangerous since the normal waves of bullets can fill the screen instead."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Bosses cannot be controlled."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "trivia": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Mad Cats"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " synergy is a reference to "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "MadCatz Interactive",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mad_Catz"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", formerly one of the leading producers of third-party gaming controllers."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "\"Assuming Direct Control\" is a reference to Harbinger from \"Mass Effect 2\" who, before gaining control over any regular enemy, would announce it by saying this phrase."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "During the reloading animation of this gun, the Gungeoneer destroys the controller and takes out a new one."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The description implies that the 3rd Party Controller belonged to "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "The Cultist",
              "kind": "character"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Gunzheng",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/9/9f/Gunzheng.png",
    "notes": "Rapidly fires inaccurate, piercing, homing arrows.",
    "quote": "Hustle",
    "quality": "B",
