          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Despite its "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Ammonomicon",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " description, the Sling is among the most powerful  tier weapons- especially against bosses."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Sling dealing additional damage against bosses is a reference to the biblical tale of "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "David and Goliath",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Goliath"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", where David slays the giant Goliath by the use of his sling."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Both the flavor text "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "\"Outrageous!\"",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " and the  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Slings and Arrows"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " synergy are references to the famous "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "\"To be or not to be\"",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " soliloquy in Shakespeare's "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Hamlet",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", in which Hamlet refers to enduring "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "\"the slings and arrows of outrageous fortune\"",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Cactus",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/a/a6/Cactus.png",
    "notes": "Fires needles.",
    "quote": "1000 Needles!",
    "quality": "C",
    "type": "Automatic",
    "dps": "25.0",
    "magazine_size": "1,000",
    "ammo_capacity": "1,000",
    "damage": "2.5",
    "fire_rate": "0.10",
    "reload_time": "0.0",
    "shot_speed": "60",
    "range": "1,000",
    "force": "1",
    "spread": "7",
    "class": "SHITTY",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "item_interactions": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Lich's Eye Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - Cactus with all its synergies combined is infamously powerful, being a reliable weapon far into the later chambers- even more so than most other weapons with all their synergies."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Remote Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " +  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Cactus Flower"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "/ "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Succulent DOOM"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "/ "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Thorn Bath, ooh!"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "/ "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Lich's Eye Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - The sheer number of projectiles created by the cactus with its synergies makes Remote Bullets very potent. The ability to redirect all the countless cactus needles towards a single target results in massive damage."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "\"1000 Needles!\" is a reference to a move used by the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Cactuar",
              "url": "https://finalfantasy.fandom.com/wiki/Cactuar"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", a recurring enemy from the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Final Fantasy",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Final_Fantasy"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " series, who resembles a walking cactus."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "\"Succulent DOOM\" may possibly be a reference to the album "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Special Herbs",
              "url": "https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=OLAK5uy_lqvzsdmMq6h3-TWD3NhhcMB5Uym0WOIOc"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " by "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "MF DOOM",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/MF_Doom"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The \"undiscovered Chamber\" in the Cactus' description may be the unused "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Unused and Cut Content",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " floor."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Black Hole Gun",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/7/79/Black_Hole_Gun.png",
    "notes": "Charges to fire a black hole that attract enemies and absorb enemy bullets.",
    "quote": "Won't You Come",
    "quality": "A",
    "type": "Charged",
    "dps": "29.6",
    "magazine_size": "1",
    "ammo_capacity": "30",
    "damage": "10",
    "fire_rate": "1.00",
    "reload_time": "1.56",
    "shot_speed": "4",
    "range": "1,000",
    "force": "9",
    "spread": "0",
    "class": "SILLY",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Cosmic Horror"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If the player has "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Abyssal Tentacle",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", black holes fire three tentacles while active."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The black hole will also attract friendly projectiles; however, beam type weapons will not be affected."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The black hole will not attract projectiles that aren't moving, such as "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Blockner",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "'s shields."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Most enemies killed by the black hole will not drop ."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Black Hole Gun is one of the best guns for clearing rooms as it can kill a whole wave of enemies with one shot while removing all projectiles."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "In boss fights it is best to switch to other weapons while the black hole is traveling. This increases damage output while saving ammo. Beam weapons are the best choice as they are not affected by the black hole."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The shots can suck up all boss projectiles, including the Mine Flayer's mines, the Dragun's knives & RPGs, etc."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "If combined with any high-ammo weapon using "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Duct Tape",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " or used with any item that grants multishot such as "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Scattershot",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", it becomes a way to easily beat every boss without taking damage. Especially when used with the  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Cosmic Horror"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " Synergy."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Interestingly, black holes appear to make the player immune to bullets while present, even if the bullet appears to hit the player. This can be seen most during "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Agunim",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "'s "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "R&G Dept.",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " fight and when fighting "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Shadow Magician",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", as their \"bullet lightning\" attacks cannot damage the player while a black hole is present, even if the bullets from the lightning pattern visibly connect with the player."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The visual distortion effect that black holes cause can stack with each other, and as such, the distortion effect intensifies if multiple black holes are present in a small space."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "trivia": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The gun's Ammonomicon Entry is a reference to the 1994 song \""
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Black Hole Sun",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Black_Hole_Sun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "\" by the American rock band Soundgarden."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Cosmic Horror"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " Synergy is a reference to the Lovecraftian Horror genre, which is also sometimes called \"Cosmic Horror.\" Cosmic horror deals with malevolent, godlike aliens affecting our reality in various unpleasant ways, including tentacles coming out of black holes."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Another  "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Cosmic Horror"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " reference might be Rift inducer 5000 from "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Ratchet and Clank",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ratchet_%26_Clank"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " series."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Black Hole Gun was first teased by "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Dodge Roll",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " designer "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Dave Crooks",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " in a Twitter post on the 19th of January 2015, supposedly the same day it was implemented."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "BSG",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/5/57/BSG.png",
    "notes": "Slowly charges up to fire a large high-damage projectile.",
    "quote": "Big Shooty Gun",
    "quality": "1S",
    "type": "Charged",
    "dps": "47.5",
    "magazine_size": "1",
    "ammo_capacity": "25",
    "damage": "50",
    "fire_rate": "4.00",
    "reload_time": "2.4",
    "shot_speed": "25",
    "range": "1,000",
    "force": "10",
    "spread": "0",
    "class": "EXPLOSIVE",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Items that increase shot speed (such as "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Rocket-Powered Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ") will allow projectiles to reach their maximum distance quicker and thus detonate in less time."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Projectiles will detonate instantly if they come in contact with a black hole created by either the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Black Hole Gun",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " or "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Singularity",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The explosion's effect is identical to that of the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Bracket Key",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", with the exception that it does not stop additional enemy waves from spawning; it can damage certain bosses during attacks where they are normally invincible, and cannot travel to other rooms."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The damage of the explosion is unaffected by passive items."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The explosion does not crack walls leading to secret rooms."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Because the gun's fire rate is slower than its reload time, the gun cannot be charged immediately after it is reloaded.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Similar to other guns with a magazine size of 1 (e.g. "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Stinger",
                  "kind": "gun"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "), dropping the gun and picking it back up will instantly reload it and reset the fire rate delay, allowing it to be charged immediately."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "If used with the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Bloody 9mm",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", it has an almost 100% chance to fire a berserk bullet if fully charged."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "trivia": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "With more than double the charge time of the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Molotov Launcher",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", the Big Shooty gun has the slowest fire rate of all guns in the game."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This gun is a reference to a weapon called the BFG 9000 from the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "DOOM",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DOOM"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " series.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The In The Mood synergy likely references the high walking speed of the character from Doom. The Thunderclap resembles another gun from Doom, whereas the STRAFE gun may refer to how fast the Doom Marine can strafe. The synergy name is likely because 'mood' is 'doom' spelled backwards."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Similarly to how BSG stands for Big Shooty Gun, BFG stands for Big F*cking Gun."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Compressed Air Tank",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/a/af/Compressed_Air_Tank.png",
    "notes": "Charges to fire a shark that swim around the room, seeking enemies and biting them.",
    "quote": "You Know My Work",
    "quality": "A",
    "type": "Charged",
    "dps": "125.0",
    "magazine_size": "1",
    "ammo_capacity": "50",
    "damage": "50",
    "fire_rate": "0.60",
    "reload_time": "1.2",
    "shot_speed": "35",
    "range": "",
    "force": "60",
    "spread": "6",
    "class": "SILLY",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Sharks leave water "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Goop",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " as they travel. Sharks fired into invalid places, such as directly into walls, will immediately disappear, leaving a large circular puddle of water behind."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Sharks trigger a different animation depending on if they kill their target. If the shark kills its prey, it will erupt from the floor and swallow the enemy whole. Enemies are stunned and cannot attack while being swallowed.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Enemies that fire bullets upon death will not do so when swallowed whole by a shark. Examples include most varieties of "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Shotgun Kin",
                  "kind": "unresolved"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": ", and "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Bloodbulon",
                  "kind": "unresolved"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Enemies that explode upon death will not do so when swallowed whole by a shark, including "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Pinhead",
                  "kind": "unresolved"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " and "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Nitra",
                  "kind": "unresolved"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Sharks will not swim over pits, with the exception of pits in "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Boss",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " rooms. This is likely to allow the sharks to hit bosses which sit in pits, such as the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "High Dragun",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ".\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Sharks that are fired while over a pit will be able to swim over pits until they reach land again, at which point they will again refuse to travel over pits."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "item_interactions": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Battery Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - The water left behind by fired sharks is automatically electrified, dealing considerable indirect damage to enemies."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Ghost Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - Sharks will not pierce enemies, regardless of how many piercing effects the player has."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Snowballets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - The meandering swimming behaviour of the Sharks allows them to build up considerable damage."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Backup Gun",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - The enemy tracking ability of Sharks makes the direction of the additional shark added by Backup Gun irrelevant, as it will hunt down enemies regardless."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Despite sharks disabling the on-death effects of some enemies, enemies will still drop any loot assigned to them. Enemies that split into other enemies such as "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Blobulon",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Poisbulon",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", and "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "King Bullat",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " will still split when eaten by a shark."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Although this gun fires water, it cannot be used to get the item from the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Black Market",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This weapon and its unique ability are a reference to the 1975 movie Jaws. It also makes a brief sound resembling the Jaws theme whenever it fires.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The \"Smile you son of a...\" synergy is a reference to Martin Brody's final line in Jaws before killing the shark. Brody wields a M1 and shoots an air tank in its mouth."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "It could also be a reference to the Land Shark Gun from the game Armed and Dangerous which behave the same way."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Enemies that are in the process of being swallowed by a shark can still take knockback from things such as "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Blanks",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ". Even if knocked out of the mouth of the shark, they will be killed regardless."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
