  {
    "name": "Makeshift Cannon",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/d/d1/Makeshift_Cannon.png",
    "notes": "Charges to fire a blast of bouncing gems that deal massive damage each.",
    "quote": "You Only Get One Shot",
    "quality": "1S",
    "type": "Charged",
    "dps": "571.0",
    "magazine_size": "1",
    "ammo_capacity": "1",
    "damage": "1213.3 (approx)",
    "fire_rate": "0.50",
    "reload_time": "2.1",
    "shot_speed": "35",
    "range": "1,000",
    "force": "60",
    "spread": "6",
    "class": "SILLY",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "The Return"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If the player also has "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Pig",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", the Pig turns green to resemble "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Cannon",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", and shoots bat projectiles at nearby enemies."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Makeshift Cannon is one of the few guns able to ignore the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Bosses",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ". Because it only has one shot, it is recommended to only use it during boss fights."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "When the shots hit enemies and get destroyed they make an explosion, but it takes no damage."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Holey Grail",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " can refill Makeshift Cannon's ammo upon taking damage."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Having "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Magazine Rack",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " will allow you to create a loop. Using the item will make this gun have infinite bullets, allowing you to destroy bosses easily, while at the same time, recharging "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Magazine Rack",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " almost instantaneously."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Duct Tape",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " this to other weapons can immensely increase its ammo count.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Plunger",
                  "kind": "gun"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " is extremely effective when Duct Taped to Makeshift Cannon as it can instantly refill its ammo when standing on goop."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Relodestone",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " can refill the Makeshift Cannon right after firing it, making it possible to fire multiple Makeshift Cannon shots in rapid succession."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Ring of Triggers",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "'s effect can shoot Makeshift Cannon's bullets in all directions, dealing high damage without consuming its ammo.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Active items could also be recharged immediately due to the high damage."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "An Ammo Spread will only restore its shot if picked up while being held, since the 50% replenishment rounds up to 1 and the 20% replenishment rounds down, to 0."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Turkey",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "'s effect applies even if the player switches weapons between shots. This can be used to endlessly restore ammo for the Makeshift Cannon."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Because of Makeshift Cannon's piercing properties, which effectively guarantees its projectiles to always be destroyed upon hitting a wall, "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Orbital Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " can significantly increase Makeshift Cannon's damage output, however this will also be very loud."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "trivia": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The weapon's appearance and function is a reference to the Star Trek episode "
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "Arena",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Arena_(Star_Trek:_The_Original_Series)"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ",",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " in which Kirk makes such a weapon out of bamboo, hand-mixed black powder, diamonds, and vines."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The gun's pickup quote, \"You Only Get One Shot\", may be a reference to a line from the song, \"Lose Yourself\" by Eminem.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "It may also be a reference to OneShot, where the phrase and idea that \"You only get one shot\" is said and reinforced multiple times across the course of the game."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The weapon takes on a special broken appearance after being fired, which is restored after its ammo is refilled."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Devolver",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/5/58/Devolver.png",
    "notes": "Has a chance to devolve enemies into simpler enemies.",
    "quote": "Degenerates",
    "quality": "C",
    "type": "Semiautomatic",
    "dps": "24.1",
    "magazine_size": "6",
    "ammo_capacity": "100",
    "damage": "6",
    "fire_rate": "0.14",
    "reload_time": "0.78",
    "shot_speed": "25",
    "range": "1,000",
    "force": "10",
    "spread": "8",
    "class": "SILLY",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Contractual Obligation"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If the player has "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Gungine",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", a pool of oil spawns underneath enemies killed using it."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Cool Kids Club"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If the player has "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Strafe Gun",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", continuously moving with the Strafe Gun held gives the player a yellow glow, increasing movement speed. The glow disappears if the player stops moving."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Overdose"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If the player also has "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Heavy Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", Heavy Bullets no longer decreases shot speed (this applies for all guns, not just  Devolver).\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "When the player gains the  "
                },
                {
                  "t": "synref",
                  "v": "Overdose"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": " synergy through "
                },
                {
                  "t": "ref",
                  "v": "Lich's Eye Bullets",
                  "kind": "item"
                },
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": ", bullet speed is increased for all guns."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "synref",
              "v": "Serious Sam Publishing Contract"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - If the player has "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Serious Cannon",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", alongside the cannonball, Serious Cannon fires a screaming Beheaded Kamikaze who chases enemies and explodes on contact."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The devolve effect also works on the bells spawned by the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Mine Flayer",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ". This changes the bells into Arrowkin as well as sending out the ring of bullets they usually emit upon death, so using the gun in this fight is not recommended."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The devolve effect does not work on bosses.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "The devolve effect also does not work on Mimics; however, bullets will still occasionally play the \"devolve\" sound when hitting a Mimic."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Devolving an enemy causes it to drop "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Coins",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Devolved enemies will spawn with full health, in some cases granting them more health than before transformation."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "trivia": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "This gun is a reference to the publisher of Enter the Gungeon, "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Devolver Digital",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ".\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Its ammo counter is represented by Ds similar to the Devolver Digital logo."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The quote \"Degenerates\" preceding the description is a play on words, describing both the effect of the gun (degenerating the strength of enemies) as well as poking fun at Devolver Digital by implying they're degenerates (people of limited morality)."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Prior to the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "A Farewell to Arms Update",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": ", the Devolver could devolve enemies into other enemies besides Arrowkin."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "Finished Gun",
    "icon": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/enterthegungeon_gamepedia/images/b/b5/Finished_Gun.png",
    "notes": "Replaces Unfinished Gun once the Ammonomicon is complete. Fires ricochet bullets. The final shot in magazine reflects enemy bullets back.",
    "quote": "Thanks For Playing",
    "quality": "D",
    "type": "Semiautomatic",
    "dps": "84.1",
    "magazine_size": "5",
    "ammo_capacity": "500",
    "damage": "14 25 (final shot)",
    "fire_rate": "0.07",
    "reload_time": "0.78",
    "shot_speed": "30 20 (final shot)",
    "range": "1,000",
    "force": "14",
    "spread": "0",
    "class": "PISTOL",
    "curse": 0.0,
    "coolness": 0.0,
    "wiki": {
      "effects": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Fires black and white bullets that are each capable of bouncing up to twice; each time the bullet bounces, the damage will be multiplied by 1.5."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The final shot in each cylinder is a larger, piercing bullet that reflects enemy bullets it comes near as it travels, but does not bounce.\n"
            }
          ],
          "sub": [
            {
              "tokens": [
                {
                  "t": "text",
                  "v": "Reflected bullets each deal 10 damage, and are sent in the same direction as the main shot."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Increases  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Curse",
              "kind": "stat"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " by 5."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Finished Gun's firerate is so high that it effectively fires as fast as the player can pull the trigger, in most situations."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "item_interactions": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Orbital Bullets",
              "kind": "item"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " - The bullet reflecting final shot of each cylinder provides incredible defense against enemy bullets while orbiting around the player."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Finished Gun actually only has an  rank, however it is programmed to replace Unfinished Gun whenever it appears, thus letting it appear out of -tier chests."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The Finished Gun has the highest  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Curse",
              "kind": "stat"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " value of any gun or item in the game, due to its immense power."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "The line "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "\"A gun to rule them all\"",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " in the Finished Guns "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Ammonomicon",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " entry is a reference to the "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "\"",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "ext",
              "v": "One Ring",
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/One_Ring"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " to rule them all\"",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " from "
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "Lord Of The Rings",
              "style": "i"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " Bug After the Finished Gun has been unlocked, the  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Unfinished Gun",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " may still appear on "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Pedestal Mimic",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " or be knocked out of the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Resourceful Rat (Boss)",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " during the third phase of his bossfight, however it will turn into the Finished Gun when dropped by the enemy onto the ground."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " Bug After the Finished Gun has been unlocked, the  "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Unfinished Gun",
              "kind": "gun"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " may still appear in the "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Resourceful Rat",
              "kind": "lore"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " free gun selection on "
            },
            {
              "t": "ref",
              "v": "Shortcut",
              "kind": "unresolved"
            },
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " runs. It will not be replaced by the Finished Gun."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "tokens": [
            {
              "t": "text",
              "v": " Bug The Finished Gun can be acquired twice in one run, however the second one will disappear when picked up."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  }
